1
00:00:04,510 --> 00:00:07,480
We will begin Round Two
of the card battle.

2
00:00:09,240 --> 00:00:10,450
Yellow, one win.

3
00:00:10,580 --> 00:00:12,810
Hyun Sung Joo has bet on yellow, one win.

4
00:00:13,550 --> 00:00:15,580
I'll go with blue, six wins.

5
00:00:16,080 --> 00:00:18,220
Kang Ji Hoo has bet on blue, six wins.

6
00:00:18,920 --> 00:00:20,490
I bet on six wins as planned.

7
00:00:23,690 --> 00:00:25,530
Heo Seong Beom, will you place your bet?

8
00:00:25,660 --> 00:00:29,800
(Team C and P3 alliance came up with
a strategy to have 6 wins.)

9
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:33,900
I'll bet on yellow, zero wins.

10
00:00:34,570 --> 00:00:36,800
Heo Seong Beom has bet on yellow,
zero wins.

11
00:00:37,710 --> 00:00:40,580
Seong Beom should've passed the round.

12
00:00:40,780 --> 00:00:42,040
But he bet on zero wins.

13
00:00:42,710 --> 00:00:45,750
Heo Seong Beom has become the master
by betting on zero wins.

14
00:00:47,150 --> 00:00:48,850
The bet has ended.

15
00:00:49,280 --> 00:00:51,820
Yellow is the master color of this round.

16
00:00:54,560 --> 00:00:56,560
He betrayed me like that?
As soon as we started?

17
00:00:58,260 --> 00:00:59,790
Who did he team up with instead?

18
00:01:04,070 --> 00:01:08,570
(20 minutes ago)

19
00:01:08,570 --> 00:01:10,540
So what's the result?
Are we in the negative?

20
00:01:10,570 --> 00:01:12,410
We're not. It's just that
the other two teams took this much.

21
00:01:12,410 --> 00:01:13,940
The other two teams did
what we were going to do.

22
00:01:14,810 --> 00:01:17,210
We should've gone with
preventing zero wins.

23
00:01:17,210 --> 00:01:19,050
- Everyone...
- Goodness.

24
00:01:19,050 --> 00:01:20,210
I thought we'd definitely win this.

25
00:01:20,210 --> 00:01:21,780
That's why I made the deal with Sang Min.

26
00:01:21,780 --> 00:01:23,450
- But they took it.
- The red team.

27
00:01:23,550 --> 00:01:25,790
- How should we win this again?
- This red...

28
00:01:25,790 --> 00:01:27,460
What are you going to do?

29
00:01:27,490 --> 00:01:29,120
Will you keep helping them?

30
00:01:30,390 --> 00:01:33,060
The situation felt strange.

31
00:01:33,230 --> 00:01:36,160
When Sang Min,
while twirling his wine glass,

32
00:01:37,100 --> 00:01:40,200
said that no matter what happens
in Round One, we should work together...

33
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:42,670
and support
whichever team has higher points.

34
00:01:42,670 --> 00:01:45,410
I understood it
as them supporting my team.

35
00:01:45,410 --> 00:01:47,680
Since we had our plans
and we would win Round One.

36
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:51,010
But now, it's come to a point
where we need to support P1 to win.

37
00:01:51,150 --> 00:01:54,150
Did he calculate this far?

38
00:01:55,350 --> 00:01:57,850
Is Sang Min really a genius?

39
00:01:58,320 --> 00:02:00,350
I don't know. This is so hard.

40
00:02:00,350 --> 00:02:02,520
Impossible situations overlapped
one after another.

41
00:02:02,690 --> 00:02:05,490
I thought we'd definitely win Round One.

42
00:02:05,730 --> 00:02:08,230
That was why I promised Sang Min...

43
00:02:08,230 --> 00:02:09,660
that we'd support the team
with higher points.

44
00:02:09,760 --> 00:02:12,730
But now that that's not the case,
I kept mulling over it.

45
00:02:13,770 --> 00:02:17,670
(Team P3 promised to help Team P1
get the points.)

46
00:02:17,670 --> 00:02:19,170
We can't break down here. Get a grip.

47
00:02:19,170 --> 00:02:20,780
Twenty minutes isn't long.

48
00:02:21,410 --> 00:02:23,910
I made a good deal, didn't I?

49
00:02:24,250 --> 00:02:25,480
I made the deal...

50
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:26,680
- before the result was out.
- Good job.

51
00:02:26,750 --> 00:02:28,720
- That we should support the winning team.
- Good job.

52
00:02:28,780 --> 00:02:30,020
- They...
- And they accepted it?

53
00:02:30,020 --> 00:02:32,020
They promised to support us.

54
00:02:32,020 --> 00:02:33,590
- They'll help us win.
- They'll help us win.

55
00:02:34,260 --> 00:02:36,160
And they said they'd definitely win...

56
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:38,690
because their strategy
was better than ours.

57
00:02:38,690 --> 00:02:40,660
So I said, "Go ahead and win."

58
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,900
"Go for the win.
We'll help you win for sure."

59
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:46,470
So what happened is...

60
00:02:46,830 --> 00:02:48,170
He made a smart deal.

61
00:02:49,700 --> 00:02:51,140
- Goodness.
- Because...

62
00:02:51,440 --> 00:02:53,040
it's all about the time delay.

63
00:02:54,740 --> 00:02:56,440
That's something I can do.

64
00:02:56,540 --> 00:02:59,850
I'm the only one
who can coordinate an alliance.

65
00:02:59,850 --> 00:03:02,780
I reckon I have the ability to lead it.

66
00:03:02,850 --> 00:03:04,190
Then we can win this.

67
00:03:04,550 --> 00:03:06,550
We need to talk with them.

68
00:03:06,550 --> 00:03:08,260
They'll go first next.

69
00:03:08,390 --> 00:03:10,890
Anyhow,
we're going to be working together.

70
00:03:11,130 --> 00:03:14,460
Let's say
we'll work together until Round Six.

71
00:03:14,460 --> 00:03:16,660
- We don't need to do it now.
- It's better to go later.

72
00:03:16,660 --> 00:03:18,570
- We made a deal with you first.
- Okay.

73
00:03:18,570 --> 00:03:19,800
So we'll work together.

74
00:03:20,030 --> 00:03:22,440
They want to bet on zero wins.
Will we join them?

75
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,240
- No, we don't need to.
- Don't.

76
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:26,070
We can't.
We need to form an alliance with them.

77
00:03:26,070 --> 00:03:28,040
I already made a very strong bond...

78
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:29,840
- with Team P3.
- Really?

79
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:31,110
After Round One ended,

80
00:03:31,110 --> 00:03:33,850
I went up after talking with Jin Hyeong.

81
00:03:33,850 --> 00:03:36,980
And Sang Min said he already
made an alliance with Jin Ho's team.

82
00:03:37,390 --> 00:03:38,850
Your team...

83
00:03:38,850 --> 00:03:40,960
- and Team P2 formed an alliance.
- Yes.

84
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:43,420
Team P2 will rely on you. Right?

85
00:03:43,620 --> 00:03:45,360
So we should use it against them.

86
00:03:45,430 --> 00:03:47,660
But I think Team P3...

87
00:03:47,660 --> 00:03:50,430
will work with Team C until Round Two.

88
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:52,530
- Until Round 2?
- Yes, until Round 2.

89
00:03:52,530 --> 00:03:53,670
Then we...

90
00:03:53,670 --> 00:03:55,670
So you won't work with us for Round Two?

91
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:57,000
Just make it clear now...

92
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,510
But the important thing is,

93
00:03:59,010 --> 00:04:01,180
our points...
As soon as we form an alliance,

94
00:04:01,180 --> 00:04:03,810
we can toss the points around among us
and win 1st and 2nd places.

95
00:04:05,510 --> 00:04:08,080
We were almost 100 percent certain...

96
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:10,420
that we'd win Rounds 1 and 2.

97
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:14,460
But now, the deal I made with Team P1
is holding us back.

98
00:04:15,990 --> 00:04:18,290
- What's the problem?
- What he said just now is,

99
00:04:18,290 --> 00:04:20,960
until Round Two, they'll work with Team C.

100
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:22,900
- So we need to...
- Just ignore it.

101
00:04:22,900 --> 00:04:24,370
- go with it.
- Sang Min.

102
00:04:24,370 --> 00:04:26,500
- The point...
- What I want to say is,

103
00:04:26,670 --> 00:04:28,400
what good comes out of
working with Team C now?

104
00:04:28,940 --> 00:04:31,240
Either your team or mine must win.

105
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:33,010
Once either one of the team
securely places first,

106
00:04:33,010 --> 00:04:34,980
that team can help the other team
become second place.

107
00:04:35,780 --> 00:04:37,580
Or if that bothers you,

108
00:04:37,580 --> 00:04:40,410
you can say you don't have a Mate,
get ten points,

109
00:04:40,410 --> 00:04:42,480
and then give us ten points
in the next round.

110
00:04:43,650 --> 00:04:45,890
You guys can take the zero win points.

111
00:04:46,420 --> 00:04:49,660
Think about which team and what strategies
are for the best.

112
00:04:50,690 --> 00:04:54,060
That means
Team P3 gets 10 points to itself.

113
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:55,560
We get in the solo lead.

114
00:04:55,730 --> 00:05:00,130
They're making the situation
so favorable for us?

115
00:05:00,570 --> 00:05:02,100
Should we go with zero wins this round?

116
00:05:02,100 --> 00:05:03,670
- Then who is our Mate?
- We should.

117
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:05,010
- Team P1?
- Yes.

118
00:05:05,010 --> 00:05:06,740
- That means we're betraying Team C.
- Three... Team C.

119
00:05:06,840 --> 00:05:07,940
We're betraying Team C.

120
00:05:07,940 --> 00:05:10,040
Betray them. Take the zero win points.

121
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:13,510
Well...

122
00:05:14,780 --> 00:05:16,020
It's a survival show, after all.

123
00:05:16,020 --> 00:05:18,820
It's not like we get
a national loyalty award or something.

124
00:05:18,820 --> 00:05:21,290
"You did not betray anyone
on the survival show, hence the award."

125
00:05:21,290 --> 00:05:22,390
There's no such thing.

126
00:05:22,790 --> 00:05:25,490
The alliance with Team C was short-term.

127
00:05:25,490 --> 00:05:27,400
"Let's exchange the zero win strategy."

128
00:05:27,630 --> 00:05:30,730
But Team P1 wanted to work together
until the end.

129
00:05:31,070 --> 00:05:33,430
"Whichever team wins the game
should help the other team."

130
00:05:33,770 --> 00:05:36,000
This alliance looks at the bigger picture.

131
00:05:36,140 --> 00:05:39,110
I was on the fence too.
You try to judge...

132
00:05:39,310 --> 00:05:41,880
which is better.

133
00:05:42,510 --> 00:05:45,750
But no matter how hard I think about it,
the right choice is to betray.

134
00:05:45,750 --> 00:05:48,320
The reason is clear.

135
00:05:48,550 --> 00:05:52,090
Our lives, our survivals come first.

136
00:05:52,190 --> 00:05:55,690
I don't think morality and promise
should come first.

137
00:05:55,790 --> 00:05:58,060
At least on Bloody Game X.

138
00:05:58,260 --> 00:06:00,260
So I made the decision...

139
00:06:00,260 --> 00:06:01,400
to abandon Team C...

140
00:06:02,330 --> 00:06:03,430
and work with Team P1.

141
00:06:03,530 --> 00:06:05,600
- I'll go with this, then.
- Okay.

142
00:06:05,870 --> 00:06:07,800
- There's only one minute left.
- Hurry up.

143
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:09,570
(Team C's room, Team P1's room)

144
00:06:09,570 --> 00:06:10,570
Seong Beom.

145
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:13,140
How did it go?

146
00:06:13,140 --> 00:06:16,610
(Team C's room, Team P1's room)

147
00:06:16,840 --> 00:06:19,350
Wait. Are we working with that team?

148
00:06:19,510 --> 00:06:20,820
- We...
- Are we working with Team P1?

149
00:06:20,820 --> 00:06:22,880
The strategy is to go with zero wins
without a Mate.

150
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:24,250
- No Mate, zero wins.
- We...

151
00:06:24,590 --> 00:06:27,590
Team P1 wants to form
a long-term alliance with us.

152
00:06:27,590 --> 00:06:28,790
The problem is,

153
00:06:28,790 --> 00:06:30,120
will Team P2 not go for 0 win?

154
00:06:30,220 --> 00:06:31,230
- No.
- They won't.

155
00:06:31,230 --> 00:06:32,390
- They won't?
- They won't.

156
00:06:32,460 --> 00:06:33,560
Then what should I do?

157
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:35,260
- This.
- If yellow hasn't been used...

158
00:06:35,260 --> 00:06:37,060
- The strategy meeting session is over.
- Bring it.

159
00:06:37,060 --> 00:06:38,200
So what should I do?

160
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:40,330
- The Round Two players of each team,
- What now? We must decide.

161
00:06:40,330 --> 00:06:41,470
- Bet on zero wins by yourself.
- bring the card of your choice...

162
00:06:41,470 --> 00:06:43,300
- If you can do that, do it now.
- and register it.

163
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:44,940
- Bet on zero wins by myself?
- Then gather at the main hall.

164
00:06:44,940 --> 00:06:45,940
Yes, zero wins, no Mate.

165
00:06:45,940 --> 00:06:47,710
We're going to betray Team C.

166
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:49,210
We're going to betray them?

167
00:06:49,310 --> 00:06:50,480
- We...
- That happened.

168
00:06:50,780 --> 00:06:52,580
If we bet on zero wins...

169
00:06:53,110 --> 00:06:55,820
We don't get much
from working with Team P1.

170
00:06:55,820 --> 00:06:57,550
First, we have to betray Team C.

171
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:59,890
And Team P1 is already in 1st place.

172
00:07:00,050 --> 00:07:01,360
What's the use of working with them?

173
00:07:01,690 --> 00:07:03,990
- We'll collaborate with Team P1.
- I need to go and tell them.

174
00:07:04,130 --> 00:07:05,390
- Five, six... Where did seven go?
- Let's do it this way.

175
00:07:05,390 --> 00:07:06,630
- Where did seven go?
- Is it not there?

176
00:07:06,630 --> 00:07:08,360
We didn't have enough time to strategize,

177
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:11,530
we used up all the time available,
and we didn't even plan our deck.

178
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:14,440
What were those three doing
without even forming the deck?

179
00:07:14,440 --> 00:07:16,600
I got so annoyed.

180
00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:19,070
You need to go.
There's no time to talk. Go.

181
00:07:25,810 --> 00:07:28,980
(Xitsuh runs to Team P1's room.)

182
00:07:30,580 --> 00:07:32,990
You okay with us going No Mate?
We're going to betray Team C.

183
00:07:32,990 --> 00:07:35,520
Or why don't you go with Mate
all the way until the end?

184
00:07:35,690 --> 00:07:37,290
- Mate all the way? Two of us?
- Yes.

185
00:07:37,630 --> 00:07:38,760
They changed their words.

186
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:40,930
We need to play the game,
there's no time left.

187
00:07:41,260 --> 00:07:43,500
But they changed from a No-Mate strategy
to a Mate strategy...

188
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:44,500
as if they had been waiting for it.

189
00:07:44,500 --> 00:07:46,000
"Become our Mate
and give us five points too."

190
00:07:46,170 --> 00:07:47,370
To make it look like
we didn't betray them,

191
00:07:47,370 --> 00:07:49,240
it'd be best for us to go with No Mate.

192
00:07:49,270 --> 00:07:51,170
That would overcomplicate things.

193
00:07:51,940 --> 00:07:53,170
Put the cards together quickly.

194
00:07:53,170 --> 00:07:54,710
- Then 1 to 7?
- Let's just do it.

195
00:07:54,710 --> 00:07:56,110
- One...
- One to seven.

196
00:07:56,110 --> 00:07:58,050
- It would overcomplicate things.
- Then we...

197
00:07:58,050 --> 00:08:00,950
Did they make use of
how we didn't have much time?

198
00:08:00,950 --> 00:08:03,080
How did No Mate suddenly turn into Mate?

199
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:05,450
I didn't feel all that great.

200
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:12,090
(Team P3's room, Team C's room)

201
00:08:14,060 --> 00:08:15,060
They...

202
00:08:15,860 --> 00:08:17,800
- I spread them out.
- Give me one high number.

203
00:08:17,930 --> 00:08:19,570
Yellow 16. No, Yellow 15.

204
00:08:19,570 --> 00:08:22,570
(Team P3's room)

205
00:08:25,470 --> 00:08:26,640
The time...

206
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:28,280
Shouldn't you have registered it
a while ago?

207
00:08:32,380 --> 00:08:33,510
Exactly.

208
00:08:40,050 --> 00:08:41,090
We're screwed.

209
00:08:42,260 --> 00:08:44,660
It's completely messed up
from the first day.

210
00:08:46,390 --> 00:08:47,430
Goodness.

211
00:08:47,860 --> 00:08:49,300
The situation is so frustrating,

212
00:08:49,300 --> 00:08:51,500
and the fact that I was in the center
of it made it all the more frustrating.

213
00:08:54,470 --> 00:08:55,940
So what did Tae Gyun say?

214
00:08:59,140 --> 00:09:00,140
We're doomed.

215
00:09:00,940 --> 00:09:02,140
He didn't take the dictator card.

216
00:09:03,580 --> 00:09:05,050
For this round? No.

217
00:09:05,810 --> 00:09:07,280
We didn't have enough time
to strategize properly.

218
00:09:07,280 --> 00:09:08,520
We have to forgo this round.

219
00:09:11,750 --> 00:09:14,120
(Round 2 card exchange,
Master, Heo Seong Beom)

220
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:17,190
Heo Seong Beom has become the master
by betting on zero wins.

221
00:09:17,890 --> 00:09:20,430
Yellow is the master color of this round.

222
00:09:21,030 --> 00:09:22,860
Please submit the card you want to give...

223
00:09:22,860 --> 00:09:24,300
to the Master.

224
00:09:26,630 --> 00:09:28,770
(Jeong Keun Woo submits red 5.)

225
00:09:28,940 --> 00:09:31,840
(Hyun Sung Joo submits yellow 8.)

226
00:09:45,620 --> 00:09:46,850
The situation was dire,

227
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:49,760
but there was one last hope
which my team could win.

228
00:09:50,020 --> 00:09:52,560
I brought the dictator card,
which is a very good card.

229
00:09:53,030 --> 00:09:55,030
The problem is, Seong Beom also knows...

230
00:09:55,300 --> 00:09:57,900
that I have the dictator card with me.

231
00:09:58,030 --> 00:09:59,800
Because he told me to bring it.

232
00:10:00,130 --> 00:10:02,640
So I had to decide whether to give
the dictator card to him or not.

233
00:10:02,970 --> 00:10:05,010
It was a very important moment.

234
00:10:05,570 --> 00:10:07,370
There were eight possible outcomes.

235
00:10:07,780 --> 00:10:10,040
If I were to give the dictator card
to Seong Beom,

236
00:10:10,380 --> 00:10:13,580
to counter it,
you must have the assassin card.

237
00:10:13,810 --> 00:10:16,220
Seong Beom having brought
the assassin card,

238
00:10:16,450 --> 00:10:18,250
Keun Woo having brought the assassin card,

239
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:21,660
me giving the dictator card to Seong Beom,
or not giving it to him,

240
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:24,860
Sung Joo giving the dictator card
to Seong Beom,

241
00:10:25,190 --> 00:10:26,490
or not giving it to him
because he didn't bring one.

242
00:10:26,490 --> 00:10:29,730
Two by two by two,
so eight possibilities in total.

243
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:32,470
Out of them,
five possibilities mean we lose.

244
00:10:32,630 --> 00:10:34,070
Two possibilities mean we win.

245
00:10:34,470 --> 00:10:37,440
One possibility gives us
a slight chance to win.

246
00:10:37,540 --> 00:10:39,670
I had to decide if I wanted
to hand over the dictator card.

247
00:10:46,250 --> 00:10:49,150
(Kang Ji Hoo submits an unrevealed card.)

248
00:10:56,660 --> 00:10:58,460
All cards have been exchanged.

249
00:10:58,830 --> 00:11:01,400
(Heo Seong Beom gets red 5,
yellow 8, and an unrevealed card.)

250
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:03,830
Heo Seong Beom,
do you wish to name a Mate?

251
00:11:04,530 --> 00:11:06,570
Yes. I choose 15.

252
00:11:07,070 --> 00:11:08,570
The player who submits card 15...

253
00:11:08,570 --> 00:11:10,740
will become the Mate.

254
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:12,210
(Jeong Keun Woo, Hyun Sung Joo,
Kang Ji Hoo, Heo Seong Beom)

255
00:11:12,210 --> 00:11:14,170
Card five in red has been submitted.

256
00:11:14,810 --> 00:11:16,940
Jeong Keun Woo, please submit your card.

257
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:22,180
You need to submit 15.

258
00:11:32,060 --> 00:11:33,190
(Jeong Keun Woo, yellow 15)

259
00:11:33,190 --> 00:11:35,630
Jeong Keun Woo has submitted card 15.

260
00:11:35,630 --> 00:11:36,930
You have become his Mate.

261
00:11:38,830 --> 00:11:39,870
I see.

262
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:43,900
Card seven in red has been submitted.

263
00:11:43,900 --> 00:11:45,540
(Jeong Keun Woo, yellow 15,
Hyun Sung Joo, red 7)

264
00:11:45,540 --> 00:11:47,140
(Heo Seong Beom, red 5)

265
00:11:51,180 --> 00:11:53,050
Card six in red has been submitted.

266
00:11:53,250 --> 00:11:55,580
Jeong Keun Woo has won Set One.

267
00:12:00,390 --> 00:12:03,720
The second set will start
with Jeong Keun Woo.

268
00:12:05,460 --> 00:12:06,530
Anything.

269
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:10,560
They did something dirty again.

270
00:12:12,270 --> 00:12:14,270
Card 12 in yellow has been submitted.

271
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:17,640
What should we do?

272
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:25,680
Team P1 and P3 came up with
a zero-win strategy.

273
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:29,350
They brought a perfectly planned puzzle.

274
00:12:29,520 --> 00:12:30,620
It's a complete betrayal.

275
00:12:30,620 --> 00:12:33,850
They do one thing in front of me
and then go do something else behind me.

276
00:12:33,850 --> 00:12:35,320
It's a complete betrayal.

277
00:12:35,490 --> 00:12:37,190
I was very disappointed in Team P1.

278
00:12:38,290 --> 00:12:40,130
Card seven in yellow has been submitted.

279
00:12:40,130 --> 00:12:43,160
(Hyun Sung Joo, yellow 7)

280
00:12:46,670 --> 00:12:49,000
Wouldn't there be something I could do?

281
00:12:49,140 --> 00:12:51,940
Even 0.1 percent of chance?

282
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:06,620
Card seven in yellow has been submitted.

283
00:13:07,420 --> 00:13:09,490
Heo Seong Beom, please submit your card.

284
00:13:09,490 --> 00:13:12,830
(Kang Ji Hoo, yellow 7)

285
00:13:12,830 --> 00:13:13,830
(Heo Seong Beom, yellow 8)

286
00:13:13,830 --> 00:13:15,630
Card eight in yellow has been submitted.

287
00:13:16,100 --> 00:13:18,400
Jeong Keun Woo has won Set Two.

288
00:13:21,070 --> 00:13:24,740
Team P3 wouldn't have figured out
the cards Team P2 has.

289
00:13:25,110 --> 00:13:27,110
But they know my team's cards
because we planned them together.

290
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:28,740
So there was nothing I could do.

291
00:13:29,380 --> 00:13:30,910
(Set 3 starts.)

292
00:13:30,910 --> 00:13:33,480
Jeong Keun Woo has submitted
card 11 in yellow.

293
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:36,680
(Jeong Keun Woo, yellow 11)

294
00:13:36,680 --> 00:13:39,320
Hyun Sung Joo has submitted
card 12 in blue.

295
00:13:39,420 --> 00:13:42,290
Kang Ji Hoo has submitted card 12 in blue.

296
00:13:42,290 --> 00:13:44,890
Heo Seong Beom has submitted
card five in red.

297
00:13:45,260 --> 00:13:47,530
Jeong Keun Woo has won Set Three.

298
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:50,300
Jeong Keun Woo has won Set Four.

299
00:13:53,270 --> 00:13:55,500
Jeong Keun Woo has won Set Five.

300
00:14:00,940 --> 00:14:02,340
What did Tae Gyun say?

301
00:14:05,080 --> 00:14:07,850
It turned out to look like
we've betrayed you.

302
00:14:08,420 --> 00:14:09,920
The situation has become tangled up.

303
00:14:09,920 --> 00:14:12,620
What do you get out of this?

304
00:14:13,320 --> 00:14:15,460
- Nothing.
- They'd buy us an extra vote ticket...

305
00:14:15,460 --> 00:14:16,790
no matter what happens.

306
00:14:16,790 --> 00:14:18,460
Regardless, one of you has to go.

307
00:14:18,790 --> 00:14:20,690
Each team will have
an elimination candidate.

308
00:14:20,690 --> 00:14:22,700
- Will you only choose one?
- No, we don't know that.

309
00:14:22,700 --> 00:14:23,860
We have no information on that.

310
00:14:23,860 --> 00:14:25,230
Whether the whole team becomes
the elimination candidate...

311
00:14:25,230 --> 00:14:26,230
- Didn't you hear?
- No.

312
00:14:26,230 --> 00:14:27,900
- It's one person per team.
- One person per team.

313
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:29,240
- What? They announced it?
- How did he explain it?

314
00:14:29,240 --> 00:14:30,670
It was announced earlier.

315
00:14:30,670 --> 00:14:32,810
- Who?
- So it's meaningless unless you win.

316
00:14:32,810 --> 00:14:34,610
That's why I don't get...

317
00:14:34,610 --> 00:14:36,140
- why you're doing this.
- No wonder I didn't get what you said.

318
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:37,740
Why didn't any of us hear this?

319
00:14:37,740 --> 00:14:39,480
- We all heard it!
- Everyone heard it!

320
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:41,380
- So it's meaningless unless you win.
- Yes.

321
00:14:41,380 --> 00:14:42,720
That's why I kept saying it.

322
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:44,420
I didn't get it since then.

323
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:48,620
They said they'd buy
the extra vote ticket...

324
00:14:48,620 --> 00:14:50,120
for whichever team that doesn't win.

325
00:14:50,420 --> 00:14:52,290
While you were gone, we discussed...

326
00:14:52,290 --> 00:14:54,330
that we should make one of the teams win.

327
00:14:54,490 --> 00:14:56,160
- Out of Team P1 and us? Why?
- Yes.

328
00:14:56,360 --> 00:14:58,530
The winning team will save the other team
by using the extra vote ticket.

329
00:14:58,530 --> 00:15:00,600
They have a lot of money, and we don't.

330
00:15:01,240 --> 00:15:05,370
This game is meaningless unless you win.

331
00:15:05,370 --> 00:15:08,040
So why did they make such a promise?

332
00:15:08,580 --> 00:15:13,350
They believed the winning team
could save one team.

333
00:15:13,710 --> 00:15:15,050
That brought upon another confusion.

334
00:15:16,580 --> 00:15:18,420
I only heard this from the announcement.

335
00:15:18,420 --> 00:15:20,050
"You could become
the elimination candidate."

336
00:15:20,050 --> 00:15:21,360
- No.
- They didn't say that.

337
00:15:21,360 --> 00:15:23,090
We understood it completely differently.

338
00:15:23,620 --> 00:15:25,460
If it's confirmed that every team...

339
00:15:25,460 --> 00:15:27,130
except the winning team
will have one elimination candidate,

340
00:15:27,130 --> 00:15:28,530
there's no reason
to help the other team win.

341
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:30,000
They can't help us anyway.

342
00:15:30,260 --> 00:15:31,570
We should win, then.

343
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:33,270
What did Jin Ho and I hear?

344
00:15:33,270 --> 00:15:34,500
Were we possessed by a ghost?

345
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:36,170
What is right?

346
00:15:36,870 --> 00:15:38,270
Team P1 understood it wrongly too?

347
00:15:38,510 --> 00:15:40,410
They didn't correct us when we said that.

348
00:15:40,740 --> 00:15:42,840
I don't think
Team P1 understood it wrongly.

349
00:15:42,980 --> 00:15:43,980
Don't you think so too?

350
00:15:44,510 --> 00:15:47,810
In that case,
I can't sit back and watch Team P1 win.

351
00:15:48,580 --> 00:15:49,920
- For now, okay.
- Yes, sir.

352
00:15:53,950 --> 00:15:54,960
Jerks.

353
00:15:56,960 --> 00:15:58,090
Total jerks.

354
00:15:58,090 --> 00:16:00,990
(Lee Sang Min, Team P1)

355
00:16:06,070 --> 00:16:08,240
Xitsuh and You Hyun were talking.

356
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:09,670
That means they've formed an alliance.

357
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,470
They said we should get ten points
by having No Mate,

358
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:13,010
so we strategized accordingly,

359
00:16:13,010 --> 00:16:15,480
and they said, "Let's become Mate with us.
It'd be safer that way."

360
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:16,580
Who said that?

361
00:16:16,580 --> 00:16:18,380
Sang Min and Tae Gyun. All of them.

362
00:16:18,380 --> 00:16:20,110
- When we were planning...
- Really?

363
00:16:20,110 --> 00:16:21,480
our cards here...

364
00:16:25,820 --> 00:16:28,290
We were going to do
the zero-win, No-Mate strategy,

365
00:16:28,290 --> 00:16:29,860
but you said no and changed the plan?

366
00:16:30,920 --> 00:16:32,290
(Flustered)

367
00:16:32,290 --> 00:16:33,590
We didn't say no.

368
00:16:33,990 --> 00:16:36,400
We were going to go with zero-win, No-Mate
until you changed your word.

369
00:16:36,930 --> 00:16:40,000
What I wanted to say was,
it's best to prioritize...

370
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:41,870
who to betray first.

371
00:16:42,140 --> 00:16:45,070
Nothing has changed from what we discussed
except one.

372
00:16:45,070 --> 00:16:47,840
We talked about how
the elimination candidates are decided.

373
00:16:47,940 --> 00:16:49,140
What we initially discussed was...

374
00:16:49,140 --> 00:16:51,010
that the winning team would be given
some kind of authority...

375
00:16:51,010 --> 00:16:52,380
- to help another team,
- Yes.

376
00:16:52,380 --> 00:16:53,950
- so we should help each other.
- Definitely.

377
00:16:54,110 --> 00:16:56,380
But one elimination candidate is chosen...

378
00:16:56,550 --> 00:16:58,650
from the teams
which placed 2nd, 3rd, and 4th.

379
00:16:58,650 --> 00:16:59,820
That's it.

380
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:01,490
- Who said that?
- This...

381
00:17:01,490 --> 00:17:03,420
They said, "One will be decided
from each team."

382
00:17:03,420 --> 00:17:04,660
Everyone except us knows.

383
00:17:04,890 --> 00:17:08,030
From the teams except the winning team,

384
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:10,060
someone will be eliminated.

385
00:17:10,260 --> 00:17:11,830
- No, each team...
- I heard they'll become the candidate.

386
00:17:11,830 --> 00:17:13,800
No, they said each team will have...

387
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:15,300
one elimination candidate.

388
00:17:15,300 --> 00:17:16,570
The exact phrase was,

389
00:17:16,770 --> 00:17:19,410
"All the teams except the winning team
can become the elimination candidate."

390
00:17:19,410 --> 00:17:20,410
- No!
- This is it.

391
00:17:20,410 --> 00:17:21,980
- One from each team...
- That was the exact phrase.

392
00:17:21,980 --> 00:17:23,180
- Goodness.
- This is it.

393
00:17:23,340 --> 00:17:25,110
- One from each team.
- No.

394
00:17:25,110 --> 00:17:27,280
That was what I heard too, so we...

395
00:17:27,410 --> 00:17:30,250
I honestly thought...

396
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:34,390
Team P1 was using my team.

397
00:17:34,390 --> 00:17:37,090
Because currently, Team P1...

398
00:17:37,290 --> 00:17:40,490
has a very high chance to win.

399
00:17:40,790 --> 00:17:44,800
Moreover, in Round 2,
when we only had 1 minute left,

400
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:48,440
they changed the strategy
so that they'd score points too.

401
00:17:49,040 --> 00:17:54,010
And in the midst of that,
he kept talking about losers.

402
00:17:54,540 --> 00:17:56,040
"He's trying to shake us up."

403
00:17:56,040 --> 00:18:00,080
"And he wants to ruin our strategy."

404
00:18:00,080 --> 00:18:01,550
That's what I felt.

405
00:18:03,150 --> 00:18:06,490
The eighth set will start
with Jeong Keun Woo.

406
00:18:19,500 --> 00:18:20,970
(Assassin card)

407
00:18:20,970 --> 00:18:22,600
The assassin card has been submitted.

408
00:18:24,770 --> 00:18:27,470
I didn't expect Team P1
to bring the assassin card.

409
00:18:27,570 --> 00:18:28,910
But he did.

410
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:31,110
Had I known he'd brought it,

411
00:18:31,580 --> 00:18:33,480
I wouldn't have submitted
the dictator card.

412
00:18:33,580 --> 00:18:35,380
In that case, Keun Woo would lose once...

413
00:18:35,380 --> 00:18:36,880
because of the assassin card.

414
00:18:36,880 --> 00:18:38,420
Sung Joo or I would have the chance,

415
00:18:38,590 --> 00:18:40,850
and there was a slight possibility
of us winning...

416
00:18:40,850 --> 00:18:42,190
against Seong Beom.

417
00:18:42,690 --> 00:18:44,020
(During the card exchange,)

418
00:18:44,020 --> 00:18:45,230
(Ji Hoo handed over
the dictator card to Seong Beom.)

419
00:18:46,360 --> 00:18:49,130
Hyun Sung Joo has submitted
card four in red.

420
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:53,200
Kang Ji Hoo has submitted card 16 in blue.

421
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:55,170
(Jeong Keun Woo, assassin card)

422
00:18:55,170 --> 00:18:57,100
(Hyun Sung Joo, red 4,
Kang Ji Hoo, blue 16)

423
00:18:57,100 --> 00:18:59,470
(Heo Seong Beom, dictator card)

424
00:18:59,470 --> 00:19:01,040
The dictator card has been submitted.

425
00:19:01,040 --> 00:19:04,850
(Jeong Keun Woo, assassin card)

426
00:19:04,850 --> 00:19:06,980
Jeong Keun Woo has won Set Eight.

427
00:19:07,980 --> 00:19:11,490
You and your Mate Team P1
each get 5 points.

428
00:19:11,790 --> 00:19:14,790
Round Two has ended.
Please leave the main hall.

429
00:19:28,270 --> 00:19:30,270
Round Three has started.

430
00:19:30,870 --> 00:19:32,470
After 20 minutes of strategy meeting,

431
00:19:32,670 --> 00:19:35,080
Round Three card battle will commence.

432
00:19:39,650 --> 00:19:40,680
You're back already?

433
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:42,020
Because the mister here betrayed us.

434
00:19:42,420 --> 00:19:43,680
- Yes.
- Yes, he betrayed us.

435
00:19:43,680 --> 00:19:44,820
I heard about it.

436
00:19:45,050 --> 00:19:46,550
I really meant it...

437
00:19:46,550 --> 00:19:48,360
when I told you about the strategy here.

438
00:19:48,360 --> 00:19:50,220
- I was set on going for six wins,
- When did it change?

439
00:19:50,220 --> 00:19:52,160
but when I went back...
After the time was up,

440
00:19:52,160 --> 00:19:54,830
and we said, "There's one minute left,
so let's decide on this."

441
00:19:55,230 --> 00:19:56,530
But when I went back, they said
we were teaming up with Team P1.

442
00:19:56,530 --> 00:19:58,570
It was 3 of them against 1,
so I couldn't persuade them.

443
00:19:58,570 --> 00:19:59,630
This...

444
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:01,940
- But now...
- It sounds like a lie.

445
00:20:03,740 --> 00:20:05,440
He said he wanted to work with us,

446
00:20:05,570 --> 00:20:07,870
but the situation didn't allow it.

447
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:10,340
But I think he's definitely lying.

448
00:20:10,710 --> 00:20:13,680
It's a game where you betray,
and betrayal is normal.

449
00:20:14,010 --> 00:20:15,580
So I thought I wouldn't feel upset
if someone betrayed me.

450
00:20:16,350 --> 00:20:17,350
But...

451
00:20:18,650 --> 00:20:19,720
I felt so upset.

452
00:20:22,020 --> 00:20:25,290
(Another person who is upset)

453
00:20:25,290 --> 00:20:26,360
- Hey.
- Welcome back.

454
00:20:27,060 --> 00:20:28,200
You were here.

455
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:32,670
Teams P1 and P3 planned everything.

456
00:20:33,300 --> 00:20:34,970
- Okay.
- They became Mates from the start?

457
00:20:35,340 --> 00:20:36,340
Yes.

458
00:20:36,470 --> 00:20:37,870
Shall I go and ask?

459
00:20:39,870 --> 00:20:42,780
But they don't have a long-term strategy.

460
00:20:43,140 --> 00:20:44,580
Who'd team up with Team P1 now?

461
00:20:47,250 --> 00:20:49,850
(Lee Jin Hyeong comes
to talk with Team P1.)

462
00:20:55,190 --> 00:20:56,260
So you enjoyed the points?

463
00:20:56,260 --> 00:20:57,960
I'm actually quite confused too.

464
00:20:58,360 --> 00:21:00,930
Within my team itself,
there are differing opinions.

465
00:21:00,930 --> 00:21:02,360
- But...
- Because...

466
00:21:02,360 --> 00:21:03,560
Give me just three minutes.

467
00:21:03,560 --> 00:21:04,700
Okay. I'll wait here.

468
00:21:04,700 --> 00:21:06,430
After talking with you...

469
00:21:06,430 --> 00:21:08,540
and playing Running Mate,
I came back here.

470
00:21:08,540 --> 00:21:11,940
but while we were playing the game,
those remaining here...

471
00:21:11,940 --> 00:21:14,540
For Lee Sang Min and Park Ji Min,

472
00:21:14,540 --> 00:21:16,280
I understand why they'd do that.

473
00:21:16,280 --> 00:21:19,050
- But we decided to work together,
- Okay.

474
00:21:19,050 --> 00:21:20,680
- but you got five points first.
- Okay.

475
00:21:20,680 --> 00:21:23,180
- You should compensate us for it.
- Okay.

476
00:21:23,180 --> 00:21:24,550
- I'll talk to her about it.
- Okay.

477
00:21:33,390 --> 00:21:35,760
They're snakes.

478
00:21:46,510 --> 00:21:47,640
You can betray.

479
00:21:48,010 --> 00:21:50,080
I get that you want more points.

480
00:21:50,380 --> 00:21:52,710
But we agreed to form an alliance.

481
00:21:53,010 --> 00:21:54,980
I thought
building a solid basis for trust...

482
00:21:54,980 --> 00:21:58,120
was much more important
than winning a game.

483
00:22:03,660 --> 00:22:05,260
What is your strategy?

484
00:22:06,290 --> 00:22:07,990
It's the same.
We'll win by betting on zero wins.

485
00:22:07,990 --> 00:22:09,360
What do we get out of it?

486
00:22:10,430 --> 00:22:12,370
But if we don't do that,
it doesn't benefit us.

487
00:22:12,370 --> 00:22:14,530
- But...
- But we have no reason to help you.

488
00:22:15,170 --> 00:22:16,340
We're in first place.

489
00:22:16,700 --> 00:22:18,870
That really pissed me off.

490
00:22:19,370 --> 00:22:21,370
They were like, "What do we get..."

491
00:22:21,510 --> 00:22:23,410
"from letting you score points?"

492
00:22:23,440 --> 00:22:27,110
We played Round 1 to get 10 points,

493
00:22:27,110 --> 00:22:29,150
but you got five points in the end.

494
00:22:29,150 --> 00:22:31,890
But I could make two choices then.

495
00:22:31,890 --> 00:22:33,650
Each team except Team P1 gets 3 points,

496
00:22:33,650 --> 00:22:34,650
- or we get five points each.
- But...

497
00:22:34,650 --> 00:22:36,220
And I chose your team.

498
00:22:36,220 --> 00:22:38,960
It wasn't that you could win ten points
for certain in that round.

499
00:22:38,960 --> 00:22:41,030
But... Yes, well,

500
00:22:41,030 --> 00:22:42,760
if we do this for you,
you should give us something in return.

501
00:22:43,360 --> 00:22:46,670
- I'm not talking about morality here.
- Hold on.

502
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:49,270
- What I'm saying is...
- We promised to work together,

503
00:22:49,270 --> 00:22:51,440
- and we did. Right?
- Right.

504
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:52,910
So...

505
00:22:53,010 --> 00:22:55,080
what I want to say is,

506
00:22:55,080 --> 00:22:58,110
I talked to you about it
because I wanted to team up with you.

507
00:22:58,140 --> 00:23:01,450
And just looking at Round One alone,

508
00:23:01,880 --> 00:23:05,290
it wasn't a bad deal for Team P2.

509
00:23:06,820 --> 00:23:08,020
What happened?

510
00:23:09,420 --> 00:23:12,190
Do you guys discuss this with Jin Hyeong?

511
00:23:12,790 --> 00:23:13,990
- Yes.
- Or is it just his own idea?

512
00:23:13,990 --> 00:23:15,660
- He discussed it with us.
- Right?

513
00:23:15,660 --> 00:23:17,660
He came to our room just now.

514
00:23:17,660 --> 00:23:18,830
- Tae Gyun?
- Yes.

515
00:23:18,830 --> 00:23:21,370
- To become the Mate together.
- But I...

516
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:24,400
I didn't hear anything about
forming an alliance with Team P2.

517
00:23:24,440 --> 00:23:25,870
- Really?
- What did she say?

518
00:23:25,870 --> 00:23:29,780
She never heard anything about
forming an alliance with Team P2.

519
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:33,110
- So...
- No, Tae Gyun...

520
00:23:33,350 --> 00:23:35,250
deceived us for the previous round.

521
00:23:35,250 --> 00:23:36,650
He 100 percent did.

522
00:23:36,650 --> 00:23:37,680
That's true.

523
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:39,120
- He stabbed us in the back.
- He can do that,

524
00:23:39,120 --> 00:23:40,490
- and he did.
- He can do that, but...

525
00:23:40,490 --> 00:23:42,460
After hearing our strategy,

526
00:23:42,460 --> 00:23:44,260
they came up with their strategy.

527
00:23:44,260 --> 00:23:46,360
- It was a perfect counter-strategy.
- Yes.

528
00:23:46,560 --> 00:23:48,660
They asked us in detail...

529
00:23:48,660 --> 00:23:50,630
what we'd do in this situation.

530
00:23:51,130 --> 00:23:53,570
Ji Min acts like...

531
00:23:53,570 --> 00:23:55,270
it's none of her business.

532
00:23:55,370 --> 00:23:57,300
"We didn't tell him to screw you over."

533
00:23:57,300 --> 00:23:59,770
"What happened?" That's what she's doing.

534
00:23:59,770 --> 00:24:02,510
"We won't team up with them again
in this game."

535
00:24:02,510 --> 00:24:04,580
"We must stop them from winning."

536
00:24:04,580 --> 00:24:05,910
That was the first thought
that came to my mind.

537
00:24:05,910 --> 00:24:07,210
We must punish them...

538
00:24:07,850 --> 00:24:10,350
for playing with such terrible manners
from the first game.

539
00:24:12,020 --> 00:24:13,190
Yes.

540
00:24:13,190 --> 00:24:14,350
Can I go in?

541
00:24:14,350 --> 00:24:15,660
Yes. Who is it?

542
00:24:16,090 --> 00:24:17,760
- Hello.
- Come in.

543
00:24:17,760 --> 00:24:20,460
(Lee Tae Gyun visits Team P2's room.)

544
00:24:20,530 --> 00:24:23,830
- I came to clear the misunderstanding.
- Yes.

545
00:24:24,460 --> 00:24:26,530
I'm not the leader,

546
00:24:26,530 --> 00:24:28,640
although I come up with strategies.

547
00:24:28,640 --> 00:24:31,670
- But since this is a team game,
- Yes.

548
00:24:31,670 --> 00:24:33,040
while I'm gone...

549
00:24:33,040 --> 00:24:34,940
- Things have already happened.
- Yes, so...

550
00:24:34,940 --> 00:24:37,340
I get how you'd feel...

551
00:24:37,340 --> 00:24:39,180
about it.

552
00:24:39,180 --> 00:24:42,050
I do understand
how you might misunderstand the situation.

553
00:24:42,180 --> 00:24:44,050
Tae Gyun came up to say...

554
00:24:44,050 --> 00:24:45,520
it was a misunderstanding.

555
00:24:45,520 --> 00:24:47,420
Everyone on Team P1 said different things.

556
00:24:47,750 --> 00:24:49,360
On survival shows,

557
00:24:49,360 --> 00:24:51,590
betrayal and other things are allowed,

558
00:24:51,620 --> 00:24:53,430
but doing this right on the first day?

559
00:24:53,530 --> 00:24:55,960
Actually, betraying others
and securing points for their team...

560
00:24:55,960 --> 00:24:58,770
could be more beneficial
than keeping the alliance intact.

561
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:00,670
If you're looking for short-term benefits,
that is.

562
00:25:00,670 --> 00:25:02,500
But when you look at the game long-term,

563
00:25:02,500 --> 00:25:04,540
will it still benefit them?

564
00:25:04,540 --> 00:25:05,710
Nobody knows.

565
00:25:05,710 --> 00:25:07,840
And we're not fools.

566
00:25:07,870 --> 00:25:08,910
When we get betrayed,

567
00:25:08,910 --> 00:25:10,210
we pay it back.

568
00:25:11,980 --> 00:25:14,380
(Team P1's room)

569
00:25:14,380 --> 00:25:16,580
Why is Jin Hyeong coming to us?

570
00:25:16,580 --> 00:25:19,550
He doesn't think we've betrayed them yet.

571
00:25:20,120 --> 00:25:21,450
He thinks we're on the same boat.

572
00:25:21,590 --> 00:25:23,090
Just ignore him.

573
00:25:23,390 --> 00:25:25,830
Just say we can't do it.

574
00:25:25,830 --> 00:25:28,030
What I agreed with Jin Hyeong was...

575
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:29,830
that we should split the points
for Round One,

576
00:25:29,830 --> 00:25:31,060
and that if things look good,

577
00:25:31,230 --> 00:25:34,370
we could work together moving forward.

578
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:37,470
I don't think that meant
we should form an alliance...

579
00:25:37,470 --> 00:25:39,270
until the end.

580
00:25:39,610 --> 00:25:40,810
Anyway,

581
00:25:40,810 --> 00:25:43,810
we must choose one side.

582
00:25:43,810 --> 00:25:45,650
I should follow Sang Min's decision.

583
00:25:45,650 --> 00:25:48,280
Did you discuss anything for this round
with Team P3?

584
00:25:48,850 --> 00:25:50,780
What cards will we bring for this round?

585
00:25:50,780 --> 00:25:52,090
Right, we need to plan it.

586
00:25:52,090 --> 00:25:53,990
We need to win the points this round.

587
00:25:53,990 --> 00:25:55,190
Ji Min, go with him.

588
00:25:58,060 --> 00:25:59,560
Where? Isn't it this room?

589
00:25:59,560 --> 00:26:00,730
This room.

590
00:26:00,730 --> 00:26:04,630
(Tae Gyun and Ji Min head
to Team P3's room.)

591
00:26:08,230 --> 00:26:09,740
- Come in.
- Can I go in?

592
00:26:09,740 --> 00:26:11,200
- Who is it?
- Team P1.

593
00:26:11,470 --> 00:26:12,870
What's your plan for this round?

594
00:26:13,040 --> 00:26:14,670
We'll get five points this round.

595
00:26:15,070 --> 00:26:16,810
- With whom?
- With that team.

596
00:26:16,810 --> 00:26:18,110
- Team C.
- Team C and us.

597
00:26:18,110 --> 00:26:19,550
- You'll team up with Team C?
- Yes.

598
00:26:19,610 --> 00:26:21,150
But you said you'd work with us.

599
00:26:21,150 --> 00:26:23,350
We talked with Sang Min about it.

600
00:26:23,350 --> 00:26:26,050
Under the premise that the winning team...

601
00:26:26,050 --> 00:26:28,790
could help the team in last place,

602
00:26:28,790 --> 00:26:30,220
we decided...

603
00:26:30,220 --> 00:26:32,860
to help the team with higher points.

604
00:26:32,860 --> 00:26:34,090
But they will have...

605
00:26:34,090 --> 00:26:35,930
one elimination candidate
from each team...

606
00:26:35,930 --> 00:26:37,100
except the winning team.

607
00:26:37,100 --> 00:26:40,070
Which got us thinking,
"Isn't that risky for us?"

608
00:26:40,170 --> 00:26:41,470
- This...
- It is too dangerous.

609
00:26:41,470 --> 00:26:44,140
But we used the assassin card just now.

610
00:26:44,170 --> 00:26:45,910
- This...
- Don't worry, we'll use the card too.

611
00:26:46,170 --> 00:26:48,880
But you won't use it for us.

612
00:26:49,280 --> 00:26:50,710
When Round Three started,

613
00:26:51,240 --> 00:26:53,010
he said he didn't know...

614
00:26:54,410 --> 00:26:56,350
the elimination candidate would be chosen
from each team.

615
00:26:56,980 --> 00:26:58,550
He said that.

616
00:26:58,550 --> 00:27:00,520
Which made me quite flustered.

617
00:27:00,750 --> 00:27:03,260
You should take responsibility
for your mistake.

618
00:27:03,260 --> 00:27:06,360
Pushing the responsibility onto us
for the mistake they've made.

619
00:27:06,660 --> 00:27:09,500
"Isn't this a betrayal?"
That's what I thought.

620
00:27:10,100 --> 00:27:12,430
You can't trust anyone here.

621
00:27:12,430 --> 00:27:15,270
Although we could play it safe
with Team P2,

622
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:19,240
we took the risk to team up with Team P3.

623
00:27:19,270 --> 00:27:20,710
My head hurt.

624
00:27:20,910 --> 00:27:23,480
As if someone made a full swing at it.

625
00:27:24,640 --> 00:27:26,680
These scums.

626
00:27:27,980 --> 00:27:29,620
We were winning.

627
00:27:31,120 --> 00:27:33,420
Hong Jin Ho and Xitsuh,

628
00:27:33,520 --> 00:27:35,220
they're spineless.

629
00:27:35,490 --> 00:27:38,260
I do feel sorry, but we can't help it.

630
00:27:38,260 --> 00:27:41,960
We betrayed Team C
and got criticized by them.

631
00:27:42,200 --> 00:27:43,630
So you're going with Team C this round?

632
00:27:43,630 --> 00:27:45,030
- We'll work with Team C.
- Yes, for this round.

633
00:27:45,030 --> 00:27:46,700
- I'm making it clear.
- I got it for now.

634
00:27:51,500 --> 00:27:53,740
We have to win, or it's meaningless.

635
00:27:55,580 --> 00:27:57,480
- At first...
- I have a question.

636
00:27:57,810 --> 00:27:59,280
In this game,

637
00:27:59,280 --> 00:28:01,980
does the promise we made with Sang Min
mean anything?

638
00:28:06,590 --> 00:28:09,660
We will begin
Round Three of the card battle.

639
00:28:10,360 --> 00:28:12,590
(Team P1, Jeong Keun Woo)

640
00:28:12,590 --> 00:28:14,430
(Team P2, YunB)

641
00:28:14,430 --> 00:28:17,060
(Team C, Kim You Hyun)

642
00:28:18,260 --> 00:28:20,100
(Team P3, Hong Jin Ho)

643
00:28:20,270 --> 00:28:21,630
Kim You Hyun,

644
00:28:21,630 --> 00:28:24,670
predict the expected wins,
pick the master color, and make your bet.

645
00:28:24,670 --> 00:28:25,740
(The 1st player of Round 3
is Kim You Hyun of Team C.)

646
00:28:27,040 --> 00:28:29,210
I'll bet on zero wins.

647
00:28:29,680 --> 00:28:31,480
- And...
- Pick the master color too.

648
00:28:31,480 --> 00:28:32,650
Blue.

649
00:28:33,210 --> 00:28:35,750
Kim You Hyun has bet on blue, zero wins.

650
00:28:35,750 --> 00:28:37,220
(Team C Kim You Hyun bets on blue, 0 win.)

651
00:28:37,350 --> 00:28:40,250
Blue is the master color of this round.

652
00:28:40,250 --> 00:28:42,390
(Round 3's master color is blue.)

653
00:28:42,390 --> 00:28:44,660
Jeong Keun Woo, YunB, and Hong Jin Ho,

654
00:28:44,660 --> 00:28:46,730
Please submit the card...

655
00:28:46,730 --> 00:28:48,800
you want to give to the Master.

656
00:28:48,800 --> 00:28:50,730
(Jeong Keun Woo submits a card.)

657
00:28:51,360 --> 00:28:53,930
(Hong Jin Ho submits yellow 1.)

658
00:28:54,230 --> 00:28:56,870
Master, check the card you've received.

659
00:29:00,010 --> 00:29:03,340
Please submit the card
you want to give to Hong Jin Ho.

660
00:29:11,880 --> 00:29:16,120
(Hong Jin Ho gets blue 11.)

661
00:29:16,120 --> 00:29:19,430
Please submit the card
you want to give to Jeong Keun Woo.

662
00:29:19,730 --> 00:29:23,130
(Jeong Keun Woo gets red 8.)

663
00:29:23,130 --> 00:29:26,500
Please submit the card
you want to give to YunB.

664
00:29:26,500 --> 00:29:28,740
(YunB gets yellow 8.)

665
00:29:33,470 --> 00:29:35,370
All cards have been exchanged.

666
00:29:35,370 --> 00:29:37,740
(All cards have been exchanged.)

667
00:29:38,410 --> 00:29:40,810
Kim You Hyun, do you wish to name a Mate?

668
00:29:40,850 --> 00:29:42,650
I choose card eleven.

669
00:29:42,650 --> 00:29:43,680
(The Mate of Round 3 is card 11.)

670
00:29:43,980 --> 00:29:47,020
The first set will start with the Master.

671
00:29:47,020 --> 00:29:48,120
(Round 3 Set 1 starts with Kim You Hyun.)

672
00:29:48,420 --> 00:29:50,520
Card eight in green has been submitted.

673
00:29:51,460 --> 00:29:54,260
The lead color of this set is green.

674
00:29:55,390 --> 00:29:58,000
Hong Jin Ho, please submit a card.

675
00:29:59,330 --> 00:30:00,700
I shall become your Mate.

676
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:06,770
Card 11 in blue has been submitted.

677
00:30:07,340 --> 00:30:10,240
Hong Jin Ho has submitted card 11...

678
00:30:10,240 --> 00:30:11,810
and became the Mate.

679
00:30:12,410 --> 00:30:13,850
Let's work together.

680
00:30:14,280 --> 00:30:15,350
Let's.

681
00:30:15,350 --> 00:30:17,750
The situation changed
after every round has ended.

682
00:30:17,750 --> 00:30:20,790
After Rounds 1 and 2, at one point,

683
00:30:20,790 --> 00:30:23,520
zero win has become very important.

684
00:30:23,520 --> 00:30:25,830
In that case, who plays first
is most important.

685
00:30:25,830 --> 00:30:27,960
Anyway, the best we can do is...

686
00:30:27,960 --> 00:30:30,260
Since Team C plays 1st in Round 3
and we play 1st in Round 4,

687
00:30:30,260 --> 00:30:32,800
the best outcome is for us
to share the points.

688
00:30:33,070 --> 00:30:34,100
Excuse me.

689
00:30:34,100 --> 00:30:36,340
(Before Round 3 started,
Team C came to visit Team P3.)

690
00:30:36,340 --> 00:30:38,270
We'll bet on zero wins this time.

691
00:30:39,170 --> 00:30:41,510
- That...
- I think that's morally right.

692
00:30:41,510 --> 00:30:43,080
- You want us to become your Mate?
- Yes.

693
00:30:43,210 --> 00:30:46,310
(Team C offers them to become the Mate
for 0 win first.)

694
00:30:46,310 --> 00:30:47,650
There's no reason for us to say no.

695
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:49,250
Xitsuh, are you okay
with teaming up with us?

696
00:30:49,320 --> 00:30:51,020
Why would I not be okay with it?

697
00:30:51,580 --> 00:30:52,820
It sounds nice.

698
00:30:52,850 --> 00:30:54,490
I'm straightforward.

699
00:30:54,490 --> 00:30:55,960
I say I betrayed you if I do.

700
00:30:55,960 --> 00:30:57,560
This is us keeping up our morals.

701
00:30:57,560 --> 00:30:59,290
- Explain quickly.
- What color?

702
00:30:59,290 --> 00:31:00,560
I'll go with blue and a big number.

703
00:31:00,560 --> 00:31:01,830
(Blue card with a big number)

704
00:31:01,930 --> 00:31:04,160
Team P3 feels sorry for us.

705
00:31:04,260 --> 00:31:06,530
Fine, then, help us...

706
00:31:06,530 --> 00:31:07,670
score points this time.

707
00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:09,640
Let's work together.

708
00:31:09,640 --> 00:31:12,000
(Teams C and P3 become Mates.)

709
00:31:15,440 --> 00:31:18,310
I saw them talking to each other...

710
00:31:18,310 --> 00:31:20,010
right in front of me.

711
00:31:20,010 --> 00:31:21,580
We already got backstabbed.

712
00:31:21,680 --> 00:31:23,220
"They've teamed up."

713
00:31:23,480 --> 00:31:25,950
Because I won the previous round,

714
00:31:25,950 --> 00:31:28,590
I could tell I couldn't win that round.

715
00:31:28,620 --> 00:31:31,090
Jeong Keun Woo, please submit a card.

716
00:31:31,560 --> 00:31:33,930
Card eight in green has been submitted.

717
00:31:35,630 --> 00:31:38,660
YunB has submitted card nine in green.

718
00:31:39,730 --> 00:31:42,030
Hong Jin Ho has won Set One.

719
00:31:42,440 --> 00:31:43,740
Okay, thanks.

720
00:31:43,740 --> 00:31:46,710
(Hong Jin Ho of Team P3
wins Round 3 Set 1.)

721
00:31:47,140 --> 00:31:50,280
The second set
will start with Hong Jin Ho.

722
00:31:52,180 --> 00:31:54,110
Including the assassin card,

723
00:31:54,110 --> 00:31:57,820
I brought a lot of blue cards
with big numbers.

724
00:31:57,980 --> 00:32:00,490
I kept submitting blue cards
with big numbers...

725
00:32:00,490 --> 00:32:02,020
and gained the upper hand.

726
00:32:02,290 --> 00:32:03,490
I choose this.

727
00:32:04,160 --> 00:32:06,630
Card 16 in blue has been submitted.

728
00:32:06,960 --> 00:32:08,630
(Round 3 Set 3)

729
00:32:08,630 --> 00:32:10,900
Card 15 in blue has been submitted.

730
00:32:10,900 --> 00:32:13,070
(Round 3 Set 4)

731
00:32:13,070 --> 00:32:15,330
Card 14 in blue has been submitted.

732
00:32:15,900 --> 00:32:16,900
I choose 13.

733
00:32:16,900 --> 00:32:19,240
Card 13 in blue has been submitted.

734
00:32:19,240 --> 00:32:21,140
After 3 comes 2.

735
00:32:21,570 --> 00:32:24,210
Card 12 in blue has been submitted.

736
00:32:24,280 --> 00:32:26,610
Hong Jin Ho has won Set Two.

737
00:32:26,610 --> 00:32:28,180
Hong Jin Ho has won Set Three.

738
00:32:28,550 --> 00:32:31,150
(Hong Jin Ho keeps winning points.)

739
00:32:31,150 --> 00:32:33,590
- Hong Jin Ho has won Set Seven.
- Okay.

740
00:32:33,690 --> 00:32:35,350
I keep throwing blue cards...

741
00:32:35,350 --> 00:32:37,790
and secure the wins.

742
00:32:37,790 --> 00:32:40,130
Since I win all the sets,
he'll automatically achieve zero wins.

743
00:32:40,130 --> 00:32:42,560
It's a very predictable way
to play the game.

744
00:32:42,560 --> 00:32:43,860
After that,

745
00:32:44,160 --> 00:32:46,170
it was smooth-sailing as planned.

746
00:32:46,300 --> 00:32:49,470
The eighth set will start
with Hong Jin Ho.

747
00:32:49,470 --> 00:32:51,300
The assassin card has been submitted.

748
00:32:51,740 --> 00:32:54,140
There is no lead color for this set.

749
00:32:54,440 --> 00:32:57,710
Jeong Keun Woo has submitted
card ten in red.

750
00:32:57,710 --> 00:33:00,850
YunB has submitted card nine in red.

751
00:33:01,050 --> 00:33:04,320
Kim You Hyun has submitted
card one in yellow.

752
00:33:04,820 --> 00:33:07,320
Jeong Keun Woo has won Set Eight.

753
00:33:08,520 --> 00:33:11,290
Team Challenger has
successfully predicted zero wins.

754
00:33:11,290 --> 00:33:14,330
Team C and its Mate P3 each get 5 points.

755
00:33:14,330 --> 00:33:15,660
It was nice making a deal with you.

756
00:33:22,400 --> 00:33:23,840
For the win...

757
00:33:24,100 --> 00:33:26,640
What's with them?

758
00:33:27,470 --> 00:33:28,510
What are they doing?

759
00:33:28,510 --> 00:33:30,210
Why are they excluding me
from the conversation?

760
00:33:30,210 --> 00:33:32,180
I felt that something was off.

761
00:33:32,240 --> 00:33:34,780
It feels uneasy and uncomfortable.

762
00:33:34,780 --> 00:33:38,550
I felt that things were going
in the wrong direction.

763
00:33:38,550 --> 00:33:41,220
The atmosphere was strange.

764
00:33:41,750 --> 00:33:45,290
(Running Mate score)

765
00:33:46,730 --> 00:33:48,290
I feel a bit at ease.

766
00:33:48,290 --> 00:33:49,560
- Me too.
- Right.

767
00:33:49,560 --> 00:33:51,660
- It's better this way.
- I agree.

768
00:33:51,660 --> 00:33:53,300
- We'll do this and...
- But...

769
00:33:53,300 --> 00:33:55,770
We can't let Team P1 win.

770
00:33:55,770 --> 00:33:58,170
- I think Sang Min...
- We can't work with him.

771
00:33:58,170 --> 00:34:00,770
lied to us once.

772
00:34:00,870 --> 00:34:03,210
He purposely said...

773
00:34:03,210 --> 00:34:04,740
- that we misheard it.
- We can't work with him.

774
00:34:04,840 --> 00:34:06,350
He's our common enemy.

775
00:34:06,750 --> 00:34:08,410
Let's work with us next time.

776
00:34:08,410 --> 00:34:09,480
Sounds good.

777
00:34:09,520 --> 00:34:10,950
- Let's go up.
- In case...

778
00:34:13,820 --> 00:34:14,950
- Sung Joo.
- Yes?

779
00:34:16,720 --> 00:34:17,860
This...

780
00:34:17,860 --> 00:34:20,630
Just now, Sang Min said...

781
00:34:21,290 --> 00:34:25,870
we didn't know for sure
if each team would have...

782
00:34:25,900 --> 00:34:28,930
an elimination candidate
or only one team would have it.

783
00:34:29,470 --> 00:34:31,200
How do you plan to break through?

784
00:34:31,740 --> 00:34:33,070
I don't get it.

785
00:34:33,070 --> 00:34:36,980
Every team except the winning team
will have an elimination candidate.

786
00:34:37,510 --> 00:34:39,810
- So...
- No, you heard it wrongly.

787
00:34:40,410 --> 00:34:43,850
Except the winning team, each team...

788
00:34:43,850 --> 00:34:45,790
I don't know
if they'll go for a Deathmatch...

789
00:34:45,790 --> 00:34:47,250
No, not at all.

790
00:34:47,250 --> 00:34:50,290
You say that
because that's what you think.

791
00:34:50,660 --> 00:34:53,890
Everyone must remember the same thing.

792
00:34:54,730 --> 00:34:56,760
It was revealed to everyone,

793
00:34:56,760 --> 00:34:59,570
and there's no way
so many people misheard it.

794
00:34:59,570 --> 00:35:01,100
There must be a reason.

795
00:35:01,170 --> 00:35:04,640
Unless he's doing all that for no reason,

796
00:35:04,640 --> 00:35:06,910
he either really didn't understand it...

797
00:35:06,910 --> 00:35:08,210
or misheard it,

798
00:35:08,370 --> 00:35:10,410
or he's drunk.

799
00:35:10,410 --> 00:35:12,880
I don't know if he said that on purpose...

800
00:35:12,880 --> 00:35:14,880
- Everything Team P1 says is a lie.
- All...

801
00:35:14,880 --> 00:35:17,150
He says he's drunk on whiskey,

802
00:35:17,150 --> 00:35:18,980
but he's not the type
to take filming so lightly.

803
00:35:18,980 --> 00:35:20,120
He's lying.

804
00:35:20,120 --> 00:35:21,250
They're all lying.

805
00:35:21,250 --> 00:35:22,490
Ji Min and Sang Min are both liars.

806
00:35:22,490 --> 00:35:23,690
- They're all lying.
- But...

807
00:35:23,690 --> 00:35:25,460
the whiskey is real. I tried a sip.

808
00:35:25,460 --> 00:35:26,730
It is actually whiskey.

809
00:35:27,230 --> 00:35:28,390
Hey!

810
00:35:28,390 --> 00:35:29,760
Here he comes.

811
00:35:32,670 --> 00:35:34,070
Why did you lie?

812
00:35:34,430 --> 00:35:35,670
You Hyun?

813
00:35:35,840 --> 00:35:36,970
You startled me.

814
00:35:37,970 --> 00:35:40,670
- Why is he so riled up?
- No. Listen to it carefully.

815
00:35:40,670 --> 00:35:41,870
That's very important.

816
00:35:41,870 --> 00:35:44,140
He was so loud at night,

817
00:35:44,140 --> 00:35:45,240
which startled me.

818
00:35:45,240 --> 00:35:47,950
Sang Min suddenly...

819
00:35:47,950 --> 00:35:49,920
exploded.

820
00:35:49,920 --> 00:35:52,750
"Who said there would be
one elimination candidate from each team?"

821
00:35:52,950 --> 00:35:55,620
"Who said that?"

822
00:35:55,620 --> 00:35:57,290
He said that...

823
00:35:57,360 --> 00:35:59,930
and got very angry at You Hyun.

824
00:35:59,930 --> 00:36:01,990
I'm still puzzled.

825
00:36:02,230 --> 00:36:04,760
Did he actually misunderstand it,

826
00:36:04,860 --> 00:36:06,700
or was he playing high-level mind games...

827
00:36:06,700 --> 00:36:09,340
to turn me into a liar and a traitor?

828
00:36:09,340 --> 00:36:11,070
There's just no reason for him to do that.

829
00:36:11,470 --> 00:36:13,470
If the elimination candidates are chosen
from all the teams...

830
00:36:13,470 --> 00:36:15,440
except the winning team,

831
00:36:15,940 --> 00:36:18,440
the deals they've suggested...

832
00:36:18,440 --> 00:36:20,410
would not work.

833
00:36:20,810 --> 00:36:24,250
The elimination candidate is chosen from
the teams other than the winning team.

834
00:36:24,250 --> 00:36:26,750
- From the other teams.
- But they didn't say one from each team.

835
00:36:26,950 --> 00:36:28,490
They said it was one from each team.

836
00:36:28,490 --> 00:36:30,290
No. Listen to it carefully.

837
00:36:30,320 --> 00:36:32,320
It's very important, Seung Jin.

838
00:36:32,530 --> 00:36:34,360
- Is it just one person?
- It's very important.

839
00:36:34,390 --> 00:36:36,800
He's trying to confuse us.

840
00:36:39,170 --> 00:36:41,200
It isn't one from each team.

841
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:44,540
Actually, for survival games like this,

842
00:36:44,540 --> 00:36:48,810
you must listen to and understand
the rules accurately.

843
00:36:48,970 --> 00:36:52,550
You need to study what variations
you can give it.

844
00:36:52,780 --> 00:36:53,980
That's how...

845
00:36:54,050 --> 00:36:56,550
you can cause confusion at the start.

846
00:36:56,720 --> 00:36:58,680
"How can I steal what they have?"

847
00:36:59,150 --> 00:37:01,950
"How can we steal it
and make it beneficial for us?"

848
00:37:02,220 --> 00:37:03,290
This strategy.

849
00:37:03,290 --> 00:37:06,230
I came up with the strategy
to spread false information.

850
00:37:10,730 --> 00:37:11,900
For now,

851
00:37:12,700 --> 00:37:15,170
when he wins the points,

852
00:37:15,470 --> 00:37:17,070
let's spread a lie.

853
00:37:21,040 --> 00:37:22,980
This is the lie we'll spread.

854
00:37:22,980 --> 00:37:24,210
The winning team...

855
00:37:24,910 --> 00:37:27,780
will choose the elimination candidates.

856
00:37:28,550 --> 00:37:30,780
- They get the exemption ticket?
- Yes.

857
00:37:31,220 --> 00:37:33,590
I thought I could make use of it...

858
00:37:33,690 --> 00:37:35,750
to confuse them.

859
00:37:35,890 --> 00:37:37,090
And today,

860
00:37:37,090 --> 00:37:39,290
every team will have
an elimination candidate...

861
00:37:39,290 --> 00:37:41,060
except the winning team.

862
00:37:41,430 --> 00:37:43,700
The elimination candidates
will be from all the teams...

863
00:37:43,700 --> 00:37:46,270
except the winning team.

864
00:37:46,670 --> 00:37:47,930
Which means...

865
00:37:48,470 --> 00:37:49,800
the winning team...

866
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:54,040
can decide...

867
00:37:54,440 --> 00:37:57,140
the elimination candidates.

868
00:37:57,810 --> 00:37:59,210
In that case,

869
00:37:59,210 --> 00:38:02,480
you'll have to read the situation
carefully.

870
00:38:02,780 --> 00:38:05,720
As time goes by, lies will be revealed.

871
00:38:05,780 --> 00:38:08,420
So I should spread the false information
at the start...

872
00:38:09,560 --> 00:38:10,890
and secure us some points.

873
00:38:11,360 --> 00:38:14,260
Okay. So this is what I think.

874
00:38:14,960 --> 00:38:17,060
I think the winning team...

875
00:38:17,760 --> 00:38:21,170
will select the elimination candidates.

876
00:38:21,900 --> 00:38:23,340
Because they said...

877
00:38:23,340 --> 00:38:27,040
everyone except the winning team
could become the elimination candidate.

878
00:38:27,140 --> 00:38:28,510
They didn't specify which team.

879
00:38:28,640 --> 00:38:31,580
That means the winning team
could decide the elimination candidates.

880
00:38:31,580 --> 00:38:34,380
Like, "Out of the three teams,
you guys are eliminated?"

881
00:38:35,180 --> 00:38:36,920
That's obviously a lie.

882
00:38:37,550 --> 00:38:39,120
If I can confuse them,

883
00:38:39,150 --> 00:38:42,050
this plan will work.

884
00:38:42,190 --> 00:38:43,990
If that's how the elimination works...

885
00:38:43,990 --> 00:38:46,790
What he said was the whole team...

886
00:38:46,790 --> 00:38:48,160
Team P1 thought that too?

887
00:38:48,160 --> 00:38:49,730
I don't know if it's true or not.

888
00:38:49,730 --> 00:38:51,000
(As per Sang Min's plan, the announcement
about the elimination candidate...)

889
00:38:51,000 --> 00:38:52,300
(brought upon huge chaos.)

890
00:38:52,330 --> 00:38:54,500
How someone is eliminated...

891
00:38:54,500 --> 00:38:58,770
has a huge impact on this game.

892
00:38:59,070 --> 00:39:02,310
I didn't understand
why they didn't listen carefully...

893
00:39:02,310 --> 00:39:05,210
and remember it in the first place.

894
00:39:05,310 --> 00:39:08,710
I also didn't understand
why they didn't bother to check it.

895
00:39:08,950 --> 00:39:12,050
So I decided to check it first.

896
00:39:12,690 --> 00:39:16,390
(In the end,
Kim You Hyun visits Voting Room.)

897
00:39:18,560 --> 00:39:19,630
Well...

898
00:39:19,890 --> 00:39:23,560
I'd like to ask about the announcement.

899
00:39:23,560 --> 00:39:25,100
Was the exact sentence...

900
00:39:25,330 --> 00:39:28,300
"The elimination candidate
will be chosen..."

901
00:39:28,470 --> 00:39:30,670
"from the three teams which didn't win?"

902
00:39:30,770 --> 00:39:35,970
I'd like to ask the exact sentence
of the announcement.

903
00:39:36,480 --> 00:39:40,310
Every team except the winning team
will have an elimination candidate.

904
00:39:40,810 --> 00:39:42,210
From every team?

905
00:39:42,210 --> 00:39:44,420
That means I was right. That jerk.

906
00:39:44,420 --> 00:39:45,820
Thank you.

907
00:39:46,590 --> 00:39:50,260
"Every team except the winning team
will have an elimination candidate."

908
00:39:50,260 --> 00:39:51,720
That was what she said.

909
00:39:51,860 --> 00:39:54,590
(Every team rechecks the announcement
about the elimination candidate.)

910
00:39:54,590 --> 00:39:56,730
Every team except the winning team...

911
00:39:56,730 --> 00:39:58,630
will have an elimination candidate.

912
00:39:59,060 --> 00:40:01,970
(Every team except the winning team
will have an elimination candidate.)

913
00:40:01,970 --> 00:40:03,000
Thank you.

914
00:40:04,170 --> 00:40:05,500
Okay.

915
00:40:05,570 --> 00:40:07,770
I think what You Hyun said
is closer to the truth.

916
00:40:07,910 --> 00:40:10,810
"Every team except the winning team..."

917
00:40:10,810 --> 00:40:12,510
"will have an elimination candidate."

918
00:40:12,510 --> 00:40:14,080
I asked if it's confirmed
that every team will have one,

919
00:40:14,080 --> 00:40:15,110
and she said yes.

920
00:40:15,150 --> 00:40:17,880
Sang Min was wrong and You Hyun was right.

921
00:40:18,180 --> 00:40:19,820
Except the winning team,
at least one from each team...

922
00:40:19,820 --> 00:40:21,420
will have to play the Deathmatch?

923
00:40:22,120 --> 00:40:24,020
That's different from what he said.
That means we must win.

924
00:40:24,020 --> 00:40:25,090
I...

925
00:40:25,390 --> 00:40:27,490
Rules make and break me.

926
00:40:27,630 --> 00:40:29,460
So what I thought then was,

927
00:40:29,460 --> 00:40:30,530
"What is this?"

928
00:40:30,630 --> 00:40:32,930
"Is this also a part of Sang Min's plan?"

929
00:40:34,130 --> 00:40:35,300
The confusion.

930
00:40:37,040 --> 00:40:38,340
At that moment,

931
00:40:39,570 --> 00:40:42,110
I started to become wary...

932
00:40:42,110 --> 00:40:44,610
of Team P1...

933
00:40:44,610 --> 00:40:47,410
and feel some hostility toward them.

934
00:40:47,680 --> 00:40:49,880
Okay.
"Every team except the winning team..."

935
00:40:49,880 --> 00:40:53,050
"will have an elimination candidate."
That's all she'll say.

936
00:40:53,350 --> 00:40:54,690
She won't say anything else.

937
00:40:54,820 --> 00:40:55,990
- So...
- "Except the winning team."

938
00:40:55,990 --> 00:40:57,860
We don't know if it's one per team.

939
00:40:57,860 --> 00:40:59,430
In the end, Sang Min lied to us.

940
00:40:59,430 --> 00:41:03,930
Since then, Team P1's mistake...

941
00:41:04,060 --> 00:41:05,530
snowballed.

942
00:41:05,530 --> 00:41:07,900
Everyone agreed...

943
00:41:07,900 --> 00:41:10,040
that they didn't like...

944
00:41:10,040 --> 00:41:11,870
what Team P1 did.

945
00:41:12,000 --> 00:41:15,440
"Let's drag down Team P1..."

946
00:41:15,440 --> 00:41:18,810
"who runs that wicked snake tongue
of theirs."

947
00:41:18,840 --> 00:41:21,750
Honestly, it feels like
they're our common enemy.

948
00:41:21,750 --> 00:41:23,320
- Can I sit here?
- Sit down.

949
00:41:23,320 --> 00:41:25,650
- Team P1 has become like a common enemy.
- Right.

950
00:41:25,650 --> 00:41:27,690
And we all agree...

951
00:41:27,690 --> 00:41:29,660
Darn it. What's happening?

952
00:41:29,660 --> 00:41:30,760
We're screwed.

953
00:41:30,760 --> 00:41:31,960
What's this?

954
00:41:32,660 --> 00:41:33,830
Can we go in?

955
00:41:33,830 --> 00:41:35,230
We'll talk first.

956
00:41:35,230 --> 00:41:37,700
Can we talk later?

957
00:41:37,930 --> 00:41:39,130
Okay.

958
00:41:39,670 --> 00:41:41,570
All the teams had gathered there.

959
00:41:42,070 --> 00:41:44,940
Which means the three teams were
in a discussion.

960
00:41:45,240 --> 00:41:46,510
This has to be...

961
00:41:46,510 --> 00:41:47,810
an alliance.

962
00:41:48,570 --> 00:41:50,480
- Shall we start discussing?
- Shall we?

963
00:41:50,480 --> 00:41:51,640
Yes, go ahead.

964
00:41:51,640 --> 00:41:52,980
Let me continue.

965
00:41:52,980 --> 00:41:55,550
We all were fooled by Team P1,

966
00:41:55,550 --> 00:41:58,250
so we don't want to see them win.

967
00:41:58,350 --> 00:42:00,150
In the end, one team has to sacrifice.

968
00:42:00,320 --> 00:42:01,690
One team has to sacrifice...

969
00:42:01,690 --> 00:42:03,660
to help another team win.

970
00:42:04,020 --> 00:42:05,860
They must become the kingmaker
to make a king.

971
00:42:05,860 --> 00:42:08,290
And they get the corresponding help
in return?

972
00:42:08,290 --> 00:42:10,530
Actually,

973
00:42:10,560 --> 00:42:12,060
I don't think that's hard.

974
00:42:12,060 --> 00:42:13,900
For example, we've decided
who'll go to the Deathmatch.

975
00:42:13,900 --> 00:42:15,070
I will.

976
00:42:15,200 --> 00:42:17,140
What Team P2 wants...

977
00:42:17,300 --> 00:42:19,870
is for all 3 teams to get 10 points each.

978
00:42:20,510 --> 00:42:22,940
(If Teams P2 and C successfully bet on
zero-vote Mate,)

979
00:42:22,940 --> 00:42:25,680
(everyone becomes a draw.)

980
00:42:25,740 --> 00:42:28,480
But we couldn't justify it.

981
00:42:28,750 --> 00:42:30,580
That's when I...

982
00:42:30,580 --> 00:42:32,220
offered a deal.

983
00:42:32,220 --> 00:42:33,920
If my team loses
and has to play the Deathmatch,

984
00:42:33,920 --> 00:42:35,050
I'll go.

985
00:42:35,090 --> 00:42:37,320
Team P3 can win the game.

986
00:42:37,560 --> 00:42:40,690
But later, help Team P2.

987
00:42:40,860 --> 00:42:43,200
In a way, I set the stage,

988
00:42:43,360 --> 00:42:45,800
so I thought I should take the bullet.

989
00:42:46,200 --> 00:42:49,570
But we want a strong alliance in return.

990
00:42:49,900 --> 00:42:51,100
That's all I ask for.

991
00:42:51,340 --> 00:42:53,240
You want us to make you win?
Or you want to work together?

992
00:42:54,070 --> 00:42:55,340
Things will change tomorrow,

993
00:42:55,340 --> 00:42:57,180
so I'm not asking you
to do this every time.

994
00:42:57,180 --> 00:42:58,980
Let's work together tomorrow.

995
00:42:58,980 --> 00:43:00,350
- We can do that much.
- Yes.

996
00:43:00,350 --> 00:43:01,810
Just keep that promise. That's all I need.

997
00:43:01,810 --> 00:43:03,080
- Here...
- Okay.

998
00:43:03,080 --> 00:43:05,520
If two people from the team
in last place need to play...

999
00:43:05,520 --> 00:43:07,290
the Deathmatch, things will get awkward.

1000
00:43:07,290 --> 00:43:08,990
We will make the sacrifice,

1001
00:43:08,990 --> 00:43:13,130
but if possible, can you make a deck
which we can catch up to Team P1?

1002
00:43:13,130 --> 00:43:15,960
We'll definitely do it if we can.

1003
00:43:15,960 --> 00:43:18,360
Okay. So what's the plan for this round?

1004
00:43:18,560 --> 00:43:20,870
Since Team C is here, I'll be direct.

1005
00:43:21,730 --> 00:43:24,600
Team P2 decided to make
a sacrifice-not-sacrifice.

1006
00:43:24,600 --> 00:43:26,770
For us,

1007
00:43:27,410 --> 00:43:29,010
we feel bad...

1008
00:43:29,110 --> 00:43:31,380
to share the points with you
and ask them to use the assassin card.

1009
00:43:31,480 --> 00:43:33,650
We must work with the team...

1010
00:43:33,650 --> 00:43:36,110
which has the assassin card
that can counter the dictator card.

1011
00:43:36,210 --> 00:43:39,150
And the only team remaining was Team P2.

1012
00:43:39,150 --> 00:43:40,350
(Only Team P2 has the assassin card.)

1013
00:43:40,390 --> 00:43:43,220
So it'd be safer if we asked
for Team C's understanding...

1014
00:43:43,220 --> 00:43:46,060
and shared the points with Team P2.

1015
00:43:46,060 --> 00:43:47,930
You don't need
to split the points with us.

1016
00:43:47,930 --> 00:43:49,700
You don't need to share with us.
You can go with them.

1017
00:43:49,700 --> 00:43:51,930
If you don't mind, can we share
with them for this round?

1018
00:43:52,030 --> 00:43:53,330
Sure.

1019
00:43:53,330 --> 00:43:56,070
I didn't think it raised our chances...

1020
00:43:56,070 --> 00:43:57,840
of winning the game.

1021
00:43:58,300 --> 00:44:01,740
If we can't win, it'll be better
to cooperate with the other teams...

1022
00:44:01,810 --> 00:44:04,380
instead of getting on their bad side.

1023
00:44:04,640 --> 00:44:06,010
If we can't win,

1024
00:44:06,010 --> 00:44:08,150
our goal is to put Team P1 in last place.

1025
00:44:08,310 --> 00:44:10,220
This is Team P1's karma.

1026
00:44:10,220 --> 00:44:12,680
They can't think of it
as us ganging up on them.

1027
00:44:12,680 --> 00:44:14,190
They can't play the victim here.

1028
00:44:14,190 --> 00:44:15,750
They had fun betraying others,

1029
00:44:15,750 --> 00:44:17,460
but they feel upset
when they get betrayed?

1030
00:44:17,460 --> 00:44:19,320
That's like a thief turning on the master
with a club.

1031
00:44:19,460 --> 00:44:21,190
Go with it.

1032
00:44:21,530 --> 00:44:22,660
Are you okay with it?

1033
00:44:22,660 --> 00:44:25,100
- Do I need to pass it to you?
- Yes.

1034
00:44:25,860 --> 00:44:28,030
- Then we...
- If we reverse it,

1035
00:44:28,270 --> 00:44:30,070
the Master will start, right?

1036
00:44:30,070 --> 00:44:31,470
The Master starts, and it goes in reverse?

1037
00:44:31,470 --> 00:44:33,110
The starting player doesn't change.

1038
00:44:39,240 --> 00:44:43,580
They had formed an alliance without us.

1039
00:44:43,850 --> 00:44:45,280
We can't beat all three teams.

1040
00:44:45,520 --> 00:44:48,590
On the off chance
that they make a mistake,

1041
00:44:48,590 --> 00:44:49,960
we may earn some points.

1042
00:44:50,420 --> 00:44:51,820
But we have no options.

1043
00:44:51,990 --> 00:44:54,860
So, I needed information
from that point on.

1044
00:44:55,230 --> 00:44:57,300
I had no choice
but to climb over the wall...

1045
00:44:57,430 --> 00:44:58,930
to figure out...

1046
00:44:58,930 --> 00:45:00,630
how many there were
and what they were talking about.

1047
00:45:00,900 --> 00:45:03,300
I feel like they'll talk to each other
outside.

1048
00:45:15,050 --> 00:45:16,980
Gosh, that hurts.

1049
00:45:18,450 --> 00:45:20,720
Man. Why is it so tall?

1050
00:45:32,730 --> 00:45:34,400
This is so annoying.

1051
00:45:49,180 --> 00:45:50,780
That's so tall.

1052
00:46:17,110 --> 00:46:21,110
Best-case scenario,
I can go over and listen in.

1053
00:46:21,650 --> 00:46:22,810
If I can't,

1054
00:46:22,810 --> 00:46:25,120
finding out who's talking to whom...

1055
00:46:25,120 --> 00:46:26,380
is good enough.

1056
00:46:27,090 --> 00:46:28,090
But...

1057
00:46:35,960 --> 00:46:37,360
I could clearly hear them.

1058
00:46:37,930 --> 00:46:40,230
I pricked my ears as hard as I could.

1059
00:46:40,800 --> 00:46:43,000
The assassin card at the end.

1060
00:46:43,470 --> 00:46:44,840
If we get a dictator card,

1061
00:46:44,870 --> 00:46:46,440
we use the assassin card.

1062
00:46:47,010 --> 00:46:50,310
Number 4 will be 14
since we have 2 of them.

1063
00:46:50,710 --> 00:46:52,410
I'll call 14.

1064
00:46:52,740 --> 00:46:55,980
If I designate a Mate in the 1st round,
I'll pick 14.

1065
00:47:02,750 --> 00:47:03,820
Reverse.

1066
00:47:05,060 --> 00:47:07,790
Yellow 14, blue 1, assassin.

1067
00:47:15,500 --> 00:47:16,500
Reverse.

1068
00:47:18,170 --> 00:47:21,070
Give me blue 1,
and I'll give you yellow 14.

1069
00:47:21,740 --> 00:47:23,010
This is so tough.

1070
00:47:28,080 --> 00:47:29,180
I got all the information.

1071
00:47:29,180 --> 00:47:31,180
(Back in Team P1's room)

1072
00:47:31,180 --> 00:47:32,480
What did they say?

1073
00:47:32,850 --> 00:47:35,550
- From Round Four, they'll...
- Yes.

1074
00:47:36,720 --> 00:47:37,760
start...

1075
00:47:37,920 --> 00:47:39,090
- Go after us?
- going after us.

1076
00:47:39,760 --> 00:47:40,930
- Us?
- Yes.

1077
00:47:41,690 --> 00:47:43,730
That's when things got out of hand.

1078
00:47:43,800 --> 00:47:46,160
That's when all the teams started...

1079
00:47:46,160 --> 00:47:49,100
getting hostile with us.

1080
00:47:49,230 --> 00:47:53,210
We were suddenly put in a situation
where we couldn't make any alliances.

1081
00:47:53,370 --> 00:47:57,910
I was like, "It's 3 versus 1 from Day 1?"

1082
00:47:58,010 --> 00:48:00,450
The cards they'll use are
assassin, reverse,

1083
00:48:01,250 --> 00:48:03,350
- blue 1, and yellow 14.
- Okay.

1084
00:48:03,350 --> 00:48:04,420
(He tells them what he heard.)

1085
00:48:04,420 --> 00:48:05,550
That's all I heard.

1086
00:48:06,150 --> 00:48:10,560
If we're losing anyway,
let's just give them bad cards.

1087
00:48:11,120 --> 00:48:12,660
Should we?

1088
00:48:13,020 --> 00:48:16,360
The three teams were going to use
the assassin card in that round,

1089
00:48:16,360 --> 00:48:20,170
so we decided to save our dictator card.

1090
00:48:20,170 --> 00:48:23,300
So, we gave Ji Min
all the cards that we didn't need...

1091
00:48:23,300 --> 00:48:24,600
in that round.

1092
00:48:25,170 --> 00:48:28,170
Round Four's card battle will begin now.

1093
00:48:28,840 --> 00:48:31,640
(Team P1, Park Ji Min)

1094
00:48:31,880 --> 00:48:33,810
(Team P2, Ha Seung Jin)

1095
00:48:33,950 --> 00:48:36,780
(Team P3, Xitsuh)

1096
00:48:36,980 --> 00:48:38,950
(Team C, Kim Nam Hee)

1097
00:48:39,150 --> 00:48:40,490
Xitsuh,

1098
00:48:40,490 --> 00:48:43,460
please pick your expected wins
and master color for the bet.

1099
00:48:44,560 --> 00:48:45,860
Zero wins.

1100
00:48:47,390 --> 00:48:50,630
And the master color will be yellow.

1101
00:48:50,800 --> 00:48:53,100
You bet on zero wins and yellow.

1102
00:48:53,100 --> 00:48:54,370
(Xitsuh bets on yellow and 0 wins.)

1103
00:48:54,430 --> 00:48:57,640
Xitsuh has become the Master
for betting zero wins.

1104
00:48:57,840 --> 00:49:00,270
Yellow is the master color of this round.

1105
00:49:01,410 --> 00:49:04,140
And I'll use the reverse card.

1106
00:49:07,250 --> 00:49:10,520
Xitsuh has used the reverse card.

1107
00:49:11,380 --> 00:49:14,690
The direction of card play shifts
to counter-clockwise.

1108
00:49:14,690 --> 00:49:15,850
(It changes to counter-clockwise.)

1109
00:49:16,290 --> 00:49:18,660
Ji Min, Seung Jin, and Nam Hee,

1110
00:49:18,660 --> 00:49:21,990
please select the card to give
to the Master and submit it.

1111
00:49:22,030 --> 00:49:24,960
(Seung Jin submits 1.)

1112
00:49:27,900 --> 00:49:30,240
Master, check the cards you received.

1113
00:49:35,010 --> 00:49:38,380
Submit the card
you want to give to Nam Hee.

1114
00:49:40,250 --> 00:49:43,780
(Nam Hee gets 8.)

1115
00:49:44,220 --> 00:49:47,390
Submit the card
you want to give to Seung Jin.

1116
00:49:47,390 --> 00:49:49,320
(Seung Jin gets 14.)

1117
00:49:49,920 --> 00:49:53,060
Submit the card
you want to give to Ji Min.

1118
00:49:53,060 --> 00:49:55,390
(Ji Min gets 7.)

1119
00:49:55,730 --> 00:49:57,460
All cards have been exchanged.

1120
00:49:57,460 --> 00:49:59,100
(All cards have been exchanged.)

1121
00:49:59,200 --> 00:50:01,530
Xitsuh,
would you like to designate a Mate?

1122
00:50:02,200 --> 00:50:03,670
I'll pick 14.

1123
00:50:04,440 --> 00:50:08,240
The 1st player to submit 14
becomes the Mate in this round.

1124
00:50:09,340 --> 00:50:12,310
The Master will start the first set.

1125
00:50:12,810 --> 00:50:15,580
Xitsuh has submitted blue 13.

1126
00:50:15,810 --> 00:50:18,280
The lead color of this set is blue.

1127
00:50:19,150 --> 00:50:22,020
Nam Hee has submitted blue eight.

1128
00:50:23,020 --> 00:50:26,160
Seung Jin has submitted yellow 14.

1129
00:50:26,690 --> 00:50:29,430
Seung Jin submitted 14...

1130
00:50:29,430 --> 00:50:30,760
and became the Mate.

1131
00:50:30,760 --> 00:50:31,800
(Teams P3 and P2 are Mates.)

1132
00:50:32,000 --> 00:50:34,130
Ji Min, please submit your card.

1133
00:50:34,130 --> 00:50:37,200
(Park Ji Min)

1134
00:50:37,200 --> 00:50:38,300
(Blue 10)

1135
00:50:38,300 --> 00:50:40,410
You have submitted blue ten.

1136
00:50:41,310 --> 00:50:43,780
Those two were working together,

1137
00:50:44,510 --> 00:50:46,110
so it got difficult.

1138
00:50:47,150 --> 00:50:49,210
There were cards that I brought...

1139
00:50:49,210 --> 00:50:52,020
to call the Mate to stop them,

1140
00:50:52,020 --> 00:50:54,950
but they bet zero wins...

1141
00:50:54,950 --> 00:50:57,190
and called the numbers
they had already decided on.

1142
00:50:57,190 --> 00:50:58,190
(Round 4, Set 2)

1143
00:50:58,190 --> 00:51:00,530
You've submitted yellow 16.

1144
00:51:01,690 --> 00:51:03,900
You've submitted green nine.

1145
00:51:04,000 --> 00:51:06,200
Seung Jin wins the second set.

1146
00:51:06,260 --> 00:51:07,730
(Round 4, Set 3)

1147
00:51:07,730 --> 00:51:10,300
You've submitted yellow 13.

1148
00:51:10,570 --> 00:51:11,840
(Round 4, Set 5)

1149
00:51:11,840 --> 00:51:14,210
You've submitted yellow 12.

1150
00:51:15,010 --> 00:51:17,210
You've submitted yellow 11.

1151
00:51:17,480 --> 00:51:18,740
Seung Jin wins the fifth set.

1152
00:51:18,740 --> 00:51:20,280
Seung Jin wins the sixth set.

1153
00:51:20,380 --> 00:51:22,580
Seung Jin wins the seventh set.

1154
00:51:25,850 --> 00:51:28,550
There wasn't anything I could do.

1155
00:51:29,490 --> 00:51:30,760
It was devastating.

1156
00:51:31,090 --> 00:51:34,360
Seung Jin will start the eighth set.

1157
00:51:37,100 --> 00:51:39,030
You've submitted the assassin card.

1158
00:51:39,030 --> 00:51:40,870
(Seung Jin, assassin)

1159
00:51:40,870 --> 00:51:43,640
Ji Min has submitted blue 9.

1160
00:51:43,640 --> 00:51:45,540
(Ji Min, blue 9)

1161
00:51:45,540 --> 00:51:48,570
Xitsuh has submitted green 1.

1162
00:51:48,770 --> 00:51:51,580
Nam Hee has submitted blue 5.

1163
00:51:51,580 --> 00:51:53,240
(Nam Hee, blue 5)

1164
00:51:53,240 --> 00:51:55,350
Ji Min wins the eighth set.

1165
00:51:55,350 --> 00:51:56,480
(Ji Min, blue 9)

1166
00:51:56,920 --> 00:51:59,520
Team P3 successfully expected 0 wins.

1167
00:52:00,250 --> 00:52:03,490
Team P2, your Mate, also gets five points.

1168
00:52:04,060 --> 00:52:05,620
Round Four has ended.

1169
00:52:05,620 --> 00:52:07,190
Please leave the main hall.

1170
00:52:12,960 --> 00:52:17,540
(Team P3 takes the lead.)

1171
00:52:17,570 --> 00:52:21,740
(Card status, Team P1)

1172
00:52:21,740 --> 00:52:25,440
(Card status, Team P2)

1173
00:52:25,440 --> 00:52:29,680
(Card status, Team P3)

1174
00:52:29,680 --> 00:52:33,990
(Card status, Team C)

1175
00:52:34,920 --> 00:52:37,890
Please gather in the main hall
to reassign your places.

1176
00:52:39,460 --> 00:52:41,160
Enter the Voting Room 1 by 1...

1177
00:52:41,530 --> 00:52:44,060
and draw the places.

1178
00:52:50,030 --> 00:52:52,240
Please pick an order card.

1179
00:52:52,900 --> 00:52:55,640
Team P1 picked number 2.

1180
00:52:55,940 --> 00:52:58,580
Team P2 picked number 4.

1181
00:52:58,910 --> 00:53:01,480
Team P3 picked number 1.

1182
00:53:01,610 --> 00:53:04,120
Team C picked number three.

1183
00:53:04,750 --> 00:53:09,320
(Round 5's playing order)

1184
00:53:09,750 --> 00:53:11,020
Jin Ho, let's have a chat.

1185
00:53:11,020 --> 00:53:12,060
Okay.

1186
00:53:13,390 --> 00:53:16,390
We can all go to our room
and talk in private.

1187
00:53:16,390 --> 00:53:18,000
But there are other teams.

1188
00:53:18,000 --> 00:53:19,930
Jin Ho,

1189
00:53:20,430 --> 00:53:22,130
after Round Two,

1190
00:53:22,130 --> 00:53:24,700
- Team C earned points in Round Three.
- Yes.

1191
00:53:24,870 --> 00:53:28,270
Why did you go with Team P2
and not us in Round 4?

1192
00:53:28,770 --> 00:53:30,240
Team P2 and Team C don't have...

1193
00:53:30,240 --> 00:53:32,010
- any dictator cards.
- Right.

1194
00:53:32,010 --> 00:53:35,110
You could have teamed up with us, but...

1195
00:53:35,110 --> 00:53:36,780
- I'll tell you what happened.
- Okay.

1196
00:53:37,350 --> 00:53:39,150
- You had a dictator card.
- Yes.

1197
00:53:39,150 --> 00:53:40,250
We thought...

1198
00:53:40,250 --> 00:53:42,020
that you could get in the way
when we were trying to score,

1199
00:53:42,020 --> 00:53:43,990
so we went with the team
that had an assassin card.

1200
00:53:46,360 --> 00:53:47,360
Did you get it?

1201
00:53:47,630 --> 00:53:49,290
It was a bit...

1202
00:53:49,630 --> 00:53:52,600
Simply put, you didn't trust us.

1203
00:53:53,800 --> 00:53:57,340
I understand
that things changed in your team...

1204
00:53:57,500 --> 00:53:59,500
because of the elimination.

1205
00:53:59,500 --> 00:54:00,840
- I get that.
- Okay.

1206
00:54:01,270 --> 00:54:04,310
Team C was going 1st in Round 3,

1207
00:54:04,510 --> 00:54:06,980
so you wanted to score with them.

1208
00:54:06,980 --> 00:54:09,780
I get that too.

1209
00:54:09,780 --> 00:54:13,950
But why would you exclude us
even in the next round?

1210
00:54:13,950 --> 00:54:16,820
We actually feel...

1211
00:54:16,850 --> 00:54:20,860
You said that we excluded you,

1212
00:54:21,460 --> 00:54:24,700
but you and Ji Min...

1213
00:54:24,860 --> 00:54:26,230
didn't come to us...

1214
00:54:26,230 --> 00:54:28,230
to talk about the next plan.

1215
00:54:28,230 --> 00:54:30,200
You were only complaining,

1216
00:54:30,200 --> 00:54:33,070
so we couldn't really have a conversation.
And then...

1217
00:54:33,070 --> 00:54:34,840
It wasn't that we couldn't have
a conversation.

1218
00:54:34,840 --> 00:54:37,110
We didn't even have time to talk.

1219
00:54:37,110 --> 00:54:39,940
You were talking to other teams
at that moment.

1220
00:54:40,010 --> 00:54:43,780
To be honest, I didn't understand
Team P3's attitude.

1221
00:54:43,780 --> 00:54:45,580
It's like
the pot calling the kettle black.

1222
00:54:45,580 --> 00:54:47,620
Team P3 was actually the one
who betrayed us.

1223
00:54:47,920 --> 00:54:49,450
We rejected Team P2...

1224
00:54:49,450 --> 00:54:52,390
so that we could team up with Team P3.

1225
00:54:52,390 --> 00:54:54,630
He set the tone...

1226
00:54:54,630 --> 00:54:58,660
as if we were the public enemy...

1227
00:54:58,660 --> 00:55:02,200
and led the alliance of the three teams.

1228
00:55:02,200 --> 00:55:04,070
I could never understand that.

1229
00:55:05,970 --> 00:55:09,040
Jin Ho, why have you changed so much?

1230
00:55:09,210 --> 00:55:11,110
- Me? I'm the same.
- What?

1231
00:55:11,410 --> 00:55:14,080
- I'm just weaker.
- Stop trying so hard to survive.

1232
00:55:14,080 --> 00:55:15,810
Are you and I playing in Round Six?

1233
00:55:16,480 --> 00:55:17,820
You and I are in Round Six.

1234
00:55:17,820 --> 00:55:19,280
- Seong Beom is in Round Seven?
- Yes.

1235
00:55:19,420 --> 00:55:20,790
I'm going to kill you both.

1236
00:55:26,020 --> 00:55:29,860
I told you everything about my team,

1237
00:55:29,990 --> 00:55:32,560
and you just... Man.

1238
00:55:37,400 --> 00:55:40,810
You sometimes survive
and you sometimes don't.

1239
00:55:41,340 --> 00:55:44,110
After everything I've told you...

1240
00:55:46,010 --> 00:55:47,680
I can't believe this happened to me.

1241
00:55:47,850 --> 00:55:49,250
You surprised me, Jin Ho.

1242
00:55:49,550 --> 00:55:51,520
This is a nasty game, Sang Min.

1243
00:55:54,720 --> 00:55:57,360
Personally, I felt annoyed at that moment.

1244
00:55:58,560 --> 00:56:01,360
Things already happened,
and they were in danger.

1245
00:56:01,660 --> 00:56:04,230
You're supposed to accept that fast
and make a decision...

1246
00:56:04,230 --> 00:56:06,960
about how they should do better.
Instead of that,

1247
00:56:07,230 --> 00:56:09,630
he practically declared war on us.

1248
00:56:09,700 --> 00:56:12,170
He was like, "I'm going to get you.
You'll see."

1249
00:56:12,700 --> 00:56:14,010
That was their attitude,

1250
00:56:14,010 --> 00:56:16,010
so we couldn't communicate
with Team P1 anymore.

1251
00:56:16,570 --> 00:56:19,080
Team P1 was ostracized...

1252
00:56:19,510 --> 00:56:22,250
partly because of themselves.

1253
00:56:22,850 --> 00:56:26,150
The hidden item will be announced
before Round Five.

1254
00:56:26,720 --> 00:56:28,690
The hidden item of Running Mate is...

1255
00:56:30,760 --> 00:56:32,590
the rainbow 16 card.

1256
00:56:33,620 --> 00:56:35,230
The rainbow 16 card is...

1257
00:56:35,590 --> 00:56:38,800
a 16 card that can be used with any color.

1258
00:56:38,930 --> 00:56:42,500
You must state the color you want
when you use the item.

1259
00:56:42,500 --> 00:56:44,140
(Yellow)

1260
00:56:44,140 --> 00:56:46,200
The purchase limit is two.

1261
00:56:46,900 --> 00:56:49,740
You may have a strategy meeting
for Round Five.

1262
00:56:50,510 --> 00:56:52,280
Isn't this similar...

1263
00:56:52,280 --> 00:56:53,580
to the dictator card?

1264
00:56:53,780 --> 00:56:55,150
- Are we buying it?
- Yes.

1265
00:56:55,410 --> 00:56:56,780
Sang Min is in line.

1266
00:57:09,030 --> 00:57:10,530
You buy it. I'm broke.

1267
00:57:12,860 --> 00:57:15,100
I'm going to go inside and think about it.

1268
00:57:17,000 --> 00:57:19,870
We're in last place,
so spending 20,000 dollars is...

1269
00:57:19,870 --> 00:57:22,210
- Today,
- We only use that when necessary.

1270
00:57:22,210 --> 00:57:24,640
I'm fixated on Jin Ho and Seong Beom.

1271
00:57:24,780 --> 00:57:26,840
I'll take them down in Rounds 6 and 7.

1272
00:57:27,310 --> 00:57:28,750
What made you fixate on them?

1273
00:57:29,050 --> 00:57:30,350
Why, though?

1274
00:57:30,720 --> 00:57:32,120
- You're an alliance.
- I...

1275
00:57:32,680 --> 00:57:35,050
When we played downstairs,
I ran to them...

1276
00:57:35,050 --> 00:57:36,520
and told them all our cards.

1277
00:57:37,820 --> 00:57:40,390
We told them the cards that we'd play...

1278
00:57:40,390 --> 00:57:42,990
in Round 2 and Round 3.

1279
00:57:45,230 --> 00:57:46,430
And they did that.

1280
00:57:47,970 --> 00:57:51,400
I never thought Jin Ho would change.

1281
00:57:53,170 --> 00:57:55,310
That's when Sang Min came to me.

1282
00:57:55,310 --> 00:57:58,080
I thought, "What is he going to do
to make things more interesting?"

1283
00:57:58,240 --> 00:58:00,950
If you help me take out Jin Ho and him,

1284
00:58:01,650 --> 00:58:03,480
I'll...

1285
00:58:03,680 --> 00:58:05,580
- What will you do for me?
- Anything.

1286
00:58:05,780 --> 00:58:07,850
I don't mind going home tomorrow.

1287
00:58:08,550 --> 00:58:10,390
He was going to play in Rounds 6 and 7,

1288
00:58:10,390 --> 00:58:11,920
and I was also going in Round Six.

1289
00:58:12,060 --> 00:58:15,230
So, he asked if I could help him
take Jin Ho down.

1290
00:58:15,360 --> 00:58:18,100
It wasn't like we had
a solid alliance at the time.

1291
00:58:19,600 --> 00:58:20,800
I'll buy one.

1292
00:58:22,470 --> 00:58:25,340
Team P3, 20,000 dollars will be deducted.

1293
00:58:25,340 --> 00:58:26,440
(Team P3 buys a rainbow 16 card.)

1294
00:58:28,840 --> 00:58:30,070
What took you so long?

1295
00:58:30,310 --> 00:58:32,080
- You were just buying one.
- We had a whole conversation.

1296
00:58:39,150 --> 00:58:40,280
Give me one. I'll buy one.

1297
00:58:41,720 --> 00:58:44,690
Team P1, 20,000 dollars will be deducted.

1298
00:58:52,460 --> 00:58:53,460
It's so cold.

1299
00:59:14,990 --> 00:59:16,390
We became outcasts all of a sudden.

1300
00:59:17,960 --> 00:59:20,830
It felt like all three teams were talking
without us.

1301
00:59:21,190 --> 00:59:25,330
Why do I always get ostracized?

1302
00:59:25,660 --> 00:59:29,600
Why am I an outcast from the start?

1303
00:59:30,600 --> 00:59:33,040
I thought Team P1 was...

1304
00:59:34,240 --> 00:59:35,470
off to a rough start.

1305
00:59:35,510 --> 00:59:36,510
Hey.

1306
00:59:37,340 --> 00:59:38,340
I mean...

1307
00:59:38,340 --> 00:59:39,640
(Team P1's room)

1308
00:59:40,780 --> 00:59:42,980
- Darn it.
- We should have gone with Team P2.

1309
00:59:42,980 --> 00:59:45,980
I don't know why we were obsessed...

1310
00:59:46,150 --> 00:59:49,250
with teaming up with Team P3.

1311
00:59:50,190 --> 00:59:53,890
I thought Team P2 would have been
a much better ally.

1312
00:59:54,090 --> 00:59:56,160
I felt so betrayed by Team P3.

1313
00:59:56,290 --> 00:59:58,360
I don't really understand
what Team P3 is saying.

1314
00:59:58,360 --> 01:00:01,700
They're just finding excuses
so that they can be number one.

1315
01:00:01,700 --> 01:00:03,830
In Round Four,

1316
01:00:04,100 --> 01:00:06,100
they went so far as to use
the reverse card...

1317
01:00:06,100 --> 01:00:08,940
to exclude us and team up with them.
That makes zero sense.

1318
01:00:09,140 --> 01:00:10,470
I asked him why he did that,

1319
01:00:10,470 --> 01:00:12,440
and he said he teamed up with them
since they had the assassin card...

1320
01:00:12,440 --> 01:00:14,280
because he was worried that we'd stop
them with the dictator card.

1321
01:00:14,480 --> 01:00:17,380
- That's all a lie.
- He was just doubting us.

1322
01:00:17,380 --> 01:00:19,450
No, it's a downright lie.
They just had to...

1323
01:00:19,450 --> 01:00:21,790
be in the lead from Round Three
to play it safe.

1324
01:00:22,150 --> 01:00:23,590
That's the choice they're making.

1325
01:00:23,590 --> 01:00:25,420
We have to stop obsessing over them.

1326
01:00:25,820 --> 01:00:27,630
We played the game so well,

1327
01:00:27,630 --> 01:00:30,760
but our alliance strategy was
a total failure.

1328
01:00:30,800 --> 01:00:32,800
I started having a mental breakdown...

1329
01:00:32,900 --> 01:00:35,070
and felt so betrayed.

1330
01:00:36,630 --> 01:00:37,800
Hold on.

1331
01:00:39,600 --> 01:00:41,010
What should we do, then?

1332
01:00:41,810 --> 01:00:44,410
In this round,

1333
01:00:47,240 --> 01:00:48,680
I want to gamble.

1334
01:00:50,010 --> 01:00:52,250
- With the 16 card?
- No.

1335
01:00:53,320 --> 01:00:54,320
How?

1336
01:00:54,750 --> 01:00:56,420
Winning ten points without a Mate.

1337
01:00:57,590 --> 01:01:00,120
You get an extra 2 points
in Rounds 5 and 6.

1338
01:01:00,420 --> 01:01:04,400
You can win 12 points
if you successfully expect 0 wins.

1339
01:01:04,500 --> 01:01:05,700
If that happened,

1340
01:01:05,700 --> 01:01:09,500
we could get ahead of Team P3.

1341
01:01:09,600 --> 01:01:11,570
If this fails,

1342
01:01:11,570 --> 01:01:14,240
there's a high chance
that we'll place last.

1343
01:01:14,770 --> 01:01:17,880
But this isn't the time to avoid it,
worrying about placing last.

1344
01:01:17,880 --> 01:01:20,140
We have to do whatever we can
to place first.

1345
01:01:21,010 --> 01:01:23,810
That means I have to bet zero wins.

1346
01:01:25,450 --> 01:01:27,720
I don't think Team P3 can bet
0 wins this time.

1347
01:01:28,390 --> 01:01:31,920
- Because we have a dictator card.
- Right.

1348
01:01:31,920 --> 01:01:35,990
Tae Gyun came up
with the zero-win strategy.

1349
01:01:36,090 --> 01:01:37,860
It's not easy to pull this off...

1350
01:01:37,860 --> 01:01:40,060
when those three teams are
playing together.

1351
01:01:40,770 --> 01:01:43,170
Nevertheless, we have to try.

1352
01:01:43,300 --> 01:01:46,670
We have to predict
when they'll get the dictator card.

1353
01:01:46,940 --> 01:01:49,140
I don't think they'll get it
in this round.

1354
01:01:49,140 --> 01:01:50,440
- Right?
- Never.

1355
01:01:50,810 --> 01:01:52,110
- So...
- Because...

1356
01:01:52,580 --> 01:01:55,610
I told Jin Ho and Seong Beom
that I was coming for them.

1357
01:01:55,610 --> 01:01:57,280
- You're playing in the last round.
- Yes.

1358
01:01:57,350 --> 01:01:58,950
Then, they'll bring that
when they play against you,

1359
01:01:58,950 --> 01:02:00,920
not Ji Min.

1360
01:02:01,020 --> 01:02:03,050
I said all those things to them,

1361
01:02:03,050 --> 01:02:04,620
so I'm sure they're focused on me.

1362
01:02:05,060 --> 01:02:06,890
They're focused on you and me.

1363
01:02:07,890 --> 01:02:08,990
Is it all right if we fail?

1364
01:02:08,990 --> 01:02:10,490
- Of course.
- I don't mind.

1365
01:02:11,360 --> 01:02:13,660
"You're going to bully us? Fine."

1366
01:02:14,130 --> 01:02:16,100
"We'll play by ourselves and win."

1367
01:02:17,330 --> 01:02:18,670
- See you.
- Bye.

1368
01:02:20,940 --> 01:02:23,310
Players for Round Five,

1369
01:02:23,410 --> 01:02:25,280
please gather in the main hall.

1370
01:02:29,050 --> 01:02:30,150
How's your team doing?

1371
01:02:30,980 --> 01:02:32,450
- Pretty well.
- Really?

1372
01:02:32,450 --> 01:02:34,590
Man, you've got some pride.

1373
01:02:34,590 --> 01:02:37,560
The cast of the first season has
a strong bond.

1374
01:02:37,620 --> 01:02:40,060
But things aren't so romantic right now.

1375
01:02:41,530 --> 01:02:43,190
No, we always keep it romantic.

1376
01:02:43,190 --> 01:02:45,900
- Really? It doesn't look like it.
- Yes.

1377
01:02:46,930 --> 01:02:49,270
If we manage to bet zero wins and win,

1378
01:02:49,270 --> 01:02:52,200
we might turn the tables.

1379
01:02:52,200 --> 01:02:53,800
We have no room to retreat.

1380
01:02:53,800 --> 01:02:54,910
We only advance.

1381
01:02:54,970 --> 01:02:57,840
We will begin Round Five
of the card battle.

1382
01:02:59,680 --> 01:03:00,910
Hye Seon,

1383
01:03:00,910 --> 01:03:03,850
predict the expected wins,
pick the master color, and make your bet.

1384
01:03:04,250 --> 01:03:05,550
Expected wins,

1385
01:03:08,420 --> 01:03:09,450
zero.

1386
01:03:12,760 --> 01:03:15,530
I was like, "What's going on?"

1387
01:03:16,260 --> 01:03:18,800
I didn't think
they'd bet zero wins this time...

1388
01:03:18,800 --> 01:03:21,900
because they knew we had a dictator card.

1389
01:03:22,030 --> 01:03:24,240
But they did,

1390
01:03:24,540 --> 01:03:27,070
so I thought, "They've lost their minds."

1391
01:03:27,640 --> 01:03:31,180
We were the 1st player in Round 5,

1392
01:03:31,310 --> 01:03:33,940
so we really needed points.

1393
01:03:33,980 --> 01:03:35,710
Our strategy was...

1394
01:03:35,710 --> 01:03:37,780
to bet zero wins
and designate Team C as our Mate...

1395
01:03:37,780 --> 01:03:40,890
so that we could win six points each.

1396
01:03:41,120 --> 01:03:43,390
(Round 5 strategy meeting)

1397
01:03:43,390 --> 01:03:45,860
We're 1st, and Team P1 is 2nd.

1398
01:03:46,890 --> 01:03:48,060
Then, we...

1399
01:03:48,060 --> 01:03:49,530
- Who's going third?
- Team C.

1400
01:03:49,730 --> 01:03:53,360
Team C has to be our Mate
and win points this time.

1401
01:03:54,700 --> 01:03:55,830
- Team C and us?
- Yes.

1402
01:03:55,830 --> 01:03:57,100
We'll have to talk to Team C.

1403
01:03:57,100 --> 01:04:00,200
I think we can bet zero wins again.

1404
01:04:00,770 --> 01:04:04,010
I didn't think it'd be easy to get 0 wins
from Round 5 to Round 8...

1405
01:04:04,010 --> 01:04:06,880
because everyone will be keeping
each other in check...

1406
01:04:06,880 --> 01:04:08,810
and we won't have that many cards left.

1407
01:04:09,080 --> 01:04:10,980
But if we bet zero wins...

1408
01:04:11,350 --> 01:04:13,480
and succeed at least once
when we play first,

1409
01:04:13,480 --> 01:04:15,350
I thought we'd have the upper hand.

1410
01:04:15,990 --> 01:04:17,350
Team P1 has the dictator card.

1411
01:04:17,820 --> 01:04:19,320
And there's no assassin card.

1412
01:04:20,120 --> 01:04:21,830
The only problem we had...

1413
01:04:21,990 --> 01:04:23,730
during the meeting was...

1414
01:04:23,890 --> 01:04:25,600
that we were out of assassin cards.

1415
01:04:26,060 --> 01:04:27,970
How should we counter the dictator card,
then?

1416
01:04:27,970 --> 01:04:31,000
If Team P1 submits the dictator card,

1417
01:04:31,000 --> 01:04:34,870
that will be the end
of our zero-win strategy.

1418
01:04:35,170 --> 01:04:37,580
We can't really protect ourselves
if they have it.

1419
01:04:37,580 --> 01:04:40,340
We can.

1420
01:04:40,340 --> 01:04:44,180
We can take our dictator card
and give it to our Mate,

1421
01:04:44,520 --> 01:04:46,220
and the Mate will keep playing first.

1422
01:04:46,450 --> 01:04:48,590
But I had backup plans.

1423
01:04:49,020 --> 01:04:52,060
My idea was that we could stop
the dictator with another dictator.

1424
01:04:52,060 --> 01:04:53,320
The DD strategy.

1425
01:04:53,960 --> 01:04:56,060
When there are two dictator cards,

1426
01:04:56,060 --> 01:04:59,200
the first one that was submitted has
superiority.

1427
01:04:59,830 --> 01:05:02,770
If the Mate wins a set,

1428
01:05:02,770 --> 01:05:06,570
that team will play first
from Set 2 to Set 8.

1429
01:05:06,900 --> 01:05:10,410
Then, the Mate will submit
the dictator card first,

1430
01:05:10,540 --> 01:05:12,580
so they can still get zero wins,

1431
01:05:12,580 --> 01:05:14,210
even if the Master submits
a dictator card.

1432
01:05:15,580 --> 01:05:18,280
We had formed a group of cards
that could stop the dictator card...

1433
01:05:18,280 --> 01:05:19,520
without an assassin card.

1434
01:05:21,220 --> 01:05:22,990
I know all the rules.

1435
01:05:23,220 --> 01:05:24,290
- That's genius.
- It's all in my head.

1436
01:05:24,290 --> 01:05:25,560
The anti-P1 alliance.

1437
01:05:25,560 --> 01:05:28,430
I offered to give Team C all the points,
and everyone was okay with it.

1438
01:05:28,660 --> 01:05:30,190
Team C and our team will get
six points each.

1439
01:05:31,230 --> 01:05:32,900
The master color is yellow.

1440
01:05:33,260 --> 01:05:35,430
You've bet on yellow, zero wins.

1441
01:05:35,430 --> 01:05:36,770
(Team P3's Hye Seon bet
on yellow and 0 wins.)

1442
01:05:37,070 --> 01:05:40,400
Hye Seon bet zero wins
and became the Master.

1443
01:05:40,400 --> 01:05:42,110
The bet is over.

1444
01:05:45,980 --> 01:05:49,110
Please submit the card you want
to give to Kyoung Hoon.

1445
01:05:49,880 --> 01:05:53,080
Please submit the card you want
to give to Ji Min.

1446
01:05:53,280 --> 01:05:56,450
Please submit the card you want
to give to Sung Joo.

1447
01:05:57,590 --> 01:05:59,490
All cards have been exchanged.

1448
01:06:00,090 --> 01:06:02,290
Hye Seon, do you wish to name a Mate?

1449
01:06:02,290 --> 01:06:04,560
Yes, number ten.

1450
01:06:04,660 --> 01:06:08,170
The 1st one to submit 10 becomes the Mate.

1451
01:06:08,170 --> 01:06:11,000
The first set will start with the Master.

1452
01:06:11,500 --> 01:06:13,770
Card two in green has been submitted.

1453
01:06:14,200 --> 01:06:17,410
Ji Min, card 16 in green
has been submitted.

1454
01:06:18,010 --> 01:06:20,410
Kyoung Hoon has submitted card ten...

1455
01:06:20,410 --> 01:06:21,910
and became the Mate.

1456
01:06:22,880 --> 01:06:24,980
Card five in green has been submitted.

1457
01:06:25,980 --> 01:06:28,190
Kyoung Hoon has won Set One.

1458
01:06:29,190 --> 01:06:31,490
Kyoung Hoon has won Set Two.

1459
01:06:31,660 --> 01:06:33,890
Kyoung Hoon has won Set Three.

1460
01:06:33,890 --> 01:06:36,190
Kyoung Hoon has won Set Four.

1461
01:06:36,190 --> 01:06:37,900
Kyoung Hoon has won Set Five.

1462
01:06:38,400 --> 01:06:40,830
Kyoung Hoon has won Set Six.

1463
01:06:40,830 --> 01:06:42,300
Kyoung Hoon has won Set Seven.

1464
01:06:42,670 --> 01:06:44,130
Kyoung Hoon has won Set Eight.

1465
01:06:48,010 --> 01:06:50,570
Team P3 has successfully bet on 0 wins.

1466
01:06:50,570 --> 01:06:52,380
(Team P3 successfully predicted 0 wins.)

1467
01:06:58,720 --> 01:07:00,990
I have no idea what Team C is thinking.

1468
01:07:00,990 --> 01:07:04,690
Team C helped Team P3
despite getting stabbed in the back.

1469
01:07:05,060 --> 01:07:07,660
Who knows what kind of a deal they made?

1470
01:07:07,660 --> 01:07:10,030
But if he did that
without anything in return,

1471
01:07:10,430 --> 01:07:12,160
he should retire from survival shows.

1472
01:07:12,630 --> 01:07:13,930
Why did he even join this show?

1473
01:07:16,100 --> 01:07:18,440
Team P3 and its running mate,
Team Challenger,

1474
01:07:18,440 --> 01:07:20,400
each get six points.

1475
01:07:20,400 --> 01:07:21,470
(Teams P3 and C earn 6 points each.)

1476
01:07:22,010 --> 01:07:26,880
(Running Mate score status)

1477
01:07:27,810 --> 01:07:29,780
That bunch of traitors.

1478
01:07:30,050 --> 01:07:31,380
(Team P1's room)

1479
01:07:31,380 --> 01:07:33,250
Team P3 won 0 times.

1480
01:07:33,750 --> 01:07:35,450
- Right.
- How frustrating, really.

1481
01:07:35,450 --> 01:07:36,590
It can't be helped.

1482
01:07:37,320 --> 01:07:39,020
The teams are giving points to each other
in turns.

1483
01:07:40,420 --> 01:07:43,090
Gosh, we're now even behind Team C.

1484
01:07:43,960 --> 01:07:44,960
We didn't come in last.

1485
01:07:45,460 --> 01:07:46,900
- Thanks.
- You're right.

1486
01:07:47,330 --> 01:07:49,030
It was a win-win. A great one at that.

1487
01:07:49,270 --> 01:07:50,530
- Thank you.
- No problem.

1488
01:07:50,530 --> 01:07:51,940
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1489
01:07:54,840 --> 01:07:57,170
- Did it go well? 11 points for us?
- It went smoothly.

1490
01:07:57,170 --> 01:07:59,280
- Is it 11 points?
- Yes, 11 points.

1491
01:07:59,280 --> 01:08:00,280
- It's 11 points?
- Team P3 has 21 points,

1492
01:08:00,280 --> 01:08:01,350
Team P1 has 10 points,

1493
01:08:01,510 --> 01:08:03,680
Team C has 11 points,
and Team P2 has 10 points.

1494
01:08:03,680 --> 01:08:05,520
- Right. 2nd place.
- We're now in 2nd place.

1495
01:08:07,890 --> 01:08:09,390
Are you free to talk?

1496
01:08:09,390 --> 01:08:10,550
- Of course.
- Or...

1497
01:08:10,550 --> 01:08:12,090
Does your team have to discuss something?

1498
01:08:12,090 --> 01:08:13,620
No, we don't. Come on in.

1499
01:08:13,620 --> 01:08:15,730
What does this mean?
Basically, let's keep this going.

1500
01:08:15,730 --> 01:08:16,890
Help Team P3 maintain 1st place.

1501
01:08:16,890 --> 01:08:18,800
We'll help you avoid coming in last.

1502
01:08:18,800 --> 01:08:21,570
As the alliance could fall apart anytime,

1503
01:08:21,630 --> 01:08:23,400
we should keep this momentum going.

1504
01:08:23,770 --> 01:08:24,770
- Well...
- Hold on.

1505
01:08:24,770 --> 01:08:26,800
If it were us...
If we were Team P1, what would we do?

1506
01:08:26,800 --> 01:08:27,810
Team P1 is currently in runner-up.

1507
01:08:27,810 --> 01:08:29,470
For Team P1 to turn the tables around,

1508
01:08:29,470 --> 01:08:31,910
it would have to predict zero wins
as a single.

1509
01:08:31,910 --> 01:08:35,250
But what if they don't call zero wins?

1510
01:08:35,250 --> 01:08:37,780
I doubt they will do that.
The risk is too big.

1511
01:08:37,780 --> 01:08:39,280
If they predict zero wins
without a running mate,

1512
01:08:39,280 --> 01:08:40,320
they might lose points.

1513
01:08:40,320 --> 01:08:43,590
There's no need
to think with certainty that...

1514
01:08:44,390 --> 01:08:46,320
they're after first place.

1515
01:08:46,320 --> 01:08:48,430
If Team P1 were to give up...

1516
01:08:48,430 --> 01:08:49,960
and think first place...

1517
01:08:49,960 --> 01:08:51,100
- is out the window...
- Then...

1518
01:08:51,100 --> 01:08:53,060
If the three teams team up,

1519
01:08:53,060 --> 01:08:55,470
we could avoid getting
the winning predictions.

1520
01:08:55,470 --> 01:08:59,570
Team P2...
We should talk to Team P2 about that.

1521
01:08:59,570 --> 01:09:01,240
He went to invite them over.

1522
01:09:01,240 --> 01:09:02,540
We should drop by instead.

1523
01:09:03,270 --> 01:09:04,340
(Team P1's room)

1524
01:09:04,340 --> 01:09:05,840
We can't get first place.

1525
01:09:07,240 --> 01:09:10,210
But to secure 2nd place,
we must team up with Team P2.

1526
01:09:11,180 --> 01:09:13,320
Say that Team P3 and Team C
keep their alliance,

1527
01:09:13,580 --> 01:09:16,950
and Team P2 and Team P1
play independently.

1528
01:09:17,090 --> 01:09:19,820
The alliance team
would have the upper hand.

1529
01:09:20,320 --> 01:09:23,260
We must talk to Team P2 about it.

1530
01:09:23,430 --> 01:09:26,260
"We'll help you take first place."

1531
01:09:26,260 --> 01:09:27,460
"Are you willing to join us?"

1532
01:09:27,460 --> 01:09:28,800
They wouldn't turn us down.

1533
01:09:28,800 --> 01:09:30,530
In the current situation,
they can't come in first place.

1534
01:09:30,530 --> 01:09:32,100
In the end,

1535
01:09:32,100 --> 01:09:34,370
we will help Team P2 take 1st place...

1536
01:09:34,370 --> 01:09:35,440
while we finish 2nd place...

1537
01:09:35,440 --> 01:09:38,140
and get help from them later on.

1538
01:09:39,210 --> 01:09:40,410
I'll go make a deal with them.

1539
01:09:40,410 --> 01:09:41,410
With Team P2?

1540
01:09:44,110 --> 01:09:45,380
Could we chat for a bit?

1541
01:09:45,380 --> 01:09:46,480
(Team P2 has become
a strategic stronghold.)

1542
01:09:46,480 --> 01:09:47,480
Yes.

1543
01:09:47,780 --> 01:09:50,850
Would you be in
if we helped you come in...

1544
01:09:50,850 --> 01:09:52,660
- first place?
- Help us come in first place?

1545
01:09:52,660 --> 01:09:55,690
- Listen. I'm bringing this up because...
- Yes?

1546
01:09:55,690 --> 01:09:58,430
we're all wrapped around Team P3's finger,

1547
01:09:58,430 --> 01:10:00,630
- and it's annoying.
- Are they getting on your nerves?

1548
01:10:01,000 --> 01:10:02,000
You mean the alliance?

1549
01:10:02,430 --> 01:10:05,170
- Here's a brief explanation of our plan.
- Okay.

1550
01:10:05,640 --> 01:10:07,670
In the next round, we will...

1551
01:10:08,070 --> 01:10:09,310
Six points. Eight points.

1552
01:10:09,510 --> 01:10:10,770
We'll call six wins.

1553
01:10:11,180 --> 01:10:12,380
- Then...
- Six wins,

1554
01:10:12,380 --> 01:10:13,580
- and they get two points each, right?
- Correct.

1555
01:10:15,410 --> 01:10:16,610
By not getting six wins.

1556
01:10:17,180 --> 01:10:18,180
- No.
- Right.

1557
01:10:20,180 --> 01:10:24,020
In the next round, we'll call six wins...

1558
01:10:24,020 --> 01:10:25,360
and give two points to the other teams.

1559
01:10:25,720 --> 01:10:26,790
In the round after that,

1560
01:10:27,120 --> 01:10:30,390
if Team C and Team P3 team up...

1561
01:10:30,390 --> 01:10:31,960
and use the zero-win strategy,

1562
01:10:31,960 --> 01:10:33,760
we will use the dictator card.

1563
01:10:34,230 --> 01:10:36,230
Those two teams will lose points from it,

1564
01:10:36,230 --> 01:10:38,200
which is the same as us gaining points.

1565
01:10:38,800 --> 01:10:41,610
Team P2 goes first in the last round,
right?

1566
01:10:41,610 --> 01:10:43,170
With zero wins,
both of us will gain points.

1567
01:10:43,570 --> 01:10:44,780
To make us come in first place,

1568
01:10:44,780 --> 01:10:46,940
you must not help others.

1569
01:10:46,940 --> 01:10:48,480
For us to come in second.

1570
01:10:48,480 --> 01:10:49,480
- I see.
- But...

1571
01:10:49,980 --> 01:10:52,720
- Here's where we stand right now.
- Okay.

1572
01:10:53,220 --> 01:10:55,250
- Either way, Seung Jin is the one...
- Yes?

1573
01:10:55,250 --> 01:10:57,850
- who makes the final call.
- I see.

1574
01:10:57,850 --> 01:10:58,960
Seung Jin is taking part...

1575
01:10:58,960 --> 01:11:00,460
- But...
- in the Deathmatch.

1576
01:11:00,820 --> 01:11:03,730
But what's your goal?

1577
01:11:04,290 --> 01:11:05,400
Us...

1578
01:11:05,530 --> 01:11:08,670
To be frank, our goal isn't to win.

1579
01:11:08,670 --> 01:11:10,630
- No, make it your goal.
- Why not?

1580
01:11:11,070 --> 01:11:12,270
We'll give you a hand.

1581
01:11:12,800 --> 01:11:15,310
Honestly, they're right.

1582
01:11:15,570 --> 01:11:18,840
We've helped Team P3 3 times already.

1583
01:11:18,840 --> 01:11:20,880
Why should we help them again?

1584
01:11:21,140 --> 01:11:22,710
Look, here's what I'm concerned about.

1585
01:11:22,910 --> 01:11:24,450
"Okay, so you'll help us win?"

1586
01:11:24,450 --> 01:11:25,980
"Let's do this."

1587
01:11:25,980 --> 01:11:27,950
But if we get stabbed in the back again...

1588
01:11:27,950 --> 01:11:29,120
- By us?
- By us?

1589
01:11:29,120 --> 01:11:31,660
By anyone. It could be the other teams.

1590
01:11:31,920 --> 01:11:35,560
If that's how you put it...

1591
01:11:35,560 --> 01:11:38,960
We have no idea
what the other teams are up to.

1592
01:11:38,960 --> 01:11:40,600
Even so, it's either going for it...

1593
01:11:40,600 --> 01:11:42,870
with the 10 to 20 percent chance
of winning...

1594
01:11:42,870 --> 01:11:44,770
or just letting Team P3 win.

1595
01:11:44,770 --> 01:11:47,240
If they want to win for sure,

1596
01:11:47,240 --> 01:11:49,370
they'd be able to if you became...

1597
01:11:49,370 --> 01:11:50,570
a double agent.

1598
01:11:55,110 --> 01:11:56,910
They think we're complete fools.

1599
01:11:56,910 --> 01:12:00,980
What got me furious
after hearing the term "double agent" was,

1600
01:12:01,220 --> 01:12:04,290
is it impossible to play games
without betraying, spying, and so forth?

1601
01:12:04,450 --> 01:12:06,460
Why does everyone like agents
and betrayals?

1602
01:12:06,460 --> 01:12:07,860
And what's with a double agent?

1603
01:12:07,860 --> 01:12:10,760
To them, betrayal is a given.

1604
01:12:10,760 --> 01:12:13,300
How can we play games with such people?

1605
01:12:13,530 --> 01:12:15,800
Get fooled once, that's a mistake.

1606
01:12:15,800 --> 01:12:17,430
Get fooled again,
and you're an accomplice.

1607
01:12:18,040 --> 01:12:21,270
I don't know what you think,

1608
01:12:21,270 --> 01:12:22,970
but I hate spying and things like that.

1609
01:12:23,370 --> 01:12:27,240
That's the main element
that makes a game boring.

1610
01:12:28,280 --> 01:12:30,450
Jin Hyeong has changed a lot.

1611
01:12:31,380 --> 01:12:33,850
But if a person changes too much,
they die.

1612
01:12:34,450 --> 01:12:35,990
From what I see, Jin Hyeong is here...

1613
01:12:35,990 --> 01:12:37,920
to clean up his image.

1614
01:12:37,920 --> 01:12:39,860
But why come on this show...

1615
01:12:40,560 --> 01:12:42,160
to do that?

1616
01:12:42,260 --> 01:12:44,230
Go do volunteer work or something.

1617
01:12:44,230 --> 01:12:45,660
No betraying?

1618
01:12:45,660 --> 01:12:47,700
He's betrayed everyone until now.

1619
01:12:48,570 --> 01:12:51,470
How is helping the team win betrayal?

1620
01:12:51,740 --> 01:12:55,870
That's when I realized the members
returned to the show even dumber.

1621
01:12:56,240 --> 01:13:00,740
So, in short,
you're going to finish in second place?

1622
01:13:00,740 --> 01:13:01,910
- Yes.
- Okay.

1623
01:13:01,910 --> 01:13:03,780
- We're done here.
- Finish in second place?

1624
01:13:03,780 --> 01:13:06,180
- Okay.
- We're done here.

1625
01:13:06,180 --> 01:13:07,520
- Our goal is to come in second.
- Okay.

1626
01:13:07,520 --> 01:13:08,950
- Okay.
- All right then.

1627
01:13:08,950 --> 01:13:10,750
- Think about it.
- Got it.

1628
01:13:10,750 --> 01:13:11,820
(Failed to get Team P1's cooperation)

1629
01:13:11,820 --> 01:13:13,720
- It was a question and nothing more.
- Right.

1630
01:13:13,720 --> 01:13:14,730
- Yes.
- Yes.

1631
01:13:15,560 --> 01:13:19,130
Team P2 will just finish in 2nd place.

1632
01:13:25,740 --> 01:13:26,740
Okay.

1633
01:13:27,000 --> 01:13:31,110
What's the plan
behind giving up on winning?

1634
01:13:32,410 --> 01:13:33,840
We're here to win.

1635
01:13:35,150 --> 01:13:36,250
Supporting the first place...

1636
01:13:36,250 --> 01:13:38,580
to get second place is understandable.

1637
01:13:39,720 --> 01:13:41,320
But for the first place...

1638
01:13:41,320 --> 01:13:44,420
to go on bended knees to the second place
and tell them to win...

1639
01:13:44,760 --> 01:13:46,690
is a plan I don't get at all.

1640
01:13:47,590 --> 01:13:49,490
It's just stupid.

1641
01:13:50,030 --> 01:13:52,500
They're like children scared of tomorrow
and giving up on today.

1642
01:13:53,730 --> 01:13:55,430
That's what drove me mad.

1643
01:13:55,870 --> 01:13:59,300
At that moment, my mind...

1644
01:14:00,440 --> 01:14:01,970
started going blank.

1645
01:14:03,440 --> 01:14:07,080
Players for Round Six,
please gather in the main hall.

1646
01:14:08,680 --> 01:14:11,680
We will begin Round Six
of the card battle.

1647
01:14:12,420 --> 01:14:13,750
Starting with Lee Sang Min,

1648
01:14:13,750 --> 01:14:16,720
predict the expected wins,
pick the master color, and make your bet.

1649
01:14:18,090 --> 01:14:19,360
Blue, zero wins.

1650
01:14:19,790 --> 01:14:22,030
Lee Sang Min has bet on blue, zero wins.

1651
01:14:22,460 --> 01:14:23,460
Hold on.

1652
01:14:23,960 --> 01:14:26,800
Zero wins? Why zero wins?

1653
01:14:27,930 --> 01:14:31,130
Is there a bigger picture
that I'm not seeing?

1654
01:14:32,770 --> 01:14:35,310
Blue is the master color of this round.

1655
01:14:35,640 --> 01:14:39,440
"What?" I was quite surprised
when he bet on zero wins.

1656
01:14:39,610 --> 01:14:41,380
Even so, he wants to win.

1657
01:14:41,380 --> 01:14:42,480
He's taking a gamble.

1658
01:14:44,380 --> 01:14:47,350
There was a need
to shake up the other teams,

1659
01:14:47,350 --> 01:14:49,790
even if it was just
the slightest possibility.

1660
01:14:50,350 --> 01:14:51,620
Either way, we're going first.

1661
01:14:51,620 --> 01:14:54,220
Bet on zero wins.

1662
01:14:55,060 --> 01:14:56,930
If it works out, then it's all good.

1663
01:14:57,360 --> 01:14:59,360
If not, take the lowest cards.

1664
01:15:00,160 --> 01:15:01,500
- Zero wins?
- Yes.

1665
01:15:02,000 --> 01:15:03,500
There's no turning back now.

1666
01:15:04,070 --> 01:15:06,700
As a solo player,
the zero-win plan is our only choice.

1667
01:15:06,940 --> 01:15:08,970
Say that we fail.

1668
01:15:08,970 --> 01:15:11,480
Still, the benefits of finishing first
and second are very different.

1669
01:15:12,580 --> 01:15:15,150
Kim Kyoung Hoon, YunB, and Hong Jin Ho.

1670
01:15:15,150 --> 01:15:18,050
Please submit the card
you want to give to the Master.

1671
01:15:27,220 --> 01:15:28,960
Must we use our heads to win?

1672
01:15:35,230 --> 01:15:36,300
In this case...

1673
01:15:36,830 --> 01:15:38,470
What should I give the Master? This one?

1674
01:15:39,740 --> 01:15:40,840
- This one?
- Yes.

1675
01:15:40,840 --> 01:15:42,140
- This one.
- Got it.

1676
01:15:42,140 --> 01:15:43,540
All three teamed up.

1677
01:15:43,540 --> 01:15:44,540
They made it obvious.

1678
01:15:44,880 --> 01:15:47,340
But to think
that's how they played the game until now.

1679
01:15:48,250 --> 01:15:49,410
Goodness.

1680
01:15:50,110 --> 01:15:53,420
I bet this will go down in history.

1681
01:15:53,880 --> 01:15:54,890
I mean this alliance.

1682
01:15:55,090 --> 01:15:59,420
The reason for the alliance
was so as not to come in first place.

1683
01:16:00,090 --> 01:16:03,390
Is it some kind of pseudo-religion?
Is there a sect leader?

1684
01:16:04,260 --> 01:16:07,060
No, that's the one. I'm sorry.

1685
01:16:08,700 --> 01:16:10,630
All cards have been exchanged.

1686
01:16:11,640 --> 01:16:13,870
Lee Sang Min, do you wish to name a Mate?

1687
01:16:14,070 --> 01:16:15,070
No.

1688
01:16:15,110 --> 01:16:17,040
No Mate was named.

1689
01:16:19,380 --> 01:16:22,550
Set One will start with the Master.

1690
01:16:24,010 --> 01:16:26,180
Lee Sang Min, submit a card.

1691
01:16:27,080 --> 01:16:28,720
All my cards are bad.

1692
01:16:37,130 --> 01:16:38,760
(Hong Jin Ho, Lee Sang Min,
Kim Kyoung Hoon, YunB)

1693
01:16:38,760 --> 01:16:41,200
Card two in blue has been submitted.

1694
01:16:41,200 --> 01:16:43,630
The lead color of this set is blue.

1695
01:16:44,470 --> 01:16:46,840
Kim Kyoung Hoon, submit a card.

1696
01:16:46,840 --> 01:16:53,440
(Hong Jin Ho, Lee Sang Min,
Kim Kyoung Hoon, YunB)

1697
01:16:53,440 --> 01:16:55,050
(Hong Jin Ho, Lee Sang Min,
Kim Kyoung Hoon, YunB)

1698
01:16:55,050 --> 01:16:57,250
Card one in blue has been submitted.

1699
01:16:57,250 --> 01:17:02,690
(Hong Jin Ho, Lee Sang Min,
Kim Kyoung Hoon, YunB)

1700
01:17:02,690 --> 01:17:04,820
YunB, submit a card.

1701
01:17:04,820 --> 01:17:07,660
(Hong Jin Ho, Lee Sang Min,
Kim Kyoung Hoon, YunB)

1702
01:17:07,660 --> 01:17:10,030
Card one in red has been submitted.

1703
01:17:10,760 --> 01:17:12,900
Hong Jin Ho, submit a card.

1704
01:17:12,900 --> 01:17:14,200
(Failed to predict 0 wins
if Hong Jin Ho submits a low card)

1705
01:17:15,370 --> 01:17:16,870
Blue is the first card, right?

1706
01:17:17,130 --> 01:17:18,940
Yes, if you have one.

1707
01:17:18,940 --> 01:17:19,940
Got it.

1708
01:17:19,940 --> 01:17:25,240
(Hong Jin Ho, Lee Sang Min,
Kim Kyoung Hoon, YunB)

1709
01:17:25,240 --> 01:17:27,510
Card two in blue has been submitted.

1710
01:17:27,510 --> 01:17:30,910
(Hong Jin Ho, Lee Sang Min,
Kim Kyoung Hoon, YunB)

1711
01:17:30,910 --> 01:17:33,350
Lee Sang Min has won Set One.

1712
01:17:33,350 --> 01:17:37,320
(With the same 2-card,
the 1st player and Master wins.)

1713
01:17:40,960 --> 01:17:44,760
Back then,
the game was rolling according to plan.

1714
01:17:45,000 --> 01:17:47,900
These two will cover
both the high and the low.

1715
01:17:47,900 --> 01:17:49,670
They will have red and green.

1716
01:17:49,670 --> 01:17:51,570
A strategy when Team P1 is 1st.

1717
01:17:51,570 --> 01:17:54,470
The 8-win plan, 6-win plan,
and 0-win plan.

1718
01:17:54,470 --> 01:17:56,610
We were to check all the cards we had,

1719
01:17:56,610 --> 01:17:57,940
come up with ways to counterattack,

1720
01:17:57,940 --> 01:18:01,240
and prevent every possible scenario.

1721
01:18:01,610 --> 01:18:03,180
If that team goes with
the zero-win strategy,

1722
01:18:03,180 --> 01:18:04,350
they'll go 1st only in Round 1.

1723
01:18:04,350 --> 01:18:06,580
After that, they'll go later.

1724
01:18:06,580 --> 01:18:08,890
The team will aim to lose.

1725
01:18:08,890 --> 01:18:11,590
For example, say they submit
the lowest card they have,

1726
01:18:11,590 --> 01:18:13,220
card two in green.

1727
01:18:13,220 --> 01:18:17,160
In that case, the next team
will also submit card two in green,

1728
01:18:17,160 --> 01:18:18,260
helping Team P1 win.

1729
01:18:18,260 --> 01:18:19,400
That'd be the end
of the zero-win strategy.

1730
01:18:20,800 --> 01:18:24,400
As Team P1 has failed to predict
the expected win, the round has ended.

1731
01:18:24,400 --> 01:18:25,770
(As expected,
the 0-win plan ends after the 1st turn.)

1732
01:18:30,340 --> 01:18:33,180
Teams P3, Challenger, and P2...

1733
01:18:33,180 --> 01:18:35,280
each get four points.

1734
01:18:36,210 --> 01:18:38,850
Team P1 loses 4 points.

1735
01:19:00,270 --> 01:19:03,510
Round Six has ended.
Please leave the main hall.

1736
01:19:04,040 --> 01:19:05,080
Really...

1737
01:19:05,080 --> 01:19:07,510
The atmosphere was...

1738
01:19:08,850 --> 01:19:10,650
dead cold.

1739
01:19:10,950 --> 01:19:15,050
Jin Ho, YunB, and I didn't move an inch.

1740
01:19:15,050 --> 01:19:18,390
The atmosphere was so tense
that we were taken aback.

1741
01:19:18,490 --> 01:19:21,830
Team P1 has become isolated.

1742
01:19:22,560 --> 01:19:25,300
Round Six was a round
of ganging up on them.

1743
01:19:25,660 --> 01:19:28,670
From Team P1's perspective,

1744
01:19:29,200 --> 01:19:30,200
we're the bad guys.

1745
01:19:31,130 --> 01:19:32,140
It's true.

1746
01:19:32,240 --> 01:19:33,800
But we had to do what was needed...

1747
01:19:34,770 --> 01:19:37,710
because I'm currently on Team P3,
not Team P1.

1748
01:19:38,540 --> 01:19:40,810
Sang Min wasn't on the show for too long.

1749
01:19:41,880 --> 01:19:43,650
Can't you feel the rage from here?

1750
01:19:44,050 --> 01:19:46,550
We ganged up on him way too obviously.

1751
01:19:47,680 --> 01:19:48,820
Gosh.

1752
01:19:49,320 --> 01:19:50,720
We were the pushovers.

1753
01:19:54,190 --> 01:19:56,730
Round Seven strategy meeting begins now.

1754
01:19:59,060 --> 01:20:00,060
It won't work.

1755
01:20:01,060 --> 01:20:03,170
- Well done.
- Did you get zero wins, Sang Min?

1756
01:20:03,170 --> 01:20:05,300
- Minus four points.
- Good.

1757
01:20:06,270 --> 01:20:08,640
It's fine. The other teams
would've expected us...

1758
01:20:08,640 --> 01:20:11,040
to use the zero-win strategy
since we had no other choice.

1759
01:20:11,040 --> 01:20:12,810
- They...
- The three discussed...

1760
01:20:12,810 --> 01:20:14,980
- without me.
- Really?

1761
01:20:14,980 --> 01:20:17,480
- Yes, they do that.
- Totally.

1762
01:20:18,920 --> 01:20:20,120
It's frustrating, Sang Min.

1763
01:20:20,850 --> 01:20:23,750
Why don't we go and wreak havoc?

1764
01:20:23,750 --> 01:20:24,820
We sure should.

1765
01:20:29,630 --> 01:20:31,830
Why did the three team up anyway?

1766
01:20:31,830 --> 01:20:34,130
Not even one of them is trying to win.

1767
01:20:34,360 --> 01:20:36,500
- What a bunch of idiots.
- For real.

1768
01:20:38,100 --> 01:20:40,700
Those idiots.
We even offered to help them win.

1769
01:20:40,700 --> 01:20:43,040
Seung Jin is taking part
in the Deathmatch.

1770
01:20:43,040 --> 01:20:46,080
Since Seung Jin will be in that match,

1771
01:20:46,080 --> 01:20:47,980
Jin Hyeong is fine with coming in second.

1772
01:20:48,610 --> 01:20:50,380
- Since it won't be him.
- Is that so?

1773
01:20:50,380 --> 01:20:51,980
- Yes.
- Unbelievable.

1774
01:20:53,320 --> 01:20:57,150
That Team P2.
They even got the password from us.

1775
01:20:57,950 --> 01:21:00,390
Tell us the password for three.
I'll return the favor.

1776
01:21:00,690 --> 01:21:02,460
- You must.
- I promise.

1777
01:21:02,460 --> 01:21:03,730
- It's 2544.
- Okay.

1778
01:21:03,730 --> 01:21:05,430
- Let's go.
- She said 2544.

1779
01:21:06,860 --> 01:21:08,970
There's no need to help others.

1780
01:21:10,300 --> 01:21:13,540
Here's what I find funny. Team C...

1781
01:21:14,740 --> 01:21:16,540
was betrayed by Team P3.

1782
01:21:17,470 --> 01:21:18,980
Team P3 betrayed Team C...

1783
01:21:18,980 --> 01:21:21,610
by using the dictator card
and asking us to use...

1784
01:21:21,610 --> 01:21:22,610
the assassin card.

1785
01:21:22,610 --> 01:21:24,210
Team C could've been bribed.

1786
01:21:25,580 --> 01:21:27,920
Jin Ho's team and the others
could've bribed them.

1787
01:21:28,650 --> 01:21:31,420
We're the only ones left
with the dictator card,

1788
01:21:31,420 --> 01:21:32,620
and yet nobody is asking for our help.

1789
01:21:33,260 --> 01:21:36,790
From what I see, I'm almost entirely sure
Jin Ho will turn up for the upcoming turn.

1790
01:21:37,290 --> 01:21:38,460
- How come?
- The upcoming turn.

1791
01:21:38,460 --> 01:21:39,530
Because he feels bad.

1792
01:21:39,530 --> 01:21:41,660
- It didn't seem like he felt bad.
- He doesn't at all.

1793
01:21:42,800 --> 01:21:43,800
Hold on.

1794
01:21:43,800 --> 01:21:45,070
- What is it?
- He's back.

1795
01:21:45,440 --> 01:21:46,500
- How was it?
- Did it already end?

1796
01:21:46,500 --> 01:21:47,570
- How did it go?
- We stopped him...

1797
01:21:47,570 --> 01:21:48,640
and ended in the first round.

1798
01:21:48,670 --> 01:21:49,840
- The 0...
- It was the 0-win strategy, yes?

1799
01:21:49,840 --> 01:21:51,470
- Yes, the zero-win strategy.
- I knew it.

1800
01:21:51,470 --> 01:21:52,540
Single?

1801
01:21:52,540 --> 01:21:53,540
The zero-win plan as a single?

1802
01:21:53,540 --> 01:21:55,410
- Without a Mate?
- Zero-wins, single, with no Mate.

1803
01:21:55,410 --> 01:21:57,580
- To think it'd finish in the first turn.
- You really did it.

1804
01:21:57,580 --> 01:21:58,680
What bold guys.

1805
01:21:59,050 --> 01:22:01,580
The atmosphere was really heavy.

1806
01:22:01,580 --> 01:22:02,790
It was really heavy.

1807
01:22:02,790 --> 01:22:04,750
- For real. It's because...
- Right now...

1808
01:22:05,190 --> 01:22:06,960
he got zero wins.

1809
01:22:07,490 --> 01:22:09,930
- He didn't name a Mate.
- Right.

1810
01:22:09,930 --> 01:22:11,390
The team needed 12 points...

1811
01:22:11,390 --> 01:22:13,560
- to come in first.
- He took a risk. He did.

1812
01:22:13,560 --> 01:22:16,300
But we prepared a counterattack
and ended it in the first turn.

1813
01:22:16,300 --> 01:22:18,270
- Because it ended in the 1st set,
- It was minus 2.

1814
01:22:18,270 --> 01:22:20,240
- he crumpled up the card and left.
- Was it...

1815
01:22:20,240 --> 01:22:21,240
- Did he crumple up the card?
- not minus?

1816
01:22:21,240 --> 01:22:23,940
Not like Chungju Man.

1817
01:22:24,140 --> 01:22:26,010
But anyone could feel his rage.

1818
01:22:26,740 --> 01:22:28,680
It's okay. This is a survival show.

1819
01:22:28,680 --> 01:22:29,910
Why did it take so long?

1820
01:22:30,550 --> 01:22:32,320
Team P1 is in last place, period.

1821
01:22:32,320 --> 01:22:34,520
How many points do we have
right now? 20...

1822
01:22:34,520 --> 01:22:35,720
We're going first this time.

1823
01:22:35,720 --> 01:22:38,020
So how many in total?

1824
01:22:38,020 --> 01:22:40,220
- Twenty-one.
- We each got four points.

1825
01:22:45,460 --> 01:22:46,460
(Thinking)

1826
01:23:05,150 --> 01:23:06,980
"Team P1 is an eyesore."

1827
01:23:06,980 --> 01:23:08,220
"Let's bring them down."

1828
01:23:09,820 --> 01:23:12,360
It doesn't seem right.

1829
01:23:12,360 --> 01:23:14,820
Why? Because if we were to bring
the team in first place down...

1830
01:23:15,020 --> 01:23:18,160
Only one team can finish in first place.

1831
01:23:18,160 --> 01:23:20,160
But why drag them down?

1832
01:23:20,160 --> 01:23:21,160
What next?

1833
01:23:22,130 --> 01:23:25,100
That's when I realized
this is just like politics.

1834
01:23:25,740 --> 01:23:29,010
I was willing to work together...

1835
01:23:29,810 --> 01:23:30,810
with Sang Min.

1836
01:23:31,010 --> 01:23:32,440
I also owe the team.

1837
01:23:33,080 --> 01:23:34,180
If it's...

1838
01:23:34,380 --> 01:23:38,110
a fair, clean, catharsis-inducing play,

1839
01:23:38,110 --> 01:23:40,450
I'm in without a doubt.

1840
01:23:40,750 --> 01:23:42,920
We were asked to submit our cards.

1841
01:23:42,920 --> 01:23:44,150
- Hi.
- Hey.

1842
01:23:46,190 --> 01:23:48,060
- Hi.
- I'm here to see...

1843
01:23:48,060 --> 01:23:49,130
what you guys are up to.

1844
01:23:49,830 --> 01:23:51,890
Why do we feel like outcasts?

1845
01:23:52,260 --> 01:23:54,060
- Feel free to come over.
- Why are you here alone?

1846
01:23:54,060 --> 01:23:56,970
No, I'm sure nobody
has any ill feelings towards Tae Gyun.

1847
01:23:56,970 --> 01:23:57,970
Sorry?

1848
01:23:59,570 --> 01:24:00,770
But ill feelings towards others?

1849
01:24:00,770 --> 01:24:02,670
No, we have no hard feelings
towards anyone.

1850
01:24:05,310 --> 01:24:06,910
- A short chat?
- Gosh, Sang Min is so angry...

1851
01:24:06,910 --> 01:24:08,340
- Right now?
- that it's awkward.

1852
01:24:09,450 --> 01:24:10,580
I should go for a smoke.

1853
01:24:16,950 --> 01:24:17,950
Hey.

1854
01:24:19,060 --> 01:24:20,220
- How about getting first place?
- What?

1855
01:24:20,220 --> 01:24:21,760
- How about getting first place?
- No, thanks.

1856
01:24:23,430 --> 01:24:24,890
Hear me out.

1857
01:24:27,500 --> 01:24:28,770
You can take 1st by placing 1st alone...

1858
01:24:28,770 --> 01:24:30,330
- in the next round.
- You see,

1859
01:24:30,630 --> 01:24:31,730
it's impossible for us.

1860
01:24:31,730 --> 01:24:33,840
The cards we have right now...

1861
01:24:34,240 --> 01:24:35,940
are bad, so we can't.

1862
01:24:36,210 --> 01:24:38,140
- How about zero wins?
- We could help.

1863
01:24:38,410 --> 01:24:41,010
We have many high-number cards.

1864
01:24:41,940 --> 01:24:43,950
- You even have the dictator card.
- Correct.

1865
01:24:43,950 --> 01:24:45,580
That's why we brought you here.

1866
01:24:46,320 --> 01:24:48,790
Then give me a few minutes, will you?

1867
01:24:48,790 --> 01:24:50,920
- Come back quickly.
- I don't know our cards.

1868
01:24:50,920 --> 01:24:52,090
- Hurry up.
- I'll tag along.

1869
01:24:52,090 --> 01:24:53,090
I get it.

1870
01:24:53,090 --> 01:24:54,760
If our cards work out,

1871
01:24:54,760 --> 01:24:55,830
let's return together.

1872
01:24:56,090 --> 01:24:59,460
After Ji Hoo hears about our plan,

1873
01:24:59,460 --> 01:25:01,100
compares our cards,

1874
01:25:01,760 --> 01:25:04,330
and thinks it'll work 100 percent,

1875
01:25:04,470 --> 01:25:05,470
it's worth a shot.

1876
01:25:07,570 --> 01:25:08,570
Listen.

1877
01:25:09,410 --> 01:25:10,740
- It's just that...
- Yes?

1878
01:25:10,940 --> 01:25:12,510
we hate being under Team P3's control.

1879
01:25:12,510 --> 01:25:14,110
We want to make you come in first place.

1880
01:25:14,110 --> 01:25:15,910
- How?
- By getting 0 wins alone in Round 7...

1881
01:25:15,910 --> 01:25:18,480
without a Mate.

1882
01:25:18,480 --> 01:25:20,220
And then, we win the rest.

1883
01:25:20,450 --> 01:25:22,620
Did you understand,
or are you here to hear us out?

1884
01:25:22,620 --> 01:25:24,850
I've come up with our team's plan.

1885
01:25:24,850 --> 01:25:26,920
- You did?
- It's my call now.

1886
01:25:26,920 --> 01:25:28,390
- Okay.
- Okay.

1887
01:25:28,390 --> 01:25:30,890
You must get that
we're supporting your zero wins.

1888
01:25:30,890 --> 01:25:33,060
- Got it. Wait a minute.
- And...

1889
01:25:33,060 --> 01:25:34,500
- We must do well in Round Eight.
- True.

1890
01:25:34,500 --> 01:25:36,870
- In Round 7...
- We'll call 0 wins.

1891
01:25:37,500 --> 01:25:38,800
Or if someone calls zero wins,

1892
01:25:38,800 --> 01:25:40,200
we can use the dictator card.

1893
01:25:40,900 --> 01:25:42,270
If not, we can call zero wins.

1894
01:25:42,270 --> 01:25:44,470
Then it's over once we lose points.

1895
01:25:44,840 --> 01:25:48,850
Here's how Team P1 is planning
to make Team C come in 1st place.

1896
01:25:49,410 --> 01:25:52,750
Team C, which goes 1st,
will bet on 0 wins.

1897
01:25:52,950 --> 01:25:55,790
Team P1 will work together
with Team C to reach a sum,

1898
01:25:55,790 --> 01:25:57,850
submit a card guaranteed to win,

1899
01:25:57,850 --> 01:25:59,360
and secure zero wins.

1900
01:25:59,690 --> 01:26:02,860
If Team C is the only one
to successfully predict 0 wins in Round 7,

1901
01:26:03,090 --> 01:26:05,130
it will get three extra points
from the round.

1902
01:26:05,130 --> 01:26:07,160
After receiving a total of 13 points,

1903
01:26:07,430 --> 01:26:09,530
Team C will come in 1st place
with 28 points.

1904
01:26:10,630 --> 01:26:12,170
Even if other teams...

1905
01:26:12,370 --> 01:26:14,770
bet on 0 wins in Round 8,

1906
01:26:14,770 --> 01:26:18,240
Team P1 can exchange the dictator card
and stop them.

1907
01:26:18,240 --> 01:26:20,680
If the other teams
do not bet on zero wins,

1908
01:26:20,680 --> 01:26:23,380
Team P1 will bet on 0 wins...

1909
01:26:23,380 --> 01:26:24,710
and lose on purpose,

1910
01:26:24,710 --> 01:26:26,880
and Team C will maintain its first place.

1911
01:26:26,880 --> 01:26:28,420
(Dictator card)

1912
01:26:29,520 --> 01:26:31,520
This plan will work without fail.

1913
01:26:32,360 --> 01:26:33,690
We have the dictator card.

1914
01:26:34,520 --> 01:26:35,730
It made sense.

1915
01:26:36,330 --> 01:26:39,430
Really, there was a perfect plan
with an over 90-percent chance...

1916
01:26:39,960 --> 01:26:42,530
where we could become the sole team...

1917
01:26:42,830 --> 01:26:44,370
in first place.

1918
01:26:45,070 --> 01:26:46,570
Going along with it felt right.

1919
01:26:46,570 --> 01:26:48,570
Take part, and we'd get first place.

1920
01:26:48,940 --> 01:26:52,040
In other words,
we'd be betraying the other two teams.

1921
01:26:52,040 --> 01:26:53,180
- Just do it.
- It'd be 2 to 1.

1922
01:26:53,180 --> 01:26:54,840
I'm all about...

1923
01:26:54,840 --> 01:26:56,550
those two teams,

1924
01:26:56,550 --> 01:26:58,250
including Jin Ho's.

1925
01:26:58,250 --> 01:27:00,420
- We just hate being swayed by them.
- I see.

1926
01:27:00,420 --> 01:27:01,850
- That's why we're proposing this plan.
- Right.

1927
01:27:01,850 --> 01:27:03,220
We won't get anything from this.

1928
01:27:03,820 --> 01:27:04,920
You're simply getting our support.

1929
01:27:04,920 --> 01:27:06,720
What you'll gain... You were outcasts.

1930
01:27:06,720 --> 01:27:07,860
- It'll become 2 against 2 now.
- Three minutes...

1931
01:27:07,860 --> 01:27:08,990
before the strategy meeting ends.

1932
01:27:08,990 --> 01:27:10,390
Is that it?

1933
01:27:10,390 --> 01:27:11,860
That's a big deal, you know?

1934
01:27:12,260 --> 01:27:14,700
- Either way, I'm in.
- First off...

1935
01:27:14,860 --> 01:27:17,600
The three-team alliance
will break up in the end.

1936
01:27:17,600 --> 01:27:20,840
- Winning this game is way better.
- True.

1937
01:27:20,840 --> 01:27:22,170
We're the losers among the three teams.

1938
01:27:22,570 --> 01:27:24,410
Let's team up starting tomorrow.

1939
01:27:24,570 --> 01:27:25,740
Which team goes first tomorrow?

1940
01:27:25,740 --> 01:27:26,740
- His.
- Ours.

1941
01:27:26,740 --> 01:27:28,040
I'll call zero wins, green.

1942
01:27:28,040 --> 01:27:29,150
- Yes.
- That's it.

1943
01:27:30,310 --> 01:27:31,910
We have to choose as soon as possible.

1944
01:27:31,910 --> 01:27:33,720
Where's Team C's card deck?

1945
01:27:33,720 --> 01:27:34,950
- Someone took it.
- A teammate took it.

1946
01:27:34,950 --> 01:27:37,250
- Who?
- He just took it somewhere.

1947
01:27:37,250 --> 01:27:38,590
He didn't take it. He already had it.

1948
01:27:38,590 --> 01:27:39,890
- Who? Ji Hoo?
- Ji Hoo.

1949
01:27:40,420 --> 01:27:42,530
- Where's Ji Hoo?
- Ji Hoo asked us not to shuffle them...

1950
01:27:42,530 --> 01:27:44,760
because they're already in order
from what we talked about.

1951
01:27:44,760 --> 01:27:47,200
- Do we not have low-numbered cards?
- I need Ji Hoo's cards.

1952
01:27:47,200 --> 01:27:49,200
- Me?
- No, I'm asking the Master.

1953
01:27:49,200 --> 01:27:51,230
- Whose turn is it?
- Team P1.

1954
01:27:51,230 --> 01:27:52,300
- Xitsuh? Seong Beom?
- Ji Hoo...

1955
01:27:52,300 --> 01:27:53,640
- It's me.
- Go downstairs.

1956
01:27:53,640 --> 01:27:55,340
Do we have blue? Did we give away blue?

1957
01:27:55,340 --> 01:27:56,910
Either way, I have to go.

1958
01:27:56,910 --> 01:27:57,910
- Yes.
- Shuffle them.

1959
01:28:01,080 --> 01:28:02,280
Where's Ji Hoo?

1960
01:28:04,250 --> 01:28:06,150
- Even if we do it...
- Where did Ji Hoo go?

1961
01:28:07,950 --> 01:28:09,490
- I can't find Ji Hoo.
- And so...

1962
01:28:11,490 --> 01:28:13,060
- Well...
- Ji Hoo's nowhere.

1963
01:28:13,060 --> 01:28:15,220
- What?
- I couldn't find Ji Hoo.

1964
01:28:15,220 --> 01:28:18,090
- Where's the deck?
- We should get a grip.

1965
01:28:18,230 --> 01:28:20,630
From what I see, Team C...

1966
01:28:20,730 --> 01:28:21,860
- I've got it.
- Right now...

1967
01:28:21,860 --> 01:28:23,400
- I...
- You're not backing out, are you?

1968
01:28:23,630 --> 01:28:26,040
I swear we're not.

1969
01:28:27,270 --> 01:28:29,510
Think carefully. Where did he go?

1970
01:28:31,140 --> 01:28:32,680
I got scared.

1971
01:28:32,680 --> 01:28:34,380
Everyone kept saying it won't happen.

1972
01:28:34,380 --> 01:28:36,750
All we needed were zero wins
and self-sabotage.

1973
01:28:37,380 --> 01:28:38,410
But after some thinking,

1974
01:28:38,410 --> 01:28:40,320
if a team gets zero wins...

1975
01:28:40,320 --> 01:28:42,990
and succeeds with the 0-win plan,
that very team will come in 1st place.

1976
01:28:43,320 --> 01:28:46,760
It seemed like no one had that in mind.

1977
01:28:47,090 --> 01:28:49,560
Everyone was chilling,
taking naps, and such.

1978
01:28:49,760 --> 01:28:51,530
The atmosphere was as if
we had already won.

1979
01:28:51,630 --> 01:28:53,860
At the same time,
Team C was acting strangely.

1980
01:28:54,560 --> 01:28:55,800
It got me all anxious.

1981
01:28:56,670 --> 01:28:59,640
We will begin Round Seven
of the card battle.

1982
01:29:01,570 --> 01:29:02,970
Starting with Kang Ji Hoo,

1983
01:29:02,970 --> 01:29:05,880
predict the expected wins,
pick the master color, and make your bet.

1984
01:29:14,350 --> 01:29:16,220
And Ji Hoo had a strange look in his eyes.

1985
01:29:16,550 --> 01:29:17,550
That's why...

1986
01:29:18,050 --> 01:29:20,360
I was so anxious.
I knew something was wrong.

1987
01:29:21,090 --> 01:29:23,860
I'll bet on zero wins, green.

1988
01:29:23,860 --> 01:29:26,100
Kang Ji Hoo has bet on green, zero wins.

1989
01:29:26,100 --> 01:29:27,400
(Kang Ji Hoo has bet on green, zero wins.)

1990
01:29:32,840 --> 01:29:35,840
Kang Ji Hoo, since you bet on zero wins,
you have become the Master.

1991
01:29:37,210 --> 01:29:40,140
Ha Seung Jin, Heo Seong Beom,
and Lee Sang Min.

1992
01:29:40,140 --> 01:29:42,750
Please submit the card
you want to give to the Master.

1993
01:29:44,450 --> 01:29:45,610
I can submit any card, right?

1994
01:29:46,450 --> 01:29:47,650
Any card?

1995
01:29:58,190 --> 01:30:00,160
Sang Min was trying...

1996
01:30:00,160 --> 01:30:03,030
not to show that we've joined forces.

1997
01:30:03,030 --> 01:30:05,600
I gave Sang Min a big number...

1998
01:30:05,600 --> 01:30:06,940
so he could win. I gave him 15.

1999
01:30:07,140 --> 01:30:11,010
(Sang Min gets 15.)

2000
01:30:11,870 --> 01:30:13,810
All cards have been exchanged.

2001
01:30:14,840 --> 01:30:17,180
Kang Ji Hoo, do you wish to name a Mate?

2002
01:30:17,580 --> 01:30:18,910
No.

2003
01:30:20,720 --> 01:30:22,850
No Mate was named.

2004
01:30:23,820 --> 01:30:26,790
The first set will start with the Master.

2005
01:30:27,920 --> 01:30:30,190
Kang Ji Hoo, please submit your card.

2006
01:30:32,090 --> 01:30:35,030
Card 16 in green has been submitted.

2007
01:30:43,010 --> 01:30:44,740
Gosh, what's going on?

2008
01:30:47,180 --> 01:30:48,510
It was the biggest number.

2009
01:30:50,180 --> 01:30:51,410
It meant no zero wins.

2010
01:30:59,090 --> 01:31:01,990
I had to act a certain way
in that situation.

2011
01:31:02,460 --> 01:31:04,790
As if Sang Min's constant persuasion...

2012
01:31:05,230 --> 01:31:07,900
was making me second-guess myself.

2013
01:31:08,230 --> 01:31:11,070
I had to play the role of the poor guy.

2014
01:31:11,800 --> 01:31:14,200
So I was standing there,
looking unsure of what to do.

2015
01:31:16,440 --> 01:31:17,570
(Before Round 7)

2016
01:31:17,570 --> 01:31:18,740
Ji Hoo, come over here.

2017
01:31:20,480 --> 01:31:22,780
Is it because you want to come in first?

2018
01:31:23,110 --> 01:31:25,820
(Thinking)

2019
01:31:25,820 --> 01:31:26,920
I was offered that.

2020
01:31:28,220 --> 01:31:30,550
- But...
- Do you think you can handle that?

2021
01:31:34,260 --> 01:31:35,520
You Hyun was like,

2022
01:31:35,520 --> 01:31:37,790
"Do you think you can handle that?"

2023
01:31:38,730 --> 01:31:39,930
He was trying to intimidate me.

2024
01:31:40,260 --> 01:31:42,700
At that point, I was freaking out.

2025
01:31:42,700 --> 01:31:45,400
"Am I doing something
I won't be able to handle?"

2026
01:31:45,870 --> 01:31:47,940
"Will I crash and burn?"

2027
01:31:47,940 --> 01:31:49,570
All kinds of worries
started running through my head.

2028
01:31:49,570 --> 01:31:51,170
Since they're all experienced,

2029
01:31:51,310 --> 01:31:53,180
I decided to do as they say.

2030
01:31:53,180 --> 01:31:55,580
I'm saying this for your sake.

2031
01:31:55,850 --> 01:31:57,280
He's right.

2032
01:31:57,280 --> 01:31:58,810
I'm only saying this for your sake.

2033
01:31:58,810 --> 01:32:01,120
- Right?
- I thought about doing that too,

2034
01:32:01,120 --> 01:32:02,120
but it would be better not to.

2035
01:32:02,120 --> 01:32:03,950
Even Kyoung Hoon said I shouldn't.

2036
01:32:04,450 --> 01:32:05,820
If he does that,

2037
01:32:05,990 --> 01:32:08,560
we would be turning our backs...

2038
01:32:08,560 --> 01:32:10,360
on Team P2 and Team P3.

2039
01:32:10,460 --> 01:32:13,100
In that case, turning our backs...

2040
01:32:13,100 --> 01:32:15,730
on both teams on the first day
would be too risky.

2041
01:32:15,800 --> 01:32:18,530
Also, You Hyun got a lot more...

2042
01:32:18,530 --> 01:32:20,240
annoyed than I expected.

2043
01:32:21,070 --> 01:32:23,710
(After telling You Hyun
about the strategy)

2044
01:32:24,570 --> 01:32:26,440
Why do you keep acting on your own?

2045
01:32:26,440 --> 01:32:28,680
No, I'm not.

2046
01:32:28,680 --> 01:32:30,850
I just sent Ji Hoo for now.
It's not finalized.

2047
01:32:30,850 --> 01:32:33,180
- Why send him?
- Ji Hoo?

2048
01:32:33,180 --> 01:32:35,120
Why send him
when there's nothing to talk about?

2049
01:32:35,120 --> 01:32:36,650
- It's just...
- Look.

2050
01:32:36,650 --> 01:32:38,290
If we come in first,

2051
01:32:38,290 --> 01:32:41,260
- the two teams will feel betrayed.
- But...

2052
01:32:41,260 --> 01:32:42,260
the thing is...

2053
01:32:42,260 --> 01:32:44,830
I thought that, if he was reacting...

2054
01:32:44,830 --> 01:32:47,830
this strongly right now,

2055
01:32:47,830 --> 01:32:50,100
it wouldn't be good for us
as we try to carry the game.

2056
01:32:50,100 --> 01:32:52,430
If we become the team
that no one can trust,

2057
01:32:52,430 --> 01:32:54,840
the traitor team, it could cause issues...

2058
01:32:54,840 --> 01:32:57,840
when we try to form alliances
with the other teams in the long run.

2059
01:32:57,910 --> 01:32:59,780
And it's not like we'd be
turning our backs on one team...

2060
01:32:59,780 --> 01:33:00,810
and gaining two allies.

2061
01:33:00,810 --> 01:33:02,010
In fact, it's the opposite.

2062
01:33:02,010 --> 01:33:06,820
That's why I thought the strategy
wasn't a good one.

2063
01:33:07,520 --> 01:33:08,650
- Go.
- Okay.

2064
01:33:09,420 --> 01:33:12,020
Zero wins, card 16.

2065
01:33:12,020 --> 01:33:13,860
Per my original mission,

2066
01:33:13,860 --> 01:33:16,790
I would submit card 16 and self-sabotage.

2067
01:33:17,260 --> 01:33:18,890
(He chose card 16 to self-sabotage.)

2068
01:33:18,890 --> 01:33:21,060
The lead color of this set is green.

2069
01:33:22,600 --> 01:33:24,930
Ha Seung Jin, please submit your card.

2070
01:33:27,470 --> 01:33:29,940
Card ten in green has been submitted.

2071
01:33:30,740 --> 01:33:34,240
Card 13 in green has been submitted
by Heo Seong Beom.

2072
01:33:34,640 --> 01:33:36,810
Lee Sang Min, please submit your card.

2073
01:33:36,810 --> 01:33:43,420
(Heo Seong Beom: 13, Kang Ji Hoo: 16,
Ha Seung Jin: 10)

2074
01:33:43,420 --> 01:33:48,220
(Master: Kang Ji Hoo, Bet: Zero wins)

2075
01:33:48,220 --> 01:33:49,360
You submitted card 16?

2076
01:33:50,630 --> 01:33:51,730
I'm sorry.

2077
01:33:52,960 --> 01:33:54,500
Gosh.

2078
01:33:55,530 --> 01:33:56,830
In that short time?

2079
01:34:07,380 --> 01:34:09,240
Sang Min,
you've still got a long way to go.

2080
01:34:10,150 --> 01:34:11,510
You've still got a long way to go.

2081
01:34:19,390 --> 01:34:20,890
Gosh, in that moment,

2082
01:34:22,360 --> 01:34:24,130
my life up to now felt like...

2083
01:34:24,660 --> 01:34:26,360
Seriously.

2084
01:34:27,500 --> 01:34:30,570
As the oldest cast member,
I gave the opportunity to win...

2085
01:34:32,000 --> 01:34:34,700
to the youngest member.

2086
01:34:35,100 --> 01:34:37,470
So why would he choose not to win?

2087
01:34:38,640 --> 01:34:41,580
I felt so disappointed and empty.

2088
01:34:45,110 --> 01:34:47,480
Card 14 in green has been submitted.

2089
01:34:53,990 --> 01:34:55,290
(Heo Seong Beom: 13, Lee Sang Min: 14,
Kang Ji Hoo: 16, Ha Seung Jin: 10)

2090
01:34:55,290 --> 01:34:57,760
Kang Ji Hoo has won Set One.

2091
01:35:01,200 --> 01:35:03,470
As Team C has failed
to predict the expected win,

2092
01:35:03,470 --> 01:35:04,930
the round has ended.

2093
01:35:06,170 --> 01:35:07,470
Guys, I stood my ground.

2094
01:35:07,470 --> 01:35:09,670
- Good. You really did good.
- Yes.

2095
01:35:10,110 --> 01:35:12,610
Team C loses four points.

2096
01:35:20,420 --> 01:35:22,280
Gosh. Kyoung Hoon, that fool.

2097
01:35:23,020 --> 01:35:25,820
Gosh, that clown. Darn it.

2098
01:35:27,360 --> 01:35:30,360
I can't believe I trusted him again.

2099
01:35:35,730 --> 01:35:37,430
Don't whistle. Who are you?

2100
01:35:38,030 --> 01:35:39,670
We're in trouble. You jerks.

2101
01:35:44,710 --> 01:35:47,040
Gosh, those clowns.

2102
01:35:51,180 --> 01:35:53,480
I understand his frustration.

2103
01:35:54,020 --> 01:35:56,190
- Right.
- I've had a similar experience.

2104
01:35:57,990 --> 01:35:59,390
I can see why he's upset.

2105
01:35:59,760 --> 01:36:01,960
But that's part of the Bloody Game.

2106
01:36:06,560 --> 01:36:07,560
- Ji Hoo.
- Yes?

2107
01:36:09,730 --> 01:36:10,800
You did a good job.

2108
01:36:10,870 --> 01:36:13,970
In a survival show, you only need to win
when it really matters.

2109
01:36:13,970 --> 01:36:16,370
- Yes.
- If you think of today...

2110
01:36:16,370 --> 01:36:18,070
as a battle you didn't have to win,

2111
01:36:18,070 --> 01:36:19,310
- you'd feel at ease.
- Okay.

2112
01:36:21,480 --> 01:36:23,680
Round Eight has begun.

2113
01:36:24,350 --> 01:36:26,080
After a 20-minute strategy meeting,

2114
01:36:26,080 --> 01:36:28,420
we will begin Round Eight
of the card battle.

2115
01:36:28,420 --> 01:36:29,450
(Round 8 strategy meeting begins.)

2116
01:36:29,450 --> 01:36:30,450
(Team P1's room)

2117
01:36:30,450 --> 01:36:33,060
- How did it go?
- How else? I got hit.

2118
01:36:33,360 --> 01:36:35,520
He bet on zero wins
then submitted card 16.

2119
01:36:35,820 --> 01:36:38,590
- What?
- I lost. I was betrayed again.

2120
01:36:39,130 --> 01:36:41,100
The one in yellow...

2121
01:36:41,100 --> 01:36:42,870
who was saying "yes" like a chick...

2122
01:36:42,870 --> 01:36:43,900
He betrayed him.

2123
01:36:43,900 --> 01:36:45,870
- He said zero wins and submitted Card 16.
- Why?

2124
01:36:47,000 --> 01:36:48,470
The three joined forces.

2125
01:36:49,570 --> 01:36:50,840
But why?

2126
01:36:50,840 --> 01:36:52,370
That's what I don't understand.

2127
01:36:52,370 --> 01:36:54,580
It's completely meaningless to be
2nd, 3rd, or 4th place.

2128
01:36:54,580 --> 01:36:56,510
So why? He could have been first place.

2129
01:36:57,510 --> 01:37:00,320
Team C really is clueless.

2130
01:37:00,320 --> 01:37:01,950
I was so surprised.

2131
01:37:01,950 --> 01:37:03,690
I thought he was a psychopath.

2132
01:37:03,690 --> 01:37:04,720
He was like "blue, zero wins."

2133
01:37:05,220 --> 01:37:07,220
He submitted card 16.

2134
01:37:08,320 --> 01:37:09,560
I was like, is he a psychopath?

2135
01:37:11,130 --> 01:37:12,430
Gosh.

2136
01:37:12,960 --> 01:37:15,900
I'd get it if he betrayed me
to become number one.

2137
01:37:16,330 --> 01:37:18,070
But why are the other teams...

2138
01:37:18,070 --> 01:37:20,500
Why are the two other teams
flanking him and...

2139
01:37:20,500 --> 01:37:22,570
Right, they're sucking up to him.

2140
01:37:23,510 --> 01:37:26,940
It's a gift to work that hard
to come in 2nd and 3rd.

2141
01:37:27,540 --> 01:37:31,880
What Kyoung Hoon said is funnier.

2142
01:37:32,210 --> 01:37:35,520
Apparently, he was trying to see...

2143
01:37:35,520 --> 01:37:37,220
who would betray first.

2144
01:37:37,220 --> 01:37:39,660
- What nonsense.
- He keeps speaking nonsense.

2145
01:37:40,260 --> 01:37:42,090
- What team would betray first?
- Right.

2146
01:37:42,090 --> 01:37:44,490
Also, they were betrayed by Team P3,

2147
01:37:44,490 --> 01:37:47,100
but now they're acting like pushovers
by backing Team P3.

2148
01:37:48,100 --> 01:37:50,200
The guys in Team C are such fools.

2149
01:37:51,300 --> 01:37:54,070
What's their purpose? They don't have one.

2150
01:37:54,070 --> 01:37:56,410
Team C stands for Team Clowns.

2151
01:37:56,410 --> 01:37:57,470
What do they call themselves? Challenger?

2152
01:38:01,010 --> 01:38:03,580
I'm sorry for being too naive
and revealing everything.

2153
01:38:03,580 --> 01:38:04,980
- It's fine.
- No, it's fine.

2154
01:38:05,480 --> 01:38:08,150
I didn't see this coming.

2155
01:38:13,790 --> 01:38:14,820
Gosh.

2156
01:38:23,070 --> 01:38:24,630
We're finishing in second place.

2157
01:38:25,570 --> 01:38:26,570
Yes.

2158
01:38:26,570 --> 01:38:29,300
Even one of us could end up
being a candidate for elimination.

2159
01:38:30,210 --> 01:38:31,510
We have to think about that too.

2160
01:38:32,210 --> 01:38:33,240
What do you think?

2161
01:38:33,980 --> 01:38:36,550
If someone volunteers,
I wouldn't stop him.

2162
01:38:36,550 --> 01:38:37,910
But otherwise,

2163
01:38:39,210 --> 01:38:41,980
I think putting it up to a vote
isn't a bad idea.

2164
01:38:42,890 --> 01:38:45,050
(Team P2's room)

2165
01:38:45,050 --> 01:38:46,620
We have the Deathmatch to think about.

2166
01:38:49,760 --> 01:38:53,360
Once we know each candidate,
we'll be able to guess who'll be there.

2167
01:38:53,930 --> 01:38:54,960
Team P1.

2168
01:38:55,130 --> 01:38:57,000
He won't be there
because of his sense of responsibility.

2169
01:38:57,000 --> 01:38:58,730
- And there's no reason for Tae Gyun.
- There's no reason for him.

2170
01:38:58,730 --> 01:39:00,900
- So it comes down to these two.
- I think...

2171
01:39:00,900 --> 01:39:02,540
We should expect Keun Woo.

2172
01:39:03,210 --> 01:39:05,840
Team C. Let's exclude women.

2173
01:39:07,280 --> 01:39:08,410
It's either You Hyun or Ji Hoo.

2174
01:39:09,280 --> 01:39:10,810
It would be really hard...

2175
01:39:11,710 --> 01:39:13,520
to beat these two.
We won't be able to win.

2176
01:39:14,380 --> 01:39:15,420
We really can't beat You Hyun?

2177
01:39:16,250 --> 01:39:18,750
It would be hard.
We'd have to be on Jin Hyeong's level.

2178
01:39:20,320 --> 01:39:23,130
We'd be in trouble if we go.

2179
01:39:23,860 --> 01:39:25,160
We'd be in trouble.

2180
01:39:25,160 --> 01:39:26,430
- We'd be in trouble?
- Yes.

2181
01:39:26,730 --> 01:39:27,800
We'd be in trouble if we go.

2182
01:39:27,800 --> 01:39:29,100
No way. I should bail.

2183
01:39:31,930 --> 01:39:33,040
This isn't the time to act tough.

2184
01:39:33,370 --> 01:39:35,240
No one here has the reason to go.

2185
01:39:36,340 --> 01:39:38,610
There is one reason.
Seung Jin said he's going.

2186
01:39:40,280 --> 01:39:41,340
That's one reason.

2187
01:39:42,280 --> 01:39:44,780
But that doesn't mean I want to send him.

2188
01:39:45,210 --> 01:39:46,280
What should we do?

2189
01:39:46,520 --> 01:39:48,980
We're going to have to...

2190
01:39:49,850 --> 01:39:52,250
have this uncomfortable conversation soon.

2191
01:39:52,490 --> 01:39:54,090
We have to come up with a reason.

2192
01:39:54,090 --> 01:39:55,220
- A reason?
- That's even more cruel.

2193
01:39:55,260 --> 01:39:56,360
We have to come up with the reason.

2194
01:40:00,230 --> 01:40:02,460
If they make us vote among ourselves,

2195
01:40:03,170 --> 01:40:04,370
the result already has a majority.

2196
01:40:04,770 --> 01:40:05,870
Right.

2197
01:40:05,900 --> 01:40:07,270
So we can decide right now.

2198
01:40:07,570 --> 01:40:08,840
Who should we send?

2199
01:40:09,670 --> 01:40:11,470
The person most likely to win.

2200
01:40:12,270 --> 01:40:13,280
We'll rationalize it?

2201
01:40:13,880 --> 01:40:15,780
- So we send him?
- Yes.

2202
01:40:15,780 --> 01:40:16,980
- Because he'll be back anyway?
- Yes.

2203
01:40:17,910 --> 01:40:20,580
The karma from the second season
of the show will...

2204
01:40:21,380 --> 01:40:23,090
We'll be making sure
karma catches up with him.

2205
01:40:23,190 --> 01:40:24,450
We'll be acting...

2206
01:40:26,620 --> 01:40:28,320
as the karma police.

2207
01:40:29,690 --> 01:40:30,790
It's kind of cruel.

2208
01:40:30,790 --> 01:40:33,860
Why does it feel like
only soft-hearted people end up going?

2209
01:40:34,160 --> 01:40:35,200
Right?

2210
01:40:35,200 --> 01:40:37,000
Someone has to.

2211
01:40:37,000 --> 01:40:39,770
- Let's just vote.
- But there is that.

2212
01:40:39,900 --> 01:40:40,940
The aftermath.

2213
01:40:42,140 --> 01:40:44,310
When he leaves and comes back...

2214
01:40:44,570 --> 01:40:46,270
How we do it matters.

2215
01:40:46,270 --> 01:40:47,910
When we send him off,

2216
01:40:47,980 --> 01:40:49,640
we make a huge deal out of it.
Like he's doing it for the country.

2217
01:40:50,380 --> 01:40:51,710
And he'll return as an ally.

2218
01:40:51,950 --> 01:40:53,420
So you're saying we have to gaslight him?

2219
01:40:54,050 --> 01:40:55,450
As harsh as it is.

2220
01:40:56,690 --> 01:40:58,520
No, it's just cold logic.

2221
01:40:59,150 --> 01:41:01,360
Jin Hyeong is...

2222
01:41:01,590 --> 01:41:02,960
the sharpest blade we have.

2223
01:41:02,960 --> 01:41:05,390
He won. He took 50,000 dollars.

2224
01:41:07,460 --> 01:41:08,800
Let us take some too.

2225
01:41:10,930 --> 01:41:12,230
What if he's around here somewhere?

2226
01:41:12,230 --> 01:41:13,670
- What?
- What if he's around here somewhere?

2227
01:41:13,670 --> 01:41:16,570
Hey, I was just joking.

2228
01:41:19,940 --> 01:41:21,780
We were bad at the battle,

2229
01:41:21,780 --> 01:41:23,580
but here we are, having fun
talking about the Deathmatch.

2230
01:41:25,750 --> 01:41:26,820
We're doomed.

2231
01:41:28,050 --> 01:41:30,220
It would be boring if only the ones...

2232
01:41:30,220 --> 01:41:32,350
who are smart
and good at the games survived.

2233
01:41:32,350 --> 01:41:33,760
The world shouldn't work that way.

2234
01:41:34,090 --> 01:41:37,990
I'll keep that in mind for now.

2235
01:41:42,500 --> 01:41:44,230
Why were you gone for so long?

2236
01:41:45,130 --> 01:41:47,800
There was another meeting.

2237
01:41:48,370 --> 01:41:50,570
I think I should get some sleep
for the Deathmatch.

2238
01:41:50,810 --> 01:41:52,540
- Yes, you should sleep.
- You should sleep.

2239
01:41:52,540 --> 01:41:53,640
I'm not sleepy, though.

2240
01:41:53,640 --> 01:41:55,080
We'll turn off the lights and leave.

2241
01:41:55,340 --> 01:41:57,550
Go smoke a cigarette.

2242
01:41:57,550 --> 01:42:00,280
At least lie down, then.
Just closing your eyes would help.

2243
01:42:00,520 --> 01:42:01,820
Let's go have a smoke.

2244
01:42:04,320 --> 01:42:06,860
I'll go over the plan one last time...

2245
01:42:06,860 --> 01:42:08,060
- Okay.
- and head down.

2246
01:42:08,520 --> 01:42:09,960
Have a good strategy meeting.

2247
01:42:09,960 --> 01:42:11,690
Okay. See you later.

2248
01:42:11,690 --> 01:42:12,730
See you.

2249
01:42:15,860 --> 01:42:17,700
Seung Jin, we need to talk to you...

2250
01:42:17,700 --> 01:42:19,940
- about something uncomfortable.
- All right.

2251
01:42:19,940 --> 01:42:21,570
- It's about the Deathmatch.
- What?

2252
01:42:21,570 --> 01:42:24,010
The Deathmatch.

2253
01:42:24,010 --> 01:42:26,510
We've analyzed the reasons,

2254
01:42:26,510 --> 01:42:29,110
and I'll skip straight to the conclusion.

2255
01:42:31,880 --> 01:42:34,780
- No, we can't. We can't do that.
- Seung Jin.

2256
01:42:35,020 --> 01:42:36,220
- We can't.
- Seung Jin.

2257
01:42:37,050 --> 01:42:38,590
They started persuading me.

2258
01:42:38,850 --> 01:42:41,460
They wanted to send Jin Hyeong.

2259
01:42:41,460 --> 01:42:43,530
As the oldest one on our team,

2260
01:42:43,530 --> 01:42:45,390
I absolutely could not accept that.

2261
01:42:45,490 --> 01:42:47,360
The idea that, if someone from our team
gets eliminated,

2262
01:42:47,360 --> 01:42:49,360
they should volunteer to leave.

2263
01:42:49,360 --> 01:42:52,970
I personally never agreed to that,
at least on the inside.

2264
01:42:52,970 --> 01:42:54,500
For the survival of our team,

2265
01:42:54,500 --> 01:42:57,540
if someone has to go,
I think it's only right that...

2266
01:42:57,540 --> 01:42:59,070
Lee Jin Hyeong leaves.

2267
01:42:59,070 --> 01:43:01,210
Sung Joo and I talked about...

2268
01:43:01,210 --> 01:43:03,280
the second season of the show,

2269
01:43:04,580 --> 01:43:06,250
there's plenty of karma waiting for him.

2270
01:43:08,120 --> 01:43:09,850
So you're saying
he should go settle his karma.

2271
01:43:10,020 --> 01:43:11,820
Yes, we're giving him
the opportunity early.

2272
01:43:11,820 --> 01:43:13,360
To go take care of it and come back.

2273
01:43:13,960 --> 01:43:16,120
We talked about keeping our loyalty,

2274
01:43:16,120 --> 01:43:18,130
but if Jin Hyeong gets voted to go,

2275
01:43:19,460 --> 01:43:21,260
everything would fall apart.

2276
01:43:22,230 --> 01:43:25,170
It would be better
to bring that out quickly.

2277
01:43:25,330 --> 01:43:27,770
He's our strongest player anyway.

2278
01:43:28,600 --> 01:43:31,010
It's as if a war broke out...

2279
01:43:31,270 --> 01:43:34,210
and we're sending our son
to the front lines first.

2280
01:43:34,310 --> 01:43:36,310
It felt like we were pushing him
into a dangerous situation,

2281
01:43:36,850 --> 01:43:38,680
so I felt very uncomfortable.

2282
01:43:38,780 --> 01:43:40,480
What do we do now?

2283
01:43:40,850 --> 01:43:42,820
- What do we do about him?
- What?

2284
01:43:42,880 --> 01:43:45,120
He keeps insisting that he'll go.

2285
01:43:46,350 --> 01:43:48,460
Is your stance still the same?

2286
01:43:48,660 --> 01:43:49,890
I'm the one...

2287
01:43:51,030 --> 01:43:52,390
who set up this whole thing.

2288
01:43:52,690 --> 01:43:54,330
Yes, you set it up, but we agreed to it.

2289
01:43:54,330 --> 01:43:55,430
Yes, but I set it up.

2290
01:43:55,430 --> 01:43:56,530
We all did.

2291
01:43:56,530 --> 01:43:58,670
I said I’d take responsibility
and set this up,

2292
01:43:59,270 --> 01:44:02,270
so it doesn’t make sense for me not to go.

2293
01:44:02,400 --> 01:44:03,710
Anyway, I'm going to vote for myself.

2294
01:44:04,240 --> 01:44:06,210
- What?
- I'm going to vote for myself.

2295
01:44:06,640 --> 01:44:08,680
So what? You're okay with
putting it to a vote?

2296
01:44:09,110 --> 01:44:11,450
Vote for me. Seriously.

2297
01:44:12,380 --> 01:44:14,550
Seung Jin kept saying, "We can't do that."

2298
01:44:14,720 --> 01:44:16,180
"I feel uncomfortable with that."

2299
01:44:17,090 --> 01:44:18,750
No matter how hard
we tried to persuade him,

2300
01:44:18,920 --> 01:44:20,890
no matter what we said,
we couldn't persuade him.

2301
01:44:20,890 --> 01:44:22,690
Seung Jin was like,
"This is wrong. I'll go instead."

2302
01:44:23,430 --> 01:44:25,260
I didn't expect that from Seung Jin.

2303
01:44:28,960 --> 01:44:29,970
You know what?

2304
01:44:31,100 --> 01:44:34,370
If someone strongly wants to die
in the game,

2305
01:44:34,440 --> 01:44:36,000
- Yes?
- he should be against the vote.

2306
01:44:36,000 --> 01:44:37,740
He should be against the vote itself,
but he's not.

2307
01:44:37,740 --> 01:44:39,340
Instead, he said he was going to
vote for himself.

2308
01:44:40,110 --> 01:44:41,380
That's implicit consent.

2309
01:44:41,540 --> 01:44:42,840
- Right.
- Yes.

2310
01:44:43,140 --> 01:44:46,650
If Jin Hyeong picks Seung Jin...

2311
01:44:47,280 --> 01:44:49,480
and Seung Jin picks himself,
it becomes 2 against 2.

2312
01:44:49,880 --> 01:44:52,450
You and I will stick to the original plan.

2313
01:44:52,720 --> 01:44:55,090
But if Seung Jin
really insists on going...

2314
01:44:55,390 --> 01:44:57,860
and says "Forget the vote, I'll go,"

2315
01:44:57,860 --> 01:44:59,360
we can't stop him.

2316
01:44:59,530 --> 01:45:00,730
If that's not the case
and he doesn't do anything,

2317
01:45:00,730 --> 01:45:02,200
that's implicit consent.

2318
01:45:02,930 --> 01:45:04,630
- So we just proceed as planned.
- Okay.

2319
01:45:04,800 --> 01:45:06,800
It's up to him now,

2320
01:45:06,800 --> 01:45:08,240
because we've already decided.

2321
01:45:08,400 --> 01:45:09,400
Okay.

2322
01:45:11,240 --> 01:45:13,940
We will begin Round Eight
of the card battle.

2323
01:45:13,940 --> 01:45:15,010
(The final round, Round Eight, begins)

2324
01:45:15,180 --> 01:45:16,580
Lee Jin Hyeong will go first.

2325
01:45:16,580 --> 01:45:19,150
Please predict the expected wins,
pick the master color, and make your bet.

2326
01:45:19,210 --> 01:45:22,080
I'll go with blue, zero wins.

2327
01:45:22,250 --> 01:45:24,520
Lee Jin Hyeong has bet on blue, zero wins.

2328
01:45:27,160 --> 01:45:29,160
Do you wish to name a Mate?

2329
01:45:29,160 --> 01:45:30,260
No.

2330
01:45:31,290 --> 01:45:32,730
Gosh, you're a lonely man.

2331
01:45:33,430 --> 01:45:35,400
For Round Eight, we all went...

2332
01:45:35,400 --> 01:45:37,530
thinking that the game was over.

2333
01:45:37,530 --> 01:45:38,700
We just wanted to finish it quickly.

2334
01:45:38,700 --> 01:45:40,700
The goal is to get Team P1
to come in last.

2335
01:45:45,340 --> 01:45:46,640
What?

2336
01:45:46,640 --> 01:45:48,040
I don't want to finish the game quickly.

2337
01:45:48,880 --> 01:45:50,850
Shall we play then?
Let's mess around a bit.

2338
01:45:51,610 --> 01:45:52,780
Just us guys who know how to have fun.

2339
01:45:54,150 --> 01:45:56,580
Are we pretending we didn't see?

2340
01:45:56,720 --> 01:45:57,790
Are we choosing randomly?

2341
01:45:59,520 --> 01:46:01,660
I can even randomly submit this.

2342
01:46:01,660 --> 01:46:02,990
(Reverse card)

2343
01:46:03,760 --> 01:46:04,830
I was furious.

2344
01:46:05,130 --> 01:46:06,490
I really didn't like that.

2345
01:46:07,060 --> 01:46:09,960
The first set will start with the Master.

2346
01:46:10,370 --> 01:46:12,500
Card 15 in blue has been submitted.

2347
01:46:12,500 --> 01:46:16,270
(Lee Jin Hyeong: 15)

2348
01:46:16,270 --> 01:46:18,070
If you have a blue card,
you have to submit it.

2349
01:46:19,070 --> 01:46:20,080
I don't have one.

2350
01:46:20,080 --> 01:46:23,350
(Master: Lee Jin Hyeong, Bet: 0 wins)

2351
01:46:23,350 --> 01:46:25,350
Card 11 in green has been submitted.

2352
01:46:25,810 --> 01:46:27,880
Lee Tae Gyun, please submit your card.

2353
01:46:28,080 --> 01:46:30,450
(Xitsuh: 11, Lee Tae Gyun: dictator card,
Lee Jin Hyeong: 15)

2354
01:46:30,450 --> 01:46:32,290
A dictator card has been submitted.

2355
01:46:32,420 --> 01:46:34,560
- This is frustrating.
- Why drag this out?

2356
01:46:35,220 --> 01:46:36,390
We're busy right now.

2357
01:46:38,230 --> 01:46:39,490
We're busy right now.

2358
01:46:39,990 --> 01:46:42,060
Lee Tae Gyun has won Set One.

2359
01:46:43,530 --> 01:46:45,600
He must have wanted to try it...

2360
01:46:45,600 --> 01:46:46,970
because it looks cool.

2361
01:46:46,970 --> 01:46:49,340
So I was like, "Okay, go ahead and use it.
You can take the win."

2362
01:46:49,470 --> 01:46:52,510
And during the next set,
I submitted a big number...

2363
01:46:52,510 --> 01:46:53,810
and won that set.

2364
01:46:54,210 --> 01:46:56,280
Lee Jin Hyeong has won Set Two.

2365
01:46:56,950 --> 01:46:58,050
Okay.

2366
01:46:59,480 --> 01:47:01,520
To be honest, I couldn't understand.

2367
01:47:01,980 --> 01:47:04,620
Team P3 was allied with Team C,

2368
01:47:04,620 --> 01:47:06,790
it allied with Team P2,
and it allied with Team C again.

2369
01:47:06,920 --> 01:47:08,790
The teams were taking turns...

2370
01:47:08,790 --> 01:47:10,790
joining forces with Team P3 only
and winning.

2371
01:47:11,030 --> 01:47:13,130
So I started to wonder
what kind of deals were made.

2372
01:47:15,460 --> 01:47:16,630
How disappointing.

2373
01:47:17,530 --> 01:47:19,770
The flaw in this strategy is that...

2374
01:47:19,770 --> 01:47:21,500
at least one person from each team...

2375
01:47:21,500 --> 01:47:23,740
is at risk of going to the Deathmatch.

2376
01:47:24,040 --> 01:47:25,910
But in my team, Seung Jin...

2377
01:47:25,910 --> 01:47:27,540
voluntarily took that role.

2378
01:47:28,080 --> 01:47:29,780
I think that's why...

2379
01:47:29,780 --> 01:47:31,850
the rest of us could play the game
more comfortably,

2380
01:47:31,850 --> 01:47:32,910
including myself.

2381
01:47:35,080 --> 01:47:37,090
Round Eight has ended.

2382
01:47:37,090 --> 01:47:38,690
(The final score: Total points)

2383
01:47:38,690 --> 01:47:40,560
(Team P3: 33, Team P1: 14,
Team C: 15, Team P2: 14)

2384
01:47:41,090 --> 01:47:43,790
The Money Challenge results
will be announced.

2385
01:47:44,630 --> 01:47:46,760
The winning team of
today's Money Challenge is...

2386
01:47:47,660 --> 01:47:49,260
Team P3.

2387
01:47:56,200 --> 01:47:59,610
Team P3 will receive 50,000 dollars
in team funds...

2388
01:48:00,010 --> 01:48:02,540
and elimination exemption tickets
for all members.

2389
01:48:02,540 --> 01:48:05,450
The team representative should enter
the voting room immediately...

2390
01:48:05,450 --> 01:48:07,820
to collect the 50,000 dollars.

2391
01:48:12,620 --> 01:48:13,760
I love the smell of cash.

2392
01:48:13,790 --> 01:48:16,620
The acquired funds will be stored
in the team vault.

2393
01:48:17,560 --> 01:48:18,660
Thank you.

2394
01:48:18,660 --> 01:48:21,060
It was worth the effort.

2395
01:48:22,000 --> 01:48:23,630
We're off to such a great start.

2396
01:48:23,770 --> 01:48:26,100
Looking back on my experiences,

2397
01:48:26,170 --> 01:48:28,770
my first days have never been this smooth.

2398
01:48:29,240 --> 01:48:31,370
By winning the main match
on the first day,

2399
01:48:31,370 --> 01:48:32,470
we received
elimination exemption tickets...

2400
01:48:32,470 --> 01:48:34,440
and received 50,000 dollars.

2401
01:48:34,440 --> 01:48:36,640
So despite spending a lot today,
our team funds...

2402
01:48:36,640 --> 01:48:39,050
increased by 10,000 dollars.
We now have 290,000 dollars.

2403
01:48:39,310 --> 01:48:41,980
This is a great start.
We should maintain this momentum.

2404
01:48:43,520 --> 01:48:47,460
(After the Money Challenge ended)

2405
01:48:48,190 --> 01:48:50,360
Whether this becomes a 3-way
or a 4-way battle,

2406
01:48:50,360 --> 01:48:51,360
(Team P2's room)

2407
01:48:51,360 --> 01:48:53,260
we're in trouble.

2408
01:48:53,260 --> 01:48:55,260
Whoever does the Deathmatch...

2409
01:48:55,260 --> 01:48:56,700
should be exempt from the next one.

2410
01:48:57,500 --> 01:49:01,200
If I go, I'll do my best.

2411
01:49:01,200 --> 01:49:02,700
I think you'll be fine...

2412
01:49:02,700 --> 01:49:04,810
- Of course.
- if you don't get too nervous.

2413
01:49:04,810 --> 01:49:05,870
I'm not nervous.

2414
01:49:05,870 --> 01:49:08,440
You can be nervous, but don't worry.

2415
01:49:08,740 --> 01:49:10,710
I think that mindset helped me the most.

2416
01:49:12,480 --> 01:49:14,120
- Let's go take a smoke.
- Okay.

2417
01:49:14,620 --> 01:49:15,680
No.

2418
01:49:21,160 --> 01:49:22,220
- Are you worried?
- Pardon?

2419
01:49:22,220 --> 01:49:23,290
Are you worried?

2420
01:49:24,190 --> 01:49:25,660
I wouldn't say I'm worried.

2421
01:49:25,660 --> 01:49:28,130
I just don't understand why
the other teams underestimate you.

2422
01:49:29,460 --> 01:49:32,130
We've only discussed this
for five minutes, but already...

2423
01:49:32,130 --> 01:49:33,430
he's starting to say things like...

2424
01:49:33,430 --> 01:49:35,640
"I can win this"
and it's a bit irritating.

2425
01:49:35,640 --> 01:49:37,040
- Yes.
- Right?

2426
01:49:37,040 --> 01:49:38,310
Knowing he's going to lose.

2427
01:49:38,340 --> 01:49:39,340
I know.

2428
01:49:39,640 --> 01:49:41,010
It's obvious he's going to lose.

2429
01:49:41,710 --> 01:49:45,380
(Jin Hyeong is looking for
Sung Joo and YunB.)

2430
01:49:45,510 --> 01:49:46,780
The two of them went down.

2431
01:49:46,850 --> 01:49:48,280
- What?
- The two of them went down.

2432
01:49:48,450 --> 01:49:50,750
They probably went to see
who the other teams are sending.

2433
01:49:52,020 --> 01:49:54,190
If you ask me, we should...

2434
01:49:54,420 --> 01:49:56,020
decide on the vote now...

2435
01:49:57,830 --> 01:49:59,790
and deal with the aftermath later.

2436
01:50:00,500 --> 01:50:02,660
- Seung Jin has to agree.
- Right,

2437
01:50:02,660 --> 01:50:03,700
but Seung Jin...

2438
01:50:03,700 --> 01:50:05,570
If he doesn't agree and
the vote ends up tied 2 to 2,

2439
01:50:05,570 --> 01:50:06,570
it would be a nightmare.

2440
01:50:06,700 --> 01:50:08,440
- We'd be doomed.
- We'd have to fight.

2441
01:50:08,440 --> 01:50:09,940
We'd be completely doomed.

2442
01:50:11,240 --> 01:50:12,310
Doing it behind his back
is sneaky, though.

2443
01:50:12,310 --> 01:50:14,210
Yes, doing it behind his back is sneaky.

2444
01:50:14,210 --> 01:50:15,840
So if we do this, it has to be based on...

2445
01:50:16,010 --> 01:50:18,880
the assumption that
Seung Jin is fully on board with us.
